title: mini cheese and onion pastries
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine cheese and onions. Separate dough into 16 triangles; cut each in half diagonally to make 32 triangles.
Place rounded teaspoon of cheese mixture on center of each triangle.
Bring corners to center over filling overlapping ends; press gently to seal.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Brush each lightly with oil; sprinkle with dillweed.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 13 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: aunt jean's cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth gradually adding sugar until blended.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold 8 ounces of Cool Whip into the cream cheese mixture, blending well. Put mixture into the premade pie crust and top with remaining Cool Whip.
Top with cherries and chill for a minimum of 4 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Prepare
rice
(directions
on	package).
Saute onion; add soup, sour cream, wine and curry powder.
Stir in chicken and rice.
Bake,
uncovered, in 2 quart casserole at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Stir before serving.

title: noodle and rice casserole
directions: Saute broken spaghetti noodles (until color changes to light brown) in 1/4 cup margarine.
Place in casserole dish, then add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: frozen pineapple delight
directions: Mix sour cream, lemon juice, sugar and salt.
Add remaining ingredients; blend together.
Pour into lined muffin tins (cupcake tins with paper).
Freeze overnight.
Makes 12.

title: onion pie
directions: Saute onions in butter until clear.
Put in pie shell.
Mix eggs, milk and seasonings to taste.
Pour over onions.
Top with cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pork chops with raisin pine nut
directions: Preheat broiler.
Spray rack in broiling pan with nonstick spray.
Arrange chops on rack and broil 6 inches from heat, until brown and done to taste, 4 or 5 minutes on each side.
In 9-inch nonstick skillet heat oil; add pine nuts and onions and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until brown.
Continue to stir; cook 1 minute longer.
Stir in broth and vermouth and bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; stir in raisins and rosemary and let simmer for 3 to 4 minutes.
To serve, arrange chops on serving dish and top with sauce.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Line a 9 x 13 pan with toasted bread, which you have diced. Add cheese and broccoli. Cover with mushrooms and 8 eggs (slightly beaten). Add salt, pepper and onions. Add milk and sprinkle top with bacon bits. Keep in refrigerator overnight. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions.
Cover with water and boil 15 minutes.
Drain.
Then cover with sugar, salt and vinegar.
Boil 15 minutes.
Pour into scalded jars.
Seal.
Makes about 6 pints.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix and blend well.
Place in a small baking dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm with a mild cracker.
Can also be served hot.

title: won ton soup
directions: Bring to boil the onions, celery and broth.
Cook meat.
Pour grease from cooked meat into boiling broth.
Pour meat into mixture.
Save some of meat for won tons.
Wet won tons and place small amount of meat in center.
Roll won tons and meat together. Drop into boiling soup mixture.
Make sure soup is boiling, or won tons will not cook.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix sour cream and milk in a large bowl. Drain all fruits, cut up grapes and add to sour cream mixture. Refrigerate until set.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Wash beans thoroughly and soak overnight.
In the morning, place beans in bean pot with molasses, oil, liquid smoke and Accent.
Peel onion and add whole to beans.
Add water enough to cover beans.
Cover pot and cook at 200° from 4 to 6 hours, or until beans are tender.
Onion may be removed when beans are done.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add next 2 ingredients.
Mix well. Chill and serve.

title: marshmallow ice cream
directions: Put marshmallows and milk in large boiler over low heat.

Stir until marshmallows are melted. Remove from heat; add vanilla extract and cool. When chilled and beginning to thicken, fold in the cream which has been whipped until thick but not stiff. Pour into freezer canister and add ice and salt as usual. Super good and oh so rich!

title: fresh vegetable salad
directions: Slice vegetables.
Pour dressing over vegetables. Refrigerate, best overnight.
Mushrooms are good also.

title: potato salad
directions: Mash potatoes.
Add boiled eggs, pickles, salt, onions and mayonnaise and you're ready to eat it.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all together, beating slightly.
Line pie shell with pecans, about 1 cup.
Pour filling over nuts.
Use shallow pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Mix butter, powdered sugar and egg yolks.
Fold in Cool Whip. Break 1/2 of angel food cake in tiny pieces.
Put in a large bowl. Top with 1/2 of Cool Whip mixture and top with 1/3 of Butterfinger candy.
Repeat second layer same as first.
Top with Butterfinger candy.

title: ham glaze
directions: Mix all.
Coat ham 3 to 4 times while baking.

title: turkey corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread cooked pasta in bottom of greased pan.
Top with a thin layer of grated Jack cheese.
In a medium bowl, combine soup, sour cream, chili powder, garlic powder, corn, onions and turkey.
Stir to blend well.
Spread evenly over the pasta and cheese layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake an additional 5 minutes.
If you wish, top with chopped tomatoes, chopped olives or green onion.

title: no fail chocolate frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan and cook until it comes to a full boil.
Boil almost two minutes.
Cool in cold water and stir until the right consistency to spread on cake.

title: pucker punch
directions: In
a large container, combine pineapple and grapefruit juices, lemonade and vodka.
Chill.
To serve, pour into punch bowl and mix in ginger ale and club soda.

title: cheesy chicken noodle hot dish
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove from bones and cut in pieces.
Use broth; add noodles and cook until tender.
Add pepper (green) and pimento.
Add grated cheese. When cheese is melted, add sauteed mushrooms (save juice) in butter, then add juice.
Add corn and chicken.
Pour into buttered pan; sprinkle with buttered corn flakes or bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 to 1 hour.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add cake mix and flour.
Knead dough.
Let rise until double.
Divide in half.
Roll to 1/4 inch thick.
Spread on butter, brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Roll.

title: yuletide onions
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: pig-picking cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixer and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 325°. Three layers work best.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix 2 cups sugar with 1/4 cup cocoa, 1/4 cup butter and 1/2 cup milk.
Put in medium size pan on medium heat and cook until comes to boil.
Remove from heat.
Cool for 1 minute.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla extract, 1 pinch salt and 1/2 cup peanut butter. . Mix well.
Add 3 cups uncooked quick cooking oats.
Stir well. Drop on wax paper by teaspoon.
Let set, cool and eat.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Let the sugar, melted margarine and milk come to a boil.
In a bowl, put the oatmeal, coconut, nuts and chips.
Add boiled mixture; drop onto wax paper.

title: lazy day lasagna
directions: Cook noodles on top of range, using package directions.
Brown beef, add onion, bell pepper, sauce and oregano.
Simmer.
Layer noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella, and meat sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake, covered, at 350° about 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl at medium speed for four minutes.
Pour batter into greased Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Drain pineapple and heat juice, adding the jello.
Dissolve jello well.
Add other ingredients.
Chill.

title: iron skillet casserole
directions: Stir together eggs, meal, milk, oil and corn.
Pour over hamburger meat.
Add onion, green pepper and cheese.
Cook at 350° on bottom rack for 25 minutes, then finish browning in top of oven.
Let stand for 10 to 15 minutes before cutting.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Boil until it is brittle in water; pour over popped corn. Stir well.
Make into balls.

title: sweet potato puffs
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add dry tapioca if mixture is not stiff enough.
Roll a large marshmallow into center of potato ball and roll in coconut.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
A pinch of cinnamon and nutmeg can be added for flavor (optional).

title: four layer dessert
directions: Combine flour, margarine and pecans.
Press into the bottom of a pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Whip the cream cheese until fluffy.
Mix Cool Whip and powdered sugar into cream cheese.
Pour over first layer.
Mix pudding and milk and pour on second layer.
Take the remainder of the Cool Whip and place on top of third layer.
Refrigerate.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into four pieces.
Roll each in mixture of 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/3 cup sugar.
Grease Bundt pan.
Place nuts in bottom of pan, then put in layers of biscuit pieces.
Combine margarine, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and brown sugar.
Boil 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour over biscuits and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: margarita sesame salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients except sesame seed in a blender.
Blend until smooth.
Add sesame seed.
Chill before serving.
Extra good on spinach and/or avocado.

title: icebox coconut cake
directions: Mix
cake mix according to package directions.	Bake in a 9
x 13-inch
pan.
Just
as
cake
is finished baking, mix sugar, milk
and
vanilla.
Bring	to a boil and pour over hot cake which has been punched full of holes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in butter in large cooking dish. Add 1 cup water; bring to boil.
Add rice.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Add corn and cream of mushroom soup.
Sprinkle top with grated cheese.
Bake in 350° oven 30 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: philadelphia pineapple bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Put in ungreased pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fluffy omelet
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add dry ingredients, milk and butter.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Fry like pancakes.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: In casserole, layer chicken, broccoli and chicken.
Mix lemon juice, soup, mayonnaise and curry powder and pour over ingredients in casserole.
May sprinkle with more curry powder, if desired. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: butter pecan turtles
directions: Cream 1/2 cup butter or margarine; add 1 cup brown sugar, beating at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Gradually add flour, mixing well.
Press mixture into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with pecans and set aside.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Place in cake pan and bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes or until you can stick a toothpick in cake and it springs back.

title: coconut pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly and mix with sugar, syrup, oleo and vanilla. Stir in pecans and coconut. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 45 minutes or until lightly browned at 375°.
Serve warm or cold with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream or plain.

title: screwball cake
directions: Put all dry ingredients in baking pan and mix well.
Put vinegar, vanilla, and oil in and then pour water over the top. Mix well.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 8-inch square baking pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole(yields 6 servings)
directions: Partially cook vegetables for 5 minutes; drain.
Combine all ingredients, except butter and cracker crumbs.
Put mixture in casserole.
Top with crackers and butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken wings with sauce
directions: Cut chicken wings at joints for easy handling and less mess. Put the tiny ends in freezer to use when making broth, as they have so little meat.
Marinate wings for 3 to 4 hours (or as long as desired) in a favorite sauce, such as barbecue sauce (thinned with water), vinegar, dill pickle juice or a combination of these.
Add horseradish or hot mustard to taste.
Wish-Bone Italian dressing makes a great marinade and sauce by itself.
Soy sauce, hot sauce and sweet and sour sauce all work well.
Bake in 2 (9 x 12-inch) pans at 325° for about 45 to 60 minutes.

title: italian's spaghetti
directions: Cook pasta.
While pasta is cooking, fry the bacon until crispy; set aside.
Whip the eggs with a fork.
Make sure eggs are whipped real well.
Drain pasta and pour eggs over pasta after it has drained.
If pasta is not hot enough to cook the eggs, microwave for 2 minutes and stir pasta.
Break bacon into small pieces and add to pasta.
Add the remaining ingredients and enjoy. It's yummy.

title: zesty slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; stir well.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour before serving.
Yields 12 servings.

title: chocolate-nut log candy
directions: Combine sugar, salt and cocoa in a heavy saucepan; mix well. Gradually stir in milk and syrup.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until soft ball stage (236°).
Remove from heat; stir in butter and vanilla.
Pour onto a buttered 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan; let cool 10 minutes.
With buttered hands, knead candy occasionally for 10 to 15 minutes or until cool enough to hold its form.
Shape into a 12 x 1 1/4-inch rope; roll in pecans.
Wrap in buttered plastic wrap.
Let candy stand at room temperature for 1 hour or until completely cooled.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies(no bakes)
directions: Melt butter, sugar, cocoa, salt and vanilla in a large pan. (You may add 1/4 cup hot coffee to help melt ingredients.)
Bring to a full rolling boil; continue stirring and boiling 3 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in uncooked oats 1 cup at a time.
Quickly spoon out on cookie sheet or wax paper.
Let cool.
Should be ready to eat within 30 minutes.

title: hot rice
directions: Melt butter.
Add onions, bell peppers, hot peppers, mushrooms, broth and shrimp.
Let simmer.
Add 2 cups rice and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cover until all is done.

title: creamy shrimp over rice
directions: Finely chop onion, bell pepper and celery.
Saute this in butter.
Add soup and milk to this and heat on low setting.
Add sour cream, finely chopped tomatoes and shrimp.
Continue to stir over low heat for about 10 minutes until well heated and tomato bits are tender.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serve over rice.

title: sylvia's chocolate caramel pecan cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs and butter; press onto bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: sweet tropical loaves
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and beat on low speed just until moistened.
Beat on high for 2 minutes.
Stir in coconut. Pour into 2 greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans to wire rack to cool completely.

title: vegetable spread
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Combine gelatin, vegetables, salt and mayonnaise in bowl.
Mix well.
Chill, covered, overnight. Serve with bread.

title: lite artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In ovenproof dish, combine artichokes, chilies, mayo and all but 2 tablespoons cheese.
Mix well. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and bake about 50 minutes or until top is lightly browned.
Serve with crisp crackers.

title: amen steak supper
directions: Place meat in center of long piece of foil.
Sprinkle with dry soup mix.
Cover with vegetables.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with salt.
Fold in foil.
Seal securely.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Yields 4 servings.

title: deluxe zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla until thick.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans or 5 small loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until a wooden toothpick comes out clean.
Serves 12.

title: cheese corn bread
directions: Stir flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, corn meal and cheese in bowl.
Beat eggs in bowl with milk, oil and corn.
Add to dry ingredients.
Pour into pan and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Clean and wash kidney beans.
Let soak overnight.
Drain and wash beans.
Cover beans with water in large cast-iron pot.
Bring to boil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Everything should be chopped and/or diced.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook slowly until beans are soft and other ingredients are tender.
Season to taste with pepper, Tabasco and salt.
You may remove some beans (2 cups) and puree in blender and return to pot to add thickness or body. When done, remove bay leaf and crab boil.
Serve over cooked rice. (Usually takes 4 to 6 hours.)

title: basic pudding or pie filling
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt in a saucepan.
Set aside.
Beat egg yolks until fluffy; add milk to yolks.
Add to ingredients in saucepan.
Cook until thick.
Add margarine and vanilla.
At this point, you can add coconut, chocolate chips or bananas.

title: beef bourguignonne
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cornstarch and water in a Dutch oven.
Cover and simmer slowly until meat is tender (about 2 hours).
Remove bay leaves.
Combine cornstarch and water; stir into meat mixture and cook until sauce thickens.
Serve hot over hot noodles or rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ranch beans
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green peppers.
Season with fajita seasoning to taste.
Drain and add Ranch beans.
Simmer on low for 30 minutes.

title: rice with fried vermicelli
directions: Melt oleo in 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Snap vermicelli into pieces about 1-inch long.
Add to saucepan and fry until medium to dark brown.
Add rice and saute until medium to dark brown.
Add rice and saute until rice turns opaque.
(Skip this step if using converted rice.)
Add the water and bouillon cubes and bring to boil.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 18 to 20 minutes.
Fluff with fork and serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: fruit-filled acorn squash
directions: Cut squash in half lengthwise; discard seeds and membrane. Place squash, cut side down, in a vegetable steamer.
Arrange apricots around squash.
Place steamer over boiling water in a Dutch oven.
Cover and steam 15 minutes or until squash is crisp-tender.
Coarsely chop apricots.
Combine chopped apricots, raisins and next 3 ingredients.
Spoon evenly into each squash half.
Cover and steam 5 minutes or until squash is tender. Sprinkle with toasted almonds.

title: coconut sour cream icing
directions: Cream sour cream with powdered sugar, light brown sugar and vanilla.
Fold in whipped cream and coconut.
Ice cake that has been split several hours before time you want to serve.

title: homemade tomato sauce
directions: Put tomatoes into Dutch oven pan.
Add the butter, sugar and cloves.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Brown the onions, celery and additional 1/4 stick butter in frying pan until lightly browned; set aside.

title: best ever meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, eggs, cheese, carrots, milk, bread and onion. Roll into medium size balls.
Put into baking dish.

title: chicken ole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut tortillas into little squares.
Put on bottom of baking dish.
In a bowl, mix chicken, soup, broth, onion, tomato, water, salt and pepper.
Pour on top of cut tortillas and lay chilies on top of mixture.
Bake 35 minutes in the oven; take it out and top with cheese.
Return to oven for 15 minutes more.

title: pumpkin patch bread
directions: Combine the shortening and sugar in a large bowl.
Mix with spoon until blended and crumbly.
Add eggs and beat until fairly smooth.
Mix in orange juice, water and pumpkin.
Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon and baking powder.
Sift into pumpkin mixture.
Stir until dry ingredients are just moistened.
Stir in raisins.
Pour evenly into pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Contains per serving (1 slice): 170 calories; 5 grams fat; 70 mg. sodium and 35 mg. cholesterol.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Layer shrimp, onions and bay leaves in baking dish.
Combine other ingredients and pour over shrimp.
Chill at least 24 hours. Stir occasionally.

title: rainy day pick-me-up
directions: In large saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer 30 minutes or until done.
Stir occasionally. Makes about 8 1/2 cups.

title: microwave garlic-butter shrimp
directions: Melt butter in small bowl.
Stir in garlic powder and parsley flakes.
Set aside.

title: okra salad
directions: Wash, slice, bread and fry okra in usual manner.
Drain on paper towels.
Toss together with remaining ingredients and serve.

title: easy fudge
directions: Lightly grease approximately 8-inch pan.
Microwave chocolate chips and milk, uncovered, on High for 2 minutes.
May need an additional minute, if necessary.
Remove and stir until smooth. Stir in sugar, vanilla and nuts until well blended.
Spread in pan.
Chill for 2 hours.
Cut into small squares.
Serve and enjoy.

title: pineapple stuffing
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat eggs and add one at a time. Fold in pineapple.
Add cubed bread.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a 2-quart greased casserole.
May be used as a side dish or a dessert (top with whipped topping).
Good.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Knead mixture into soft dough.
Do not let rise.
Cut into small pieces immediately and roll into "ropes" (not too thick; they swell in baking).
Twist into pretzel shape.
Lay on foil covered cookie sheet dusted with flour.
Brush with beaten egg and salt lightly as desired.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.
Makes 3 to 6 dozen.

title: pecan pie
directions: In mixing bowl, slightly beat eggs.
Stir in syrup, brown sugar, butter, salt, pecans and vanilla.
Pour into pie crust. Bake on preheated cookie sheet at 375° until center is set when gently shaken, about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Work together graham crackers and 1 stick oleo like pie dough. Place in square pan.
Beat well 1 stick of oleo, powdered sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add on top of crust; then add pineapple on top of egg-sugar mixture.
Place bananas on top of pineapple.
Put Cool Whip on top of bananas.
Add a few cut up nuts and cherries. Refrigerate.

title: creamsicle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions. Let cake cool. Poke holes in top of cake with handle of wooden spoon. Prepare 1 package of Jell-O. Pour over entire cake (while still in pan).

title: tasty hamburgers
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Make 5 patties and cook in ungreased Teflon frying pan.

title: apricot rice
directions: In a deep saucepan, melt butter; saute the onions, celery and ginger over medium heat until soft, 5 minutes.
Add rice and continue to saute until grains are coated.
Add broth, apricots and chutney.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer slowly for 20 to 25 minutes or until rice is tender.
Add nuts and serve hot, garnished with freshly chopped parsley.

title: savory herbed chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Break onion slices into rings.
Put half of the onion in a casserole dish.
Layer chicken on top, then rest of onion, squash, tomatoes, herbs, paprika and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Pour juice over all.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: sweet n sour smokies
directions: Add all ingredients in large sauce pan.
Cook slow until jelly and mustard are blended and sauce thickens.
Stir occasionally.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken breast. Cut up and place in 9 x 13 baking dish. Cook broccoli and place on top of chicken. Mix soups, mayonnaise, and lemon juice. Pour on top of broccoli. Top with shredded cheese. Bake at 350 degrees until brown and bubbly.

title: fresh apple cake(good)
directions: Add the sugar, eggs and oil to apples.
Mix well.
Measure and sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon together.
Stir into apple mixture.
Add nuts and vanilla last.
Pour in pan 10 x 13-inch and bake for 45 minutes to one hour at 350°.
Frost if desired.

title: ann's rice salad
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni according to directions on box.
In a mixing bowl, combine cooked rice, mayonnaise and artichoke hearts (1 jar drained, 1 not).
Mix well.
Add pimento if desired.
Chill overnight.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Mix all the ingredients together. Spray cookie sheets with cooking spray.
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 350° for about 8 minutes.
Keep checking so as not to burn bottom of cookies.
When cookies are completely cooled, ice them.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place rice, onion soup mix, poultry seasoning and water in casserole.
Top with chicken; dot with butter.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: easy swiss steak
directions: Rub large sheet of a heavy duty foil with 1 tablespoon oleo. Place foil in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle roast with 1 envelope of Lipton onion soup mix (dry).
(Do not use entire envelope of mix, if steak weighs less than 2 pounds.)
On top of this put bell pepper (chopped) and the tomatoes only.
Extra slices of onion may be added.
Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon black pepper, garlic powder to taste and m.s.g. or Accent (optional).
To juice from tomatoes, add A.1. sauce and cornstarch.
Mix together and pour over top of meat.
Seal tightly in foil and bake at 350° for about 2 hours.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Place all ingredients in large pot.
Add water and vinegar to cover pickles.
Place on stove and cook until it comes to full boil.
Remove from stove and can.

title: cranberry onion pork chops
directions: In a large nonstick skillet, brown pork chops on one side over medium heat. In medium bowl, stir together French dressing, onion soup mix and cranberry sauce. Turn chops; pour cranberry mixture over chops. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes, until chops are done but still tender.

title: hummus bi tahini(chickpeas with sesame seed paste)
directions: Soak the chickpeas overnight in cold water after checking for small stones and blemished peas.
Wash and rinse several times. Put in pot with 6 cups water and cook on high.
When they are easily mashed between two fingers, they're done.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine buttermilk and dry pudding.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Place 1/2 of fruit mixture in another serving bowl.
Top with pudding mixture.
Place remaining fruit on top.

title: zesty grilled chops
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Place chops in a glass baking dish and pour marinade over them.
Cover overnight in refrigerator.
Cook on grill.
Brush occasionally with marinade.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Let set out overnight after feeding.
Do not use metal spoon or store in metal.
I also bake in glass loaf pan.

title: citrus slush
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; stir until drink mix and sugar dissolve.
Divide into 2 heavy-duty, gallon-size, zip-top plastic bags; freeze.

title: "poke" chops
directions: Sprinkle chops with meat tenderizer and "poke" into meat with fork.
Combine soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce, oil and garlic salt in a shallow pan or casserole dish.
Put the pork chops in the marinade and place in refrigerator for at least 2 hours (overnight is best).
"Poke" and turn occasionally.
Cook on a grill for about 10 minutes on each side (can be broiled in oven). Baste with leftover marinade while meat cooks.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown beef; add taco seasoning, salsa and 1/4 jar of water and cook until done.
Line bottom of pan with cheese; add layer of beef, tortillas and meat to layer.
You will have 3 or 4 layers. Cover and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
This only needs to get hot.

title: butter pecan salad
directions: Combine ingredients, saving enough Cool Whip for top. Decorate with cherries and nuts.

title: popsicles
directions: Dissolve Jell-O, soft drink mix and sugar in boiling water. Add cold water. Pour into ice cube trays, small paper cups or freezer pop molds.
Insert wooden sticks after pops are partially frozen.
Freeze until firm (2 or 3 hours).
Makes 20 to 24 pops.

title: milk gravy
directions: Mix bacon drippings, pepper and flour in skillet.
Brown over medium heat until paste starts to thicken.
Add milk and stir continually until mixture thickens.

title: eggnog(for diabetics)
directions: Combine eggs, milk, vanilla and sugar substitute in a large bowl.
Stir until smooth. Sprinkle with nutmeg, if desired.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix very well all ingredients in a very large bowl.
Drop by small ice cream scoop on well greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until done.
Note: Make a whole bunch.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Place paper liners in 8 to 12-inch muffin pan cups.
Combine all ingredients in a medium-size bowl.
Divide mixture evenly among the muffin cups, depending on the size desired.
These are easy, nutritious and delicious for those who carry sack lunches.

title: chinese beef and peppers
directions: Saute beef, onion and garlic in oil until meat is browned. Add ginger, green pepper strips, bouillon and soy sauce.
Bring to a boil; stir in rice.
Cover; remove from heat and let stand for 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spoon refrigerator rolls
directions: Preheat oven. Dissolve yeast in warm water. Stir all ingredients together. Spoon into greased muffin pans and bake at 425° for 20 minutes. Store leftovers in the refrigerator.

title: applesauce
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Put in saucepan with water; cook until mushy.
Add sugar and sprinkle with a bit of cinnamon.

title: glazed raised doughnuts
directions: Mash potatoes and put in large mixing bowl.
Add butter, sugar and scalded milk.
When lukewarm, add eggs and yeast.
Add salt and flour.
Place in greased bowl and let rise.
Punch down and let rise again.
Roll out to about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut doughnuts and let rise until about double in size.
Fry in deep fat at 375°.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Mix lemonade and condensed milk; fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in pie shell.
Chill before serving.
Freezes well.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Beat 3 eggs and add buttermilk.
Add sugar, cornmeal and margarine. Stir well.
Pour into a greased pan.
Cook at 400° until brown.

title: really great chicken
directions: Arrange pieces of chicken in a single layer in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine soup, onion, mushrooms, mushroom liquid, water and lemon juice in a bowl.
Mix and spoon over chicken pieces.
Bake in 375° oven 1 hour or until chicken is tender and richly browned.

title: biscotti(italian cookies)
directions: Beat eggs until lemon color.
Add sugar, melted shortening and extracts until sugar is blended well.
Have the flour which is your 8 cups plus 16 level teaspoonfuls of baking powder all measured out and add a small amount at a time until you have it all mixed.
If it is too sticky, add 1 more cup plus 2 teaspoons of baking powder to the mixture.
Let stand in the refrigerator for 1 hour.
You can either roll out like a pretzel and tie or make them in balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes on a greased tin.
Makes 7 or 8 dozen.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Wash and dry apples.
Leave skins on if bright red.
Dice apples and add to chopped celery and nuts.
Mix well.
Mix salad dressing and toss just before serving.
Decorate with cherries.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Saute onions in butter.
Layer carrots and cheese in baking dish.
Pour onions over them.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: buster bars
directions: Mix cookies and 1/2 cup melted margarine.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan to form a crust.
Soften ice cream slightly and spread over crust.
Press peanuts into ice cream with back of large spoon. Freeze until firm.
Combine rest of ingredients in medium saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 8 minutes. Remove from heat.
Cool thoroughly.
Spread over ice cream and freeze until firm.
(I don't use all of sauce, it's very rich. Leftover sauce is great ice cream.)

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain and chop artichokes.
Mix all ingredients together except cheese.
Place in 8 x 8-inch baking dish or pie plate.
Cover top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Spread on small party crackers.

title: pizza cups
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Stir in tomato paste, onion and seasonings (mixture will be thick).
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Place biscuits in a greased muffin pan, pressing to cover bottom and sides.
Spoon about 1/4 cup of meat mixture into biscuit-lined cups and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 12 pizza cups.

title: caramel icing
directions: Melt butter, add brown sugar, bring to a boil and cook 1 minute.
Cool 2 minutes.
Add cream, salt and vanilla.
Slowly add sugar, mixing well until creamy.
Spread on cake.

title: duchess soup(1 gallon)
directions: Cook vegetables in fat until tender.
Do not brown.
Add flour and blend well.
Add hot chicken stock and seasonings.
Cook 30 minutes.
Add cheese and milk.
Cook just long enough to heat to serving temperature.
If soup is too thick, add milk.
Soup can be stored in gallon milk jug and servings heated as needed.

title: dream cake
directions: Slice angel food cake in layers.
Beat Dream Whip and milk together.
Add sugar and mix.
Beat cream cheese until smooth. Add Dream Whip mix to cream cheese a little at a time.
Place a layer of cake on plate; add a layer of Dream Whip mixture, layer of cake and Dream Whip mixture until gone.
Put cherry pie filling on top and chill overnight.

title: salmon dip
directions: Mix together until smooth.
Serve with crackers.

title: tater tots casserole
directions: Brown Tater Tots in baking dish, then sprinkle cheese.
Mix potato soup with can of milk.
Pour over tots and bake until warm and cheese is melted.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Bring water and chicken breasts to a boil, cover, reduce heat and simmer until tender...about 30-45 minutes.
Remove chicken from broth, cool and cut into small pieces.
(I do this in the morning and refrigerate broth until dinnertime.)

title: fresh market fruit salad
directions: Chop apples.
Slice bananas.
Mix all ingredients together. Chill before serving.

title: buttered potato wedges in microwave
directions: Place margarine in 1 cup measuring cup; microwave on High for 45 to 60 seconds.
Stir in pepper.
Cut potatoes into quarters. Arrange on 12-inch plate.
Brush with half of margarine.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Rearrange potatoes and brush with remaining butter.
Sprinkle with cheese and green onions.
Cover and microwave on High 7 to 13 minutes or until potatoes are fork-tender.
Let stand 5 to 6 minutes.
Cover with foil during standing time.
Potatoes will hold temperature for 30 minutes before serving when covered with foil.

title: chili colorado
directions: Put the meat, salt and 1/4 cup of the water into a heavy pan. Cover pan and cook over low heat, shaking pan from time to time to prevent sticking, until the meat is just tender, all the liquid absorbed and the fat is rendering out, about 45 minutes.
If it becomes too dry during cooking, add a little water.
Crush the garlic, cumin and oregano in a mortar.
Remove stems from chiles (leave in the seeds and veins). Cover with water and simmer about 10 minutes or until the skin is soft.
Drain and transfer to a blender jar, along with 1 cup of the water, the garlic, cumin and oregano; blend until smooth.
Set aside.

title: potato casserole
directions: Place layer of potatoes in baking dish.
Cover with onion. Crumble hamburger on top.
Make 1 more layer.
Next spread soup on top.
Pour 1 can of water over casserole.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: banana cake *
directions: Sift dry ingredients, then add shortening, sugar, buttermilk and bananas.
Mix enough to dampen flour.
Beat 2 minutes, using low speed on mixer, then add eggs and vanilla.
Beat one minute. Fold in chopped nuts.
Dust cake tin with 6 tablespoons of flour. Cook at 325°.

title: apricot bars(serves 12 to 15)
directions: Rinse apricots; cover with water and boil 10 minutes.
Drain; cool and chop apricots.
Set aside.
Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Mix butter, granulated sugar and 1 cup flour until crumbly.
Pack into pan and bake for 25 minutes.
Sift 1/3 cup flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs and add brown sugar. Beat until well mixed.
Add flour mixture.
Spread over baked layer.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Cut into squares and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: raisin cream pie
directions: Cook raisins in water.
Add 1 cup boiling water.
Add salt, sugar, flour, butter and egg yolks.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Pour in pie crust and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Dice onion and garlic in large saucepan; add rest of ingredients.
Add salt and pepper; saute together while you prepare meatballs.
Broil meatballs before adding to sauce.
Add 1 small can (+) red wine to sauce.
Add meatballs.

title: sock-it-to-me cake
directions: Blend cake mix (reserve 2 tablespoons), sour cream, oil, sugar, water and eggs with electric mixer.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed.
Pour half of the batter mixture in a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube or Bundt cake pan.
Combine brown sugar, cinnamon and 2 tablespoons reserved dry cake mix.
Sprinkle over batter in pan.
Add 1 cup chopped pecans to remaining batter and pour evenly over batter in pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool upright for 25 minutes before removing from pan.

title: sweet potato pie(yields one 9-inch pie)
directions: Make Rich Pastry.
Roll out to a 12-inch round on a lightly floured pastry cloth or board; fit into a 9-inch pie plate.
Trim overhang to 1/2-inch; turn under and flush with rim.
Flute to make a stand-up edge.
Chill while making filling.

title: mother's pumpkin pie(makes 3 pies)
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie crust.

title: sausage and rice
directions: In oleo, brown onion, green pepper, celery and mushrooms. Brown sausage until crumbly.
Boil 4 1/2 cups water; add chicken noodle soup and cook 5 minutes.
Add rice.
Cook until rice is almost done.
Mix all together.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: oatmeal crisp
directions: With an electric mixer thoroughly cream Crisco, sugars, eggs and
vanilla;
beat
well.
In
separate
bowl mix flour, salt and soda.
Add
mixed
dry
ingredients
to
the
cramed mixture; add oats.
Drop by spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 5 to 8 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Using largest bowl, cream together sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat using electric mixer.

Sift flour and measure accurately. Sift again with the baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and salt. Add the flour mixture to the sugar, margarine and egg mixture. Blend well with a wooden spoon.
Add the pumpkin, vanilla and nuts. Blend well after each addition, but do not beat.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour in loaf pans which have been lightly greased and floured.
Fill pans 2/3 full.

title: strawberry parfait
directions: Combine gelatin and boiling water in a mixing bowl, stirring to dissolve.
Add strawberries and let stand for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
In a separate bowl, beat cream until stiff, but not dry.
Blend in sugar and vanilla.
Spoon alternate layers of both mixtures into parfait glasses, ending with cream mixture.
Dash tops with nutmeg and garnish with a whole, fresh strawberry.

title: ham dip
directions: Blend all ingredients and mix at medium speed until smooth and creamy.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: chicken cashew casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; place in baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sour pickles
directions: Fill a gallon jar with cukes, then add salt, sugar and dry mustard.
Top off with cider vinegar to fill jar.
Shake well. Let sit for a few days.

title: chocolate fondue
directions: Break chocolate into pieces about 1-inch square and combine with other ingredients into fondue pot.
Place over low heat and stir until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth.

title: cool pudding dessert
directions: Mix together 1 cup Cool Whip, powdered sugar and cream cheese. Spread on cooled crust.
Mix pudding with milk until thick. Spread pudding mixture on top of cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.

title: chicken breast supreme
directions: Brown chicken on both sides in small amount oleo.
Lightly salt chicken.
Mix soup and mushroom pieces and pour over chicken breasts in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water. Mix dry ingredients. Cut in shortening. Add yeast mixture and buttermilk. Mix well.

Roll out on floured board and cut out as biscuits. They do not need to rise before baking. Bake at 400° for approximately 20 minutes. Unused dough will keep up to a week if well covered and refrigerated. After cutting as biscuits, you may brush on a bit of melted margarine and turn over as Parker House rolls.

title: robert redford sugarless pie
directions: Melt margarine; mix crumbs and Equal or Sweet 'N Low together. Spread into a 13-inch cake pan and cool.
Mix lite cream cheese and Cool Whip with 3 or 4 packages of Equal.
Spread on top of cracker crumbs.
Cool 1 box of instant vanilla and 1 box of chocolate pudding.
Mix as directed and combine both.
Spread on top of Cool Whip.
Mix.
Cool.
Put 8 ounces of Cool Whip on top.

title: simple cherry cheese cake
directions: Blend cream cheese and sugar together.
After it is blended, add Cool Whip and beat until fluffy.
Spoon into pie crust and cover with pie filling.

title: pork chops delicious
directions: Brown chops in a little butter.
Add pepper, teriyaki sauce, Worcestershire sauce and beer. Simmer until half done and add onion rings and mushrooms. Continue cooking about 15 minutes or until chops are tender.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Melt margarine and saute onion.
Add potatoes, soup, cheese, sour cream and seasonings.
Pour into buttered casserole dish. Mix melted margarine and corn flakes.
Pat into a crust, covering potatoes during last 10 minutes of baking.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: streusel filled coffee cake
directions: Sift the four, baking powder, salt and sugar together. cut in the shortening with a pastry blender until the mixture is like fine corn meal.
Blend in well beaten egg, mixed with the milk.
Then blend in the vanilla, and beat just enough to mix well.
Pour half of the batter into a well greased and floured 6x10-inch or an 8-inch square baking pan.
Sprinkle with half the streusel mixture. Add remaining batter, and sprinkle remaining streusel mixture over the top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: marshmallow icebox loaf
directions: Cut marshmallows in quarters and pour water over them.
Add sweetened condensed milk, chopped nutmeats and chopped dates.
Add cracker crumbs and blend.
Form into rolls or loaf about 6 inches long and 3 inches in diameter.
Place in refrigerator.
Let ripe 12 hours before serving.
Serve in slices.
May be garnished with whipped cream.
Serves 10.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together; drop and cook at 375°.

title: pecan pies
directions: Line pie shell with pecans.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over pecans, making sure they're all coated with mixture. Bake at 350° until the top starts to crack around the pecans in the middle of the pie.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make balls the size of marbles.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
May be served hot or at room temperature.
Dough may be frozen and cooked at a later date.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend soup and milk.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, alternately arrange potatoes, onion, soup sauce and seasonings. Dot with margarine.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°, then cover and bake 15 minutes more. Serves 4 to 6.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Cook lasagne according to package; drain and rinse in cold water.
Drain and set aside.
Stir together egg whites, cottage cheese and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Set aside.

title: apple butter sweet potatoes
directions: Prepare sweet potatoes; cut into 1-inch cubes.
Cook in light salted boiling water to cover until tender, about 15 minutes. Drain and let cool.
Melt butter in large nonstick skillet over medium heat; mix in apple butter, sugar and salt.
Add sweet potatoes.
Cook over medium-low heat until heated through, stirring often, gently.
Turn into serving bowl.
Sprinkle with pecans.

title: nancy's tuna marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients in a food processor with metal blade or blender.
Blend for 30 seconds, until smooth.
Marinate for at least 1 hour at room temperature.
Spread over fresh tuna and bake.

title: sausage soup
directions: Parboil sausage; cut in bite size slices.
Brown sausage in a large pan, drain off fat.
Add all remaining ingredients except cabbage and Parmesan.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer at least 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Add cabbage and simmer 5 minutes longer.
Serve topped with Parmesan cheese.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Cut or coarsely grind all vegetables except carrots and put in salt water brine overnight.
(Bring:
1/4 cup salt to 1 quart water.)
Next day, drain brine; add carrots (cooked and chopped). Cook vinegar and spices together.
Bring to a boil.
(Pickling spice should be put in cheesecloth.)
Add vegetables and cook 10 minutes.
Seal while hot.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Mix turkey or chicken with mayo, chopped onion and the celery.

title: big soft ginger cookies
directions: Combine flour, ginger, soda, cinnamon, cloves and salt; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, beat margarine with an electric mixer on low speed for 30 seconds to soften.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add egg and molasses; beat well.
Stir dry ingredients into beaten mixture.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls (1 heaping tablespoon of dough each).
Roll in the 2 tablespoons sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheet about 2 1/2-inches apart.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until light brown and still puffed.
(Do not overbake.)
Let stand for 2 minutes before transferring to wire rack.
Cool.
Makes 24 (3-inch) cookies.

title: lemon tarts
directions: Separate tart crusts.
Mix instant pudding with milk until well blended.
Fill each tart crust approximately 3/4 full, using a large spoon.
Top with whipped cream, using a cake decorator or spray can and maraschino cherries, if desired.
Chill until time to serve.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Melt margarine; add sugar and milk.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Boil
for
2 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in chocolate
chips, beating until smooth and creamy.	Ices 3 layers.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Make plain or add desired amount of berries.
Bake at 400° to 425° for 20 minutes.

title: four bean salad
directions: Bring vinegar, water, sugar and salt to a boil.
Cook to lukewarm and pour over vegetables.
Will keep for a long time in refrigerator.
The longer you keep it, the better it tastes.

title: taco salad
directions: Fry meat in large skillet; drain.
In large bowl, combine lettuce, tomato, onion, peppers, olives and cheese; toss well.
Add meat, chips and beans; toss lightly.
Serve with dressing.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes and drain well.
Mash potatoes; add butter and sugar and beat well.
Add eggs, nutmeg, pumpkin spice, flour and milk and beat well.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 4 pies.

title: pasta with cheese and walnuts
directions: Cook pasta.
At the same time in large saucepan melt butter over medium heat.
Add garlic and saute 30 seconds.
Add spinach, salt and pepper; saute 2 minutes or until spinach is wilted. Transfer pasta to a warm serving bowl.
Add spinach, tomatoes and goat cheese; toss well.
Makes 4 servings, containing 645 calories each.

title: pasta shells with artichokes
directions: Saute peppers in oil, garlic and basil until crisp and tender. Chop artichokes and add to peppers to heat.
Add pasta, salt and pepper.
Follow sparingly with a few good dashes of wine vinegar. Drain excess oil.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Toss and transfer to platter.
Serve with a goblet of your favorite wine and hearty loaf of bread!
Bon appetit!

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine; press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly, adding enough milk or water to moisten well.
Bake in oven about 1 hour.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix milk, cheese, eggs, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over bread and sausage in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let sit 15 to 30 minutes. (Best if made the day before and refrigerated.)
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: 1886 gingersnaps
directions: Rub shortening and sugar together into the flour; add enough more flour to roll very smooth, very thin and bake in a quick oven.
The dough can be kept for days by putting it in the flour-barrel under the flour and bake a few at a time.
The more flour that can be worked in and the smoother they can be rolled, the better and
more brittle they will be.
Should be rolled out to wafer-like thinness.
Bake quickly without burning.
They should become perfectly cold before putting aside.

title: grandma's deep butter cake
directions: Sift flour and salt together in a large mixing bowl.
Add sugar and margarine; mix with fingers to form crumbs.
Take out 1 cup of crumbs.
Then add rest of the ingredients and beat 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased and floured pan. Sprinkle 1 cup of reserved crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chicken breast baked in lemon and garlic
directions: Heat small skillet; add olive oil.
Heat and add garlic. Saute 30 seconds.
Stir in lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil; set aside.
Arrange chicken in lightly buttered shallow baking dish, enough to hold chicken in single layer.
Pour garlic mix over chicken; sprinkle with grated lemon peel.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 10 to 15 minutes more or until chicken is done.
Transfer to plates; pour from dish into small skillet.
Add broth and bring to boil.
Cook until reduced by 1/2 and mixture is syrupy.
Pour over chicken and serve.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Cook broccoli; drain well.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, eggs and onions.
Blend in cooked broccoli.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Melt oleo and seasoned crumbs; mix well and sprinkle over top.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pecan ladyfingers
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add water and vanilla; blend.
Cut in flour with nuts and salt.
Mix into a ball of dough, then roll in small finger size.
Bake in slow oven (250°) for about 1 hour. Roll in powdered sugar while hot.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, meal and flour.
Beat eggs and blend in the sugar mixture.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake about 40 minutes in slow oven at 325°.

title: cocktail meatballs(do ahead)
directions: Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, onion, milk, egg, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce together.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Melt shortening in large skillet and brown meatballs.
Remove meatballs from skillet and pour off fat.
Heat chili sauce and jelly in skillet, stirring constantly, until jelly is melted.
Add meatballs and stir until thoroughly coated.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.
Serve hot.

title: bean burritos
directions: Combine first two ingredients; set aside.
Spoon heaping 1/2 cup bean mixture and 1 tablespoon cheese onto center of each tortilla.
Roll up tortillas to enclose filling.
Place seam side down in 11 x 17-inch microwavable dish.
Pour taco sauce evenly over burritos.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Loosely cover dish.
Microwave on High 10 to 12 minutes or until heated through. If desired, garnish with lettuce, tomato and black olives.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine flour, 1 cup sugar and milk.
Mix well.
Pour over melted butter.
Do not stir. Combine peaches and 1 cup sugar and bring to a boil.
Pour over batter.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat water and margarine to a rolling boil in saucepan.
Stir in the flour, vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball, about 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs, all at once, beating until smooth.
Drop by scant 1/4 cup 3 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until puffed and golden, 40 minutes.
Keep away from draft.
Cool.
Cut off tops; spoon out filaments of soft dough.
Fill with pudding.
Replace tops.
Dust with powdered sugar.
Refrigerate.

title: ratatouille
directions: In 3-quart casserole, combine onion, green pepper, oil and garlic.
Cover with lid.
Cook at High 4 minutes.
Stir.
Add remaining ingredients; stir.
Cover.
Cook at High for 18 to 20 minutes.
Stir twice.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes before serving.

title: pumpkin custard pie
directions: Mix in order listed and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 350° to 400° oven for about 25 minutes.
I bake longer, more like an hour.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Cook chicken until well done in unsalted water.
Pick off bones.
Set aside.
Save broth.
Melt margarine.
Stir into dressing mix.
In a greased 13 x 9-inch dish, put layer of dressing crumbs, layer of chicken and layer of celery soup diluted with one can broth.
Place another layer of dressing crumbs, layer of chicken and can of chicken soup diluted with one can chicken broth. Top with dressing crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to one hour.

title: thickening agent
directions: Mix together and store in covered container.
Can be used to thicken gravies, sauces, soups, fruit pie and anything that needs to be thickened.
I usually start with 1 or 2 tablespoons to 1/4 cup water.

title: granny's baked beans
directions: Rinse beans and soak, covered, overnight.
Cook very slowly in water (on top of stove) until beans split open when blown on. Drain.
Place beans in bean pot with pork and other ingredients; cover with water.
Bake in moderate 350° oven for 5 or 6 hours. Let water cover the beans until the last hour.

title: spinach meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine all ingredients and mix well. The mixture should be moist.
Form into loaf.
Place in loaf pan. Bake 1 hour.

title: owens sausage and hot apple sandwiches
directions: Crumble sausage and saute until just gray.
Drain excess oil and add apples, onions and cinnamon and continue to saute until the onions are translucent and the apples are just tender.
Heat a pocket sandwich maker until hot.
Spread margarine on one side of four slices of bread.
Place two slices of bread on the sandwich maker, margarine side down, and put 1/6th of the sausage apple mixture on each slice.
Top each with another slice of bread, margarine side out.
Seal and cook until nicely browned.
Continue until bread and mixture are gone.
This should make 12 half sandwiches.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and rhubarb. Add juice. Turn into pastry lined pie pan. Dot with butter. Cover with strips of pastry to make a lattice. Bake at 450° for 20 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 350° and bake 20 minutes on foil covered cookie sheet in middle of oven.

title: lemon squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix, margarine and 1 egg until crumbly.
Measure out 1 cup and reserve.
Pack rest
in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake until light brown (15 minutes).
Mix remaining ingredients together and beat until light and foamy.
Pour over hot layer and sprinkle reserved crumbled mix and bake 15 minutes more.
Sprinkle powdered sugar.

title: potato fritters
directions: Heat water, butter and salt until water comes to boil.
Add flour and stir until it forms a ball and leaves side of pan. Remove pan from heat and add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Peel potatoes and cook in salted water until tender; drain.
Cool slightly.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Make Stove Top according to directions.
Cook cheese, soup and milk until cheese is melted, stirring constantly.
Put chicken in casserole dish followed by Stove Top and pour cheese mixture on top.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine the first 9 ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well. Spoon chicken mixture into a lightly greased shallow 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with cheese and top with potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients three times.
Add eggs, unbeaten.
Add fruit cocktail.
Mix together.
Place in 9 x 15-inch pan, greased and floured.
Sprinkle with nuts and brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Put chicken in a greased casserole dish.
Mix mushroom soup and sour cream together.
Pour over chicken.
Melt margarine and mix with poppy seed.
Spread on top of casserole.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 400 degrees.

title: broccoli casserole 2
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on the box.
Drain and season to taste.
Mix remaining ingredients and fold into broccoli.
Pour into a baking dish.
Sprinkle with Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350 for 45 minutes.

title: almond bars
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and flour and press into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Beat eggs, sugar, almond extract and coconut.
Mix and put over crumb layer.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except cheese.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into large greased skillet (heated).
Put 1/2 of cheese on top.
Put remaining mixture in with rest of cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 55 minutes.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Grate the cheese, margarine and eggs into a bowl.
Add the drained olives, pimiento, onion and soup.
Mix well and add salt and pepper to taste.
Spread on rye bread cocktail rounds and place under broiler until bubbly.

title: spanish style pork chops
directions: Season pork chops with salt and black pepper.
Cut green peppers and onions.
Place seasoned pork chops into a hot skillet. Pour ketchup all over pork chops.
Pour a little water so food does not stick.
Add the green peppers and onions.
Let simmer for about 1/2 hour.
Thicken with flour and water to make gravy. Serve over rice.

title: pie oh my
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into graham cracker pie crust.
Let chill.

title: chocolate cinnamon sheet cake
directions: Melt butter, Crisco, water and cocoa in saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients to mixture.
Stir well.
Pour into ungreased deep large cookie sheet or jelly roll pan.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes or until it tests done.
Frost while still warm.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese. Blend together the Marshmallow Creme, cream cheese and lemon juice.
Serve with fruit.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in half the called for amount of hot water (1 cup).
Add gelatin and after it dissolves, add half the amount of cold water (1/2 cup).
Add nuts, pineapple and cranberries.
Pour in mold and refrigerate.

title: onion cheese casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter until transparent.
Place in buttered casserole; sprinkle with cheese.
Do not mix.
Mix soup with milk; pour over cheeses and onions.
May stick buttered slices of French bread around sides.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients, except butter.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Pour melted butter on top.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes until browned.

title: salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients and add dressing.

title: pastry shell
directions: Mix all ingredients; form into ball.
Let set about 5 minutes. Roll out and place in pan. Bake, then cool before filling.

title: slush punch
directions: Dissolve gelatins as directed on package.
Mix frozen limeade and lemonade in 1 quart of water.
Add to gelatin mixture along with pineapple juice.
Freeze, stirring frequently.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and ice cubes, if needed.
Serves about 50.

title: chicken wings
directions: Heat first 5 ingredients together.
Pour over chicken wings. Bake, covered, at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes on each side.
Uncover last 1/2 hour to brown.

title: supreme potatoes
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Thaw potatoes. Combine potatoes, soups, onion, sour cream, milk, salt and pepper.
Put mixture in greased pan. Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes. Remove foil and put cheese and bacon on top. Bake an additional 15 minutes.
(Some ovens may take a little longer.)

title: quick and easy meatballs
directions: Place meatballs, salsa and grape jelly in saucepan, crock-pot or chafing dish.
Simmer for at least 30 minutes.
Serve with picks.

title: tamale pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; cook together just to soften the onion and brown meat. Add remaining ingredients and cook 20 minutes on low heat. Add 3 well beaten eggs, mixing thoroughly. Turn into large casserole and bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: orange oatmeal cookies
directions: Cut candy slices in small pieces.
Mix with 1/3 cup flour. Sift remaining flour with baking powder, soda and salt; set aside. Cream butter and sugars.
Add egg and vanilla; beat thoroughly. Stir in flour mixture, oats, coconut and candy; shape into small balls.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Arrange all the ingredients in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Cover with foil and place in preheated 350° oven and bake for 1 hour.

title: hamburger noodle stroganoff
directions: Brown beef and onion; pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish (10 x 6 x 2-inch).
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until hot; stir.
Put buttered bread crumbs on and bake for 5 minutes more.
Garnish with tomato slices.

title: crawfish macque chaux
directions: Saute first four ingredients in margarine.
Add Ro-Tel.
Cook 30 minutes.
Add corn.
Cook 30 minutes.
Add crawfish, salt and pepper.
Cook 15 minutes.
Thicken with cornstarch and water. Cook 5 minutes.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Fry chicken.
Add tomato sauce and ingredients.
Simmer and serve.

title: crazy pea salad
directions: Mix together.
Put in a 2 1/2-quart baking dish.

title: fudge brownie muffins
directions: Place butter and cocoa in microwave on High for 1 minute until butter melts. Set aside. Combine eggs, sugar and vanilla. Add butter mixture, flour, cinnamon and pecans, stirring until blended. Place batter in paper cups. Fill 2/3 full. Sprinkle each muffin with 6 to 8 chocolate morsels. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Makes 10.

title: chocolate chip ice cream
directions: Separate eggs.
Whip egg yolks with a little milk.
Add junket tablets, sugar and a little more milk.
Stir until sugar is completely dissolved.
Add salt and vanilla.
Whip egg whites and fold into other mixture.
Pour into ice cream maker can and add milk to the line on can.
Turn until it begins to thicken, then add chocolate chips.
It is finished when you can not turn any more. Put into freezer until ready to serve.

title: noodle salad
directions: Toss first 3 ingredients together. Saute noodles in butter or olive oil until slightly brown. Cool and toss with greens. Add almonds and sesame seeds.

title: creek coffee cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar and mix thoroughly.
Add eggs, beating well.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add slowly to mixture, kneading well.
Using a small piece of dough (a little larger than a walnut), roll in your hand to any shape desired.
Brush with a beaten egg; dip in sesame seeds.
Bake on cookie sheet in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until light golden brown.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Melt oleo and peanut butter over low heat.
Stir in both sugars and eggs, beating well.
Gradually stir in flour mixture until a smooth soft dough forms.
Cover tight and refrigerate 1 hour.
Drop spoonfuls of dough 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork in crisscross pattern.
Bake 8 to 12 minutes at 350° or until slightly firm.
Let cool for about 1 minute and remove.

title: california casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in oil and place in a 3-quart casserole.
Saute meat and add to casserole with remaining ingredients except cheese.
Spread cheese on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 generously.

title: tangy wiener pickups
directions: In a 1-quart casserole, combine gravy mix and water.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook, uncovered, for 6 minutes on High, stirring twice.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Fry bacon.
Mix remaining ingredients together and sprinkle bacon on top.

title: mom's clam chowder
directions: Drain clams and pour over vegetables.
Add water to cover. Cook until tender, about 20 minutes.
In separate pan, melt butter and add flour.
Blend and cook 1 minute.
Add cream.
Stir with whip utensil until smooth and thickened.
Add to vegetables and clams; mix well.
Season with salt, pepper and sugar.
Serves a lot (10).

title: turkey with mushrooms
directions: Saute the mushrooms in the butter.
When brown, add the turkey.
Saute only until hot.
Add the remaining ingredients; stir for about a minute and remove the turkey and mushrooms to a heated platter.
Reduce the sauce and pour over the turkey.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: meringue for pies
directions: Beat egg whites until they form a peak.
Add sugar gradually. Beat until all sugar is dissolved and stiff and glassy.

title: scallops and shrimp with linguine(serves 6)
directions: Place rinsed scallops and shrimp in a bowl and set aside. Wash peas and cut in half. Set aside.
In a skillet, cook onion and garlic in hot oil and margarine over medium heat for 30 seconds.
Add half of the seafood mixture, parsley, basil and hot pepper.
Cook for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring, or until scallops are opaque and shrimp turn pink.
Remove scallops and shrimp mixture with a slotted spoon and set aside. Repeat with remaining scallops and shrimp.
Return all of the mixture to skillet. Add tomatoes and pea pods.
Cook and stir for 2 more minutes. Toss mixture with linguine in a large bowl and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Enjoy.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Heat cranberry sauce, being careful not to scorch.
Stir gently so as to not break or mash berries.
Strain, reserving juice.
Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add salt and lemon juice. Chill until slightly jelled (enough to mound a little when dropped from spoon).
Mold in individual molds or one large mold.

title: pina (no-collida) colada
directions: Blend until smooth.
Thin if necessary with Master of Mixes mixer or pineapple juice. Garnish with a dab of whipped cream and a toothpick with a cherry and pineapple chunk.
Makes 4 (8 ounce) servings.

title: elizabeth's casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions and drain.
Add all ingredients except cheese.
Spread 1/2 of mixture into casserole dish.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Spread remaining mixture on top of Cheddar cheese and top with remaining cheese. Top with can of onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: date-nut squares
directions: Mix oatmeal, flour, brown sugar, baking soda, salt and butter or margarine like pie crust.
Spread 3/4 of mixture in bottom of buttered tin.
Pat down until firm.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk in a medium bowl, stirring with a wire whisk until smooth. Gently fold 1 cup Cool Whip into pudding mixture. Toss in banana slices with lemon juice. Arrange banana slices over bottom of crust. Spoon pudding mixture over bananas. Cover and chill 1 1/2 hours or until set. Pipe or spoon remaining cup of Cool Whip around edge of the pie just before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Sauce the onions in tablespoon of butter until tender.
Add the following ingredients:
soup, chestnuts, beans, mayonnaise and pimento.
Cook rice according to directions on the box.
Add 1 tablespoon butter to the water; add to the first mixture.
Pour into a baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Cook at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Can be served with a salad and French bread.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Melt and mix; pour over mixture and top with nuts or coconut. Chill until firm; cut and serve.

title: onion-dill freeze and bake rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water, add 2 teaspoons sugar; let stand 5 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients.
Knead until smooth, 6 to 8 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, cover and let rise until doubled, 1 1/2 hours.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: In a large soup pot, brown beef cubes, then add onion and garlic.
Cook 5 minutes or until soft.
Add remaining ingredients except frozen vegetables.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add frozen vegetables; simmer 10 minutes more.

directions: Preheat

to 350° and grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan. Heat

title: baked macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni by package directions; drain.
Mix onion, pepper, pimento, mushroom soup and mayonnaise.
Blend with macaroni and bake at 375° to 400° until golden brown.

title: beau's pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until tender; drain.
Add all ingredients except cheese.
Mix and put in baking dish.
Top with grated cheese and bake on 350° until bubbly.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Using 4 cup glass measuring cup, place sugar, syrup, salt and margarine in it.
Place in microwave and bring to a full boil (full power 2 to 4 minutes).
Remove from microwave and stir in baking soda.
Spray inside of a large grocery bag with nonstick cooking spray.
Add corn pops or popcorn and pour hot mixture over corn.
Place in microwave on full power for 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake; repeat.
Microwave 1/2 minute.
Shake; repeat.
Place on hot cookie sheet.
Cool.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add onions, Worcestershire sauce, chili powder and salt.
Add 1 large can tomato juice.
Add sugar to own taste.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: perfect tuna casserole
directions: In 1-quart casserole, blend soup and milk.
Stir in tuna, eggs and peas.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot; stir.
Top with chips and bake 5 minutes more.

title: taco salad
directions: Prepare lettuce as for a salad.
Toss with hamburger, tomatoes, onion, taco chips and 1 package taco seasoning.
Mix Miracle Whip, sugar, 3 tablespoons taco seasoning and taco sauce.
Mix in chips and Miracle Whip mixture just before serving.
Add black olives, if desired.

title: quiche
directions: Mix and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 15 minutes at 425°, then reduce heat to 300° and bake 30 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add beaten eggs. Cream the bananas until fluffy. Add to the sugar mixture alternately with the dry ingredients. Add chopped nuts.
Pour into a greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until you poke with a toothpick and it comes out clean.

title: banana pudding
directions: Layer ingredients in order given so that you have two complete layers.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: best cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Frost with Cool Whip but can use cream cheese frosting.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix ingredients in a blender and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: governor's buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into baked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: grandma bradshaw's sweet potato biscuits
directions: Sift together the flour, salt and baking powder.
(If you use self-rising flour, leave out baking powder.)
Add shortening and beat until smooth.
Add the dry ingredients to the potato mixture alternately with the milk.
Blend well.

title: petros
directions: Prepare ingredients as noted above and then layer the ingredients in each serving bowl as follows:

crunch 2 handfuls of Fritos in the bottom of each bowl; add 1 handful of shredded cheese; add 4 tablespoons of Hormel chili; add 1 handful of lettuce; add 1 1/2 tablespoons of tomatoes; add 1 tablespoon of onions; and then add 2 teaspoons of sour cream.
This can be eaten as a layered salad or mixed up and eaten.
Either way, it is wonderful.
Serves approximately 8.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat 12 egg yolks until they are light.
Gradually add 1 1/2 cups sugar and chill it.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Mix pecans and sugar thoroughly.
Add egg whites and vanilla; mix well.
Drop by scant teaspoonfuls on well-greased cookie sheet 1 inch apart.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Moisten confectioners sugar with water; dot top of each cookie with mixture.
Remove with spatula.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Mix together pretzels with oleo and sugar.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 8 minutes.
Cool.
Beat together cream cheese and sugar.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust. Dissolve jello in water.
Stir in strawberries.
Mix well until it starts to set.
Pour over cheese mix and refrigerate.

title: noodle medley
directions: Brown ground beef in 2 tablespoons of fat.
Add onion, green pepper and celery.
Cook slowly until still crunchy (don't overcook).
Add remaining ingredients and seasonings.
Stir until well blended.
Cover skillet and bring to a boil.
Turn heat to low and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve hot.
Can be put into casserole after bringing to a boil and bake at 350° until frillets are done or freeze to bake later.

title: apricot bread
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Add eggs and oil.
Mix well.
Add apricots.
Mix well.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat until fluffy.
Pour into three 9-inch layer pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° until done, about 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: homemade sugar cookies
directions: Combine flour and salt in a bowl and set aside.
Add remaining sugar and eggs; mix well, while slowly pouring in flour mixture. Chill thoroughly.

title: peanut butter-fruit cookies
directions: In a large saucepan, stir together sugar and corn syrup.
Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves, then remove from the heat. Add peanut butter; mix well.
Stir in cereal and fruit until well coated.
Press into an ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Cool until firm, then cut into bars.
Makes 24 servings; 2 grams of fat per serving.

title: never fail meringue
directions: Cook sugar, water and cornstarch until clear and let stand. Beat egg whites until dry.
Add to sugar mixture and beat until dry and shiny.

title: congo bars
directions: Mix melted butter and brown sugar.
Add flour, salt, baking powder and eggs and mix together.
Fold in chocolate and butterscotch chips and walnuts.
Do not grease pan!
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: no dough cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside.
Combine flour, 3/4 cup sugar and baking powder; add milk and stir until blended. Pour batter over butter in pan; do not stir.

title: authentic ratatouille *
directions: Heat 5 tablespoons oil in large heavy skillet and when hot, add eggplant.
Cook, stirring, about 3 minutes.
Remove with slotted spoon and drain in colander with bowl under.
Add zucchini to skillet with salt and pepper; cook about 3 minutes.
Add to eggplant.
Add remaining oil, plus whatever has accumulated in bowl, to pan with onions and peppers and cook until wilted.
Add eggplant, zucchini, salt and pepper and thyme.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and stir.
Cover; simmer for 20 minutes. Uncover.
Add garlic and cook about 10 minutes to reduce liquid. Tastes best at room temperature.

title: clam chowder
directions: In microwave-safe dish with lid, melt butter and onion.
Saut onion 2 to 3 minutes (time differs per microwave).
Add the remaining ingredients and return to microwave and cook 20 minutes, stirring twice.
Serve.

title: zucchini-apricot jelly
directions: Boil zucchini on low for 15 minutes; stir often.
Reduce heat. Add sugar.
Boil 6 minutes; stir often.
Add lemon juice and undrained pineapple.
Boil 6 minutes and stir.
Add jello.
Pour into container and freeze.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add well beaten egg yolks, then add milk gradually and stir until smooth.
Then cook in a double boiler until thick.
Add the juice and grated rind of 2 lemons and pour in a baked 9-inch pie shell.
Top with beaten egg whites to which 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla has been added.
Bake until golden brown.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: reduced-calorie ranch dressing
directions: In a jar, with a tight fitting lid, combine all ingredients. Shake well to blend.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours, allowing flavors to blend.
Makes 24 (1 tablespoon) servings at 8 calories each.

title: chop suey hot dish
directions: Brown meat with onion.
Mix all together and cook in medium oven for 1 hour or crock-pot all afternoon.
Top with slivered almonds or chow mein noodles.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add zucchini, flour, cinnamon and nuts.
Blend together.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Divide between the 2 pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Bakes real good and looks pretty to bake it in 3 coffee cans.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Mix.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer until tender, approximately 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Put broccoli in a casserole.
Stir in uncooked stuffing and herbs.
Add butter.
Spread soups over mixture.
Sprinkle onion on top.
Add cheese to taste over onions. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pita bread
directions: In a warm mixer bowl, combine 2 c. flour, yeast, sugar, salt and water.
Blend until moistened, then beat by hand for 3 minutes. Stir in 2 1/2 to 2 3/4 c. flour to make firm dough.
Knead on floured board until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes.
Cover dough with plastic wrap and towel.
Let rise for 20 minutes.
Punch down dough.
Divide into 12 equal parts.
Shape each part into a smooth ball and place on floured board leaving space between each ball.
Cover and let rise 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 500°.
