Roll each ball into a 6 inch circle.
Place 3 circles at a time on a cookie sheet and bake 3 to 4 minutes.
(They do not burn.)
Cool on racks.

title: pumpkin banana nut bread
directions: Combine pumpkin, bananas, sugar and oil in large bowl.
Beat well.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Beat in remaining ingredients, except nuts.
Stir in the nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 13-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a slow oven at 325° for about 1 hour or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Decorate with powdered sugar glaze.

title: cereal flake kisses
directions: Beat egg whites with salt until stiff, but not dry.
Add sugar in small amounts, beating after each addition, until stiff.
The mixture should hold its shape by the time all the sugar is added. Beat in vanilla.
Fold in coconut and cereal.

title: barbecue chuck roast
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Plus add 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Pour mixture over roast.
Marinate 2 to 3 hours. Place on grill and baste.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: ham casserole
directions: Cook vermicelli as directed on package.
Drain.
Blend soup, milk, water, parsley and pepper in large pot and heat well.
Stir in ham and vermicelli.
Place mixture in a lightly sprayed casserole dish.
Mix bread crumbs and melted margarine together and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: italian polenta(4 to 8 servings)
directions: *If not fresh, add 1/2 teaspoon to tomato sauce and heat.

title: delicious chocolate cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Fold in chocolate chips. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°.
While cake is hot, poke holes in top with end of a wooden spoon.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over cake.
When cake is cool, spread 1/2 jar ice cream fudge topping on top, then 1 small container Cool Whip on top of that.
Put crushed Heath candy bars on top of whipped cream.
Refrigerate. Enjoy!

title: paul lynde's stew
directions: Note:
No. 2 can contains 1 pound 2 ounces to 1 lb. 8 ounces or 2 1/2 cups.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until crisp-tender; thinly slice onions and peppers.
Mix sugar, oil, vinegar, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Add to vegetables in a large bowl.
Mix well. Chill 24 hours.

title: vermicelli salad
directions: Boil vermicelli in water with 2 tablespoons oil; drain and rinse.
Marinate overnight in salad oil, Accent and lemon juice. Next day, add all other ingredients.

title: purple hull pea salad
directions: Drain and rinse canned peas.
Chop vegetables.
Mix all ingredients well.
Serves 8.

title: prosciutto with mozzarella
directions: Wrap each Mozzarella ball in Prosciutto slice.
Brush with olive oil.
Bake at 425° for about 5 minutes or until slightly melted.

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Add vanilla to milk and alternate milk and flour and baking powder.
Add only enough flour to make dough stiff enough to roll out and cut into shapes. Decorate with sugar.
Bake at 400° for approximately 10 to 12 minutes.

title: dried beef and macaroni casserole
directions: Mix all together; let set for 2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered.
Remove cover the last 5 minutes.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: zucchini mericoli
directions: Heat cooking oil in 10-inch skillet; add sliced zucchini, carrot, onion, celery, green pepper, garlic salt, basil and pepper.
Toss to mix well.
Cook covered over medium-high heat for 4 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Combine taco sauce and mustard; stir into vegetable.
Add tomato wedges.
Cook uncovered 3 to 5 minutes or until heated through.
Season with salt; serve in the skillet or transfer to serving dish.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together potatoes, 1 cup sugar, egg, salt, 1/2 stick oleo, milk and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into Pyrex dish.
Mix brown sugar, 1/2 stick oleo, 1/2 teaspoon vanilla, flour and nuts. Spread over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield: 10 servings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into a greased baking dish.
Chill overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set.

title: swankbratten(german recipe)
directions: Rub both sides of meat with Lawry's salt and pepper. Cover meat with onions and green onions. Sprinkle with minced garlic. Add about 1/4 cup each of oil and water for juice.
Let set for at least 24 hours, covered, in refrigerator.
Grill or bake as desired.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix above ingredients adding poppy seed last. Bake in Bundt pan at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: corn bread muffins(low cholesterol)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Sift together the dry ingredients.
Add egg, milk and oil; stir quickly and lightly until mixed.
Do not beat.
Pour batter into 2 1/4-inch muffin tins or an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes, or until golden brown.
Yields 12 (2 1/4-inch) muffins.
Each serving contains 130 calories.

title: ma byrd's oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in saucepan and cook for 3 minutes.
Stir in peanut butter, oats and coconut.
Stir well and drop by spoonfuls on wax paper .

title: oysteretta snacks
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over crackers; blend until absorbed. Ready to serve.

title: canned milk chocolate fudge
directions: Stir over medium heat until mixture boils and is bubbly all over top.
Boil and stir over medium heat 5 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and chocolate pieces until melted. Stir in nuts.
Spread in buttered 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Press nuts on top.
Cool.
Cut into 30 pieces.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except milk and vanilla, then stir in well.
Cook in double boiler until thick and smooth.
Add flavoring.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: quick and easy carrot cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; beat 2 minutes at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Fold in carrots, raisins and pecans.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes and test.

title: big red cake
directions: Preheat your oven to 350°.
Blend your cake mix, Big Red soda pop, egg, egg whites and oil until well moistened.
Beat as directed on the cake mix package, then pour the batter into a greased and lightly floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Let cool and then frost with your favorite frosting.

title: barbecue
directions: Place hamburg and onion in frypan.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Simmer on low heat until ready to serve.

title: bachelor's soup
directions: Mix in saucepan and heat.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.

title: sour cream pound cake with nuts
directions: Add baking soda to sour cream and allow to sit.
Beat butter and sugar until smooth.
Add 1 cup sifted flour and 2 eggs until all flour and eggs are mixed then add vanilla and sour cream mixture.
Beat well between each addition.

title: mom's chili
directions: Brown
hamburger
and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and cook at least 30 minutes.

title: coffee toffee bars
directions: Cream
margarine and sugar, blend in vanilla and instant coffee.
Add
dry
ingredients,
stir
in
chocolate
chips and pecans.
Press
dough
into well greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
May be glazed if desired and cut into bars or squares.

title: a chunk of minestrone
directions: Brown onion with meat.
Add tomato juice, tomato sauce, carrots, celery stalks, basil, salt, pepper and water and cook, covered, for 45 minutes.
Add shredded cabbage and cook 30 minutes. Add rice and cook 10 minutes.
Add rosamarina macaroni and cook 15 minutes.
Lastly, add chili powder and red beans or kidney beans, with juice.
Simmer a few minutes and add more water, if needed.

title: butter rolls - 1930's
directions: Use enough biscuit dough for a 9 x 7-inch pan or iron skillet (easy butter; we had no icebox so butter must be soft).
I could take these to school in my lunch bucket and trade to other children for apples or bananas that we didn't have.
They loved them, too.

title: turnip casserole
directions: Pare and cut turnips into small slices.
Boil until tender, drain and mash hot turnips, adding butter, sugar, salt and pepper. Beat with electric mixer until blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat until fluffy.
Stir in bread crumbs and lemon juice. Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and refrigerate until baking time.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Combine cake mix and strawberry Jell-O.
Add water and Wesson oil (mix well), then add 2/3 box strawberries and eggs.
Bake at 350°.

title: beef brisket
directions: Trim all fat off brisket.
Cover 1 side with Kitchen Bouquet; rub in evenly.
Add small amount of Liquid Smoke; rub it in evenly. Sprinkle with celery salt, garlic salt, seasoned salt and pepper. Repeat on other side.
Seal tightly in aluminum foil and place in baking dish.
Cook at 225° for 6 to 8 hours.
Let cool.
Cut with electric knife across the grain.
Arrange in baking dish.
Add lightly, barbecue sauce, and bake on low heat 10 to 20 minutes until warm.
Serve hot.
Leftovers make great sandwiches.

title: dreamy vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine eggs, flour, sugar and salt in blender container
and mix well.
Heat milk to lukewarm in a large saucepan. Gradually add
about
cup warm milk to egg mixture.
Blend constantly. Stir
egg
mixture (with the 1 cup milk in it) to the
remaining milk on the stove,
then cook over low heat for 5
minutes.
Stir constantly
until thickened.
(It won't get very
thick; don't boil.) Remove from heat.
Stir in condensed milk,
half
and
half and
vanilla.
Stir
well.
Pour
into freezer and freeze.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: angel delite dessert
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with sugar.
Add milk.
Save some Cool Whip for topping; fold cream cheese mixture into rest of Cool Whip and cake pieces.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with reserved Cool Whip and sprinkles.
Festive and easy.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chicken dijon
directions: In skillet, brown chicken in oil; remove.
In same skillet, saute mushrooms until tender.
Stir in wine, gravy, milk and pepper.
Add chicken.
Simmer, uncovered, for 5 to 7 minutes, until chicken is cooked; turn and baste occasionally.
Stir mustard into sauce just before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pineapple dressing
directions: Mix ingredients together. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: pina colada popcorn
directions: Place popcorn in a large baking pan that has been buttered. Keep warm in 300° oven.
In small saucepan, melt margarine.
Remove from heat.
Stir in corn syrup, pudding mix and extract.
Pour this mixture over popcorn, tossing popcorn with spoon to coat. Bake popcorn, uncovered, for 15 minutes more in 300° oven.
Remove popcorn from oven and stir in dried pineapple and the coconut. Bake 5 minutes more.
Cool completely.
Serve immediately or store in tightly covered container.

title: green tomato pie(tastes like homemade apple pie)
directions: Roll out and line a 9-inch pie pan with 1/2 of the pastry. Roll out remainder for top.
Combine all ingredients (except the butter).
Pour the pie mixture into the pie shell.
Divide the tablespoon of butter into four smaller pieces and dot top of pie with pieces.
Top with rolled out pastry.
Crimp edges to seal and make 4-inch slits on top near center.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: surprise meat balls
directions: Combine ingredients, except olives.
Place 1 teaspoon meat mixture into palm of hand and flatten.
Place olive in center of meat.
Mold meat mixture around olive.
Continue until all meat mixture is gone.

title: fruit filled macaroni salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Combine eggs, syrup, sugar and lemon juice.
Cook and stir over medium to low heat until mixture thickens.
Add to cooked macaroni.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: old time beef stew
directions: Brown beef in a mixture of first 4 ingredients.
Boil water and add browned beef, vinegar, bay leaf, Worcestershire, and onion.
Cover and simmer 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add potatoes, carrots, and turnips.
Cook 20-25 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix
dry
ingredients
well and add oil, water and eggs (one at
a
time);
beat 1 minute.
Add 1/2 package of strawberries. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until done in oblong pan.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Serve with crackers or cocktail bread.

title: chicken 'n rice
directions: Make rice 'n sauce per package instructions.
Add can of soup (do not dilute).
Add contents of can of chicken.
Cook in one pot.
Add salad and cornbread.

title: baby wipes
directions: *Cut one roll in half.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Place ingredients in dish in order given.
Combine salad dressing and sugar and spread over salad as frosting and top with cheese.
Refrigerate 8 to 12 hours before serving.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Combine Ritz crackers and oleo.
Save 3/4 cup crumbs.
Place remaining crumb mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine milk and pudding and beat for 2 minutes.
Add ice cream to pudding.
Pour over crackers.
Spread Cool Whip over top.
Sprinkle crumbs over top.
Place in refrigerator or freeze.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Cut chicken up into bite-size pieces.
Place in hot skillet with 1 can Ro-Tel tomatoes and simmer until chicken is done. Place 1 tortilla shell in a plate and spoon chicken and tomatoes in each shell and roll up.
Place rolls in casserole dish.
Mix sour cream and cream of chicken soup together.
Pour over rolls to cover.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes uncovered.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in 1 1/2 quart casserole, except 2/3 c. onion.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until hot, stir, top with remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: vermicelli salad
directions: Boil vermicelli, rinse and cut up into bite sizes.
Mix olive oil, lemon juice and mayo.
Pour over cold vermicelli.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Chill before serving.
Tastes best when served 24 hours after making.

title: bear chops with rice
directions: Trim fat from the chops.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and paprika.
Place them in a pot, cover with water and simmer, covered, over low heat for 1/2 hour.
Spread 2 tablespoons rice over each chop, sprinkle each with garlic powder and top each with slices of tomato, onion and pepper.
Add water to reach the top of the meat.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1/2 hour or until well done.

title: southern cornbread dressing
directions: Beat eggs slightly; combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pack lightly into prepared bird just before roasting or bake separately.
Enough for 12 pound bird.

title: chicken delight
directions: Place chicken in buttered 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix together remaining ingredients. Pour over chicken.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender (do not turn).

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, Eagle Brand milk, lemon juice and pineapple in large bowl.
(Mix with spoon.)
Add coconut and pecans, crushed. Pour into 2 graham cracker crust.
Save some pecans to sprinkle on top.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: frank's chili
directions: In a large frying pan, add 1 tablespoon oil and chopped onion and garlic.
Saute on medium heat until lightly browned, then apply the ground steak.
Put flame up high and keep moving meat around until browned (10 to 15 minutes).
Turn off heat and set aside.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Mix together in a kettle.
Add tiny meatballs and cook until vegetables are done.

title: chocolate revel bars
directions: In a large mixer bowl, beat margarine on medium speed for 30 seconds.
Add half the flour, sugar, egg and 2 teaspoons of vanilla and baking soda.
Beat on low speed until thoroughly combined.
Beat in remaining flour.
Stir in oats.

title: columbian red snapper
directions: Sprinkle fish inside and out with salt and pepper.
Dredge outside lightly with flour.
Place fish in greased baking dish. Arrange lemon on top.
Heat margarine in skillet and cook onion, celery and green pepper until wilted.
Add lemon rind, tomatoes, parsley, rosemary, peppercorns and all remaining spices.
Salt to taste.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes. Pour sauce around and over fish.
Bake at about 150° for about 45 minutes.
Baste frequently.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: corn broccoli bake
directions: Saute butter and onion.
Mix all other ingredients.
Cook in microwave at High for 8 minutes. Stir.
Cook until mixture is set, 7 to 10 minutes.

title: carrot-mushroom stir-fry
directions: In large skillet, heat butter and oil until bubbly.
Add carrots, mushrooms and onions.
Cook and stir until vegetables are tender, about 8 minutes.
Stir in lemon juice, salt and pepper. Makes 4 servings.

title: edna's muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add eggs, milk and oil.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Mixture "keeps" in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks.

title: corn souffle
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well, and place in buttered casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Combine ingredients, shape into bite size balls.

title: fruit shake
directions: Combine in a blender or bowl and beat.
Try adding an egg for a thicker shake which is high in protein.

title: scarlet's potato patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into patties.
Dip in flour and brown slightly in butter in a frypan.
Cook about 5 minutes on each side.

title: edam cheese stuffed
directions: Let cheese stand at room temperature until soft.
Slice off 1-inch of top and scoop out the cheese, leaving wax shell intact. Grate cheese and let stand until very soft.
Add other ingredients; blend until creamy.
Refill shell; mound high. Store in fridge for one week.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix carrots, peppers and onions.
Set aside.
Mix other ingredients.
Add vegetables and simmer until blended.
Cook over medium heat until carrots are tender but not mushy.

title: eggplant and beef casserole
directions: Saute eggplant (peeled and diced) in oil with onion, green pepper and ground beef for 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper and sugar and cook 10 minutes longer.
Pour into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Cover with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: real potato rolls
directions: Start with about 3 or 4 cups of flour but the amount of flour is dictated by the amount of moisture in the potatoes. So accuracy is not a necessity but a little dough testing is.

title: bacon-cheese muffins
directions: In a large skillet cook bacon until crisp.
Drain; keep drippings.
Add enough oil to make 1/3 cup.
In small bowl mix drippings, egg and milk; set aside.
Crumble bacon and set aside. In large bowl combine flour and baking powder.
Make a well in center.
Add drippings and egg mixture all at once to flour mixture, stirring just until moist.
Batter should be lumpy.
Fold in bacon and cheese.
Spoon into greased muffin cups about 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° in preheated oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove and cool.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: apple breakfast sandwiches
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a small bowl; set aside. Separate biscuits and press each into a 3-inch circle.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet; sprinkle with cheese.
Top each with an apple ring.
Sprinkle with reserved sugar mixture and drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until crust is golden.
Serve immediately.
Yields 10 servings.

title: homemade salsa
directions: Bring to a boil, then simmer 5 to 10 minutes.

title: depression casserole
directions: In a saucepan, saute onion in oil until tender.
Stir in ketchup, water, vinegar, mustard and pepper.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Place franks in a 1-quart baking dish. Pour sauce over franks.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve over toasted bread or rice.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Spray crock-pot.
Cut up Velveetas in cubes and place in crock-pot.
Add other cheeses, soup and sausage.
Cook on low heat until melted, stirring occasionally.
Add relish or salsa as you wish.
If it gets too thick (and it will as it sits) add small amounts of milk and stir.
Eat with Doritos, taco chips or Fritos.

title: company chicken
directions: Mix rice, mushroom soup, celery soup and sherry together. Place in 10 or 12-inch casserole dish.
Place chicken on top of rice mixture and sprinkle with dry onion soup mix.
Cover securely with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer until smooth. Pour into pie shells.
Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: party potatoes
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add cheese and cook, stirring until melted. Add sour cream, scallions, salt and pepper. Turn into a 2-quart casserole. Scoop potatoes from skins and stir into cheese mix.
Top with crumbled bacon.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes and drain.
Combine eggs, soup, cheese and mayonnaise.
Fold into broccoli and pour into a greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch chips over double boiler on low heat.
Mix noodles and peanuts in butterscotch.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: copper penny salad
directions: Clean and slice carrots. Cook until just tender. Blend together all other ingredients. After carrots have cooled, pour the well-blended mixture over carrots. Let set in refrigerator 24 hours before serving.

title: sweet rolls
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with package of crescent rolls.
Mix egg, cream cheese and sugar.
Spread this mixture over rolls.
Cover with second can of crescent rolls.
Bake until brown at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix eggs, can of pumpkin, brown sugar, salt and pie spice. After that, mix Milnot with it.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked crust. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan or 12-cup Bundt pan.
Beat sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla in a large mixer bowl on low, scraping bowl constantly, for 30 seconds.
Beat on high, scraping bowl constantly for 5 minutes.
Beat in flour, baking powder and salt alternately with milk on low speed.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 70 to 80 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into middle comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes; remove from pan.

title: lemon crumb bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 dish.
Beat cake mix, margarine and 1 egg until crumbly.
Stir in crackers and press into bottom of 13 x 9 (reserving 2 cups crumb mix).
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: raspberry pie
directions: Cook water, sugar and cornstarch until thick.
Add Jell-O and mix well.
Pour over berries arranged in baked shell; chill. Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: fiesta turkey pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cook turkey on medium heat until brown; stir in salsa.
Press crescent roll dough in 9-inch pie plate to form crust.
Spread turkey mixture evenly over crust; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 20 minutes or until crust is browned.

title: mary's mother's favorite chocolate cake
directions: *I substitute 1 1/2 cups of whole wheat pastry flour.

title: cornstarch pudding
directions: Mix together cornstarch, sugar and a little water to make a liquid mixture; set aside. Bring to a boil the cream and milk. On low heat add cornstarch mixture slowly, stirring constantly. After it thickens, remove from heat and add vanilla. Pour in a bowl and top pudding by sprinkling some sugar and cinnamon to make suitable for your taste and a drop of butter.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, ginger, cloves, brown sugar and salt.
Add shortening, using hands to blend.

title: crostini toasts
directions: Diagonally slice bread 1/4 inch thick.
Arrange in single layer on baking sheet.
Bake for about 8 to 10 minutes, or until crisp and lightly browned.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix milk, lemon juice and Cool Whip in large bowl until smooth.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill in refrigerator for 1 hour before serving.

title: cheese cake ice cream
directions: Mix everything together.
Freeze in an electric ice cream maker.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: chicken in a biscuit
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Combine flour, gravy mix, and whipping cream.
Mix well. Turn out onto a lightly floured surface and gently knead 5 or 6 times. Roll out to a thickness of about 1/2 inch and cut with a 2-inch biscuit cutter. Dip in melted butter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 425 degrees for 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: a b c chip dip
directions: Combine and mix lightly. Serve with crackers. Good with shredded wheat crackers.

title: millionaire pound cake
directions: Blend the butter and sugar together.
Then add 2 of your 4 cups of flour, then add milk and the other 2 cups of flour.
Blend together then add eggs, 1 at a time.
Then add vanilla and lemon flavor.
Mix well.
Grease and flour a Bundt cake pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes, until brown and ready.

title: broccoli salad no.1
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Toss with dressing.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream first 2 ingredients.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Add last 2 ingredients.
Bake in loaf pan about 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken breasts in sour cream
directions: Line shallow baking dish with layers of dried beef.
Wrap each chicken breast with 1/2 slice of bacon then place on top of beef. Combine sour cream and mushroom soup.
Then pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice cooked with chicken broth, mushrooms and pimento.
Can be frozen uncooked then baked just before the meal.
Can also be cooked in a crock pot.

title: frozen vegetable casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add remaining ingredients; salt and pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for about 50 minutes.
Remove and cover with noodles. Return to oven for about 10 minutes.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Cut shortening into flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt with pastry blender until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Stir in buttermilk until dough leaves side of bowl.
(If buttermilk is thick, it may be necessary to add slightly more than 3/4 cup.) Turn dough onto lightly floured surface; knead lightly 10 times.
Roll or pat 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with floured 2 1/2-inch round cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet about 1 inch apart for crusty sides, touching for soft sides.
Bake until golden brown, 10 to 12 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Makes 1 dozen biscuits (155 calories per biscuit).

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Line pan with rolls.
Brown sausage and drain.
Add eggs, green pepper, green onions, cheese, salt and pepper to sausage. Pour over rolls.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill!

title: creamy fruit dip
directions: Use with fresh fruit.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place melted butter in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Next, mix all other ingredients together thoroughly except corn flakes and place in 9 x 13 pan.
Then sprinkle crushed corn flakes on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In large saucepan, brown hamburger in oil.
Add onions.
When browned, put in large pot.
Add other ingredients.
Cook on medium heat for 3 hours.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes in prepared 450° oven. Drain.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift together
and
set aside sugar and flour.
Combine in saucepan
margarine,
shortening
or
oil, cocoa and water. Bring to boil and remove from heat.
Add to 1st mixture.
Then add the following:
buttermilk,
eggs, soda and vanilla.
Mix well and bake 20 minutes at 400° in sheet pan.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: *Select 1 cup each of a selection of cauliflower, sliced carrots, cherry tomatoes, zucchini, sliced mushrooms, green pepper strips or green beans

title: salad
directions: Dissolve in 1 cup boiling water.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: best ever pot roast
directions: Sprinkle
flour
on
roast and brown both sides in oil; pour soup mix and can of soup over roast.
Add 1 can of water. Cover and bake for 3 hours at 350°.

title: colossal cookies
directions: Heat oven to
In
a 8 quart pan, beat butter and sugars.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Stir
in
oats,
flour,
chocolate chips and soda.
Mix well.
Drop
batter on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with fork.
Bake 10
to	12 minutes.
Cool 1 minute.
Move to rack. (Dough may be frozen.)

title: heath bar cake
directions: Mix and bake cake as directed.
When cake comes out of oven, while warm, punch holes in cake (I use the end of a wooden spoon), about 1 1/2-inches apart.
Pour caramel topping over cake, making sure to fill holes.
Pour canned Eagle Brand sweetened milk all over top of cake.
Let this cool COMPLETELY.
When cake is completely cooled, spread Cool Whip on evenly just as you would frosting.
Top this with crushed Heath bars.
Refrigerate. Yuuuuuuuuuuuuum Good.

title: potato-broccoli cheese soup
directions: Melt the margarine; add onions and saute for 5 minutes.
Add potatoes, water and bouillon cubes.
Cover and cook until tender. Remove 1 or 2 cups potatoes and set aside.
Blend remaining potato mixture in blender until smooth.
Return all to saucepan.
Mix in reserved potatoes and broccoli.
Simmer a few minutes until the broccoli is cooked the way you like it.
Add cheese and heat through to melt.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain and set aside.
Beat eggs slightly with milk.
Add bread cubes, grated cheese and sausage.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
This is to be prepared the night before and refrigerated until ready to bake.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Cut beef across the grain into thin slices.
Combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger.
Toss with meat and set aside.
Heat oil in large skillet or wok.
Add beef and stir-fry until browned.
If not tender, simmer 30 to 40 minutes over low heat.
Turn up heat and add vegetables.
Toss until tender-crisp (about 10 minutes). Mix cornstarch with water; add to pan and cook until thickened. Add tomatoes and heat through.
Serves 4.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream shortening, 2 cups sugar and lemon rind.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add sifted flour, salt and baking powder with milk to creamed mixture, beating well. Bake in 2 small 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pans at 350° for 40 minutes or until tests done with a toothpick.
Remove from pan.
Combine 1 cup sugar with juice from the two lemons and spread on loaves while still hot.
Let stand a day or two before serving.
They also freeze well.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Fry bacon and onion together. Place in bowl and mix in the rest of the ingredients. Bake in 9 x 9 pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: seven layer bars
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, melt butter or oleo.
Sprinkle over the next 4 ingredients.
Drizzle over Eagle Brand milk; sprinkle chopped nuts over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.
Do not mix!

title: easy apple cobbler
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; mix gently.
Spoon into a lightly greased 9-inch square baking pan; dot with butter.
Set aside. Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Spoon over apple mixture in 9 equal portions (batter will spread during baking). Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: Peel onion.
Cut in half lengthwise, then crosswise into thin slices.
In 3-quart saucepan, melt butter.
Add onion and garlic. Cook over medium heat for about 20 minutes or until onion is soft and transparent, stirring occasionally.
Stir in flour.
Add water, wine, beef and chicken bouillon granules and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: old settler's baked beans
directions: Cook hamburger meat and drain.
Cook and drain bacon. Crumble.
Add all ingredients; mix.
Bake in crock-pot for about 5 hours or in oven at 225°.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix water and sugar; bring to a boil.
Mix cornstarch with water and add to sugar water; cook until thickened.
Dissolve Jell-O in the mixture and cool.
Add fresh sliced peaches.
Cool until partially set.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill. Add Cool Whip and serve.

title: fabulous fruitcake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch Bundt pan. Sift flour and baking soda.
Set aside.
Mix eggs, mincemeat, milk, fruit and nuts.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake 50 minutes or 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: oreo cookie ice cream pie
directions: Mix crushed cookies with melted butter; press into the bottom of a 12-inch pie taker.
Spread ice cream over top of cookies. Pour fudge topping in even layer over ice cream.
Spread whipped topping over fudge.
Garnish with chocolate curls or Oreo cookie mini's, if desired.
Put in freezer for 2 hours before serving.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Measure dry ingredients into bowl and mix well.
Stir in oil, egg and vanilla.
Mixture may seem almost dry.
Form into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: favorite pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and corn syrup together.
Add pecans, salt and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Complete baking 20 to 25 minutes. Brush with butter, if desired.
Can be served with whipped cream.

title: old fashioned custard pie
directions: Beat together until thoroughly mixed.
Bake for 15 minutes at 450°, then bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Beat the cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in sour cream, lemon juice, salad dressing mix and shrimp.
Chill for at least 1 hour before serving.
This is even better if you make it the day before.
Doubles easily.

title: tandy cake
directions: Melt butter in scalded milk; set aside.
Mix eggs, vanilla, salt, sugar, flour and baking powder in bowl.
Add milk mixture. Use electric beater.
Pour in greased jelly roll pan (I put foil in bottom of pan to make cutting easier).
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
While hot, spread peanut butter over cake.
Cool. Melt chocolate and stir in one spoon of peanut butter as melting. Ice over cake.
Cool before cutting.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease baking dish with butter.
Mix broth and milk.
Beat eggs; add to milk and broth.
Chop pepper and celery.
Toast buttered bread; cut into cubes.
Mix all ingredients together, except bread cubes; place it on top.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: sticky caramel rolls
directions: Microwave brown sugar, cinnamon and butter in pie plate for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir.
Cut 1 can of biscuits in fourths and place in pie plate.
Stir.
Microwave 3 1/2 minutes.

title: southwestern spice rub
directions: Cook cumin and coriander seed in a small skillet over low heat, stirring constantly, 3 minutes.
Combine seeds, chiles and remaining ingredients in an electric blender; process until mixture resembles coarse powder.
Store in airtight container.

title: tastes like reeses
directions: Mix butters, sugar and graham cracker crumbs.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Melt chips and spread over first layer. Refrigerate until set.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash with onion until done (add 1 cup green pepper for extra flavor).
Drain.
Put 1 stick margarine in squash and mash like potatoes.
Add sour cream and soup; mix well.
Add stuffing mix or crumbled croutons.
Mix.
Add grated cheese.

title: flax seed muffins
directions: Mix together flour, flax, oat bran, brown sugar, baking soda, powder, salt and cinnamon.

title: german sweet chocolate cherry cake
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Add cake mix.
Beat until well mixed.
Add flavoring and cherry pie filling.
Mix.
Bake in 10 x 15-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes until done.

title: mocha chocolate frosting
directions: Combine cocoa and coffee. Add margarine and vanilla; mix. Add powdered sugar and mix thoroughly.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Beat
eggs
well
and
add salt.
Put lard in hot stock. Add alternately
stock	and flour to egg mixture until a stiff dough is formed.	Roll thin and let stand in cool room on cloth for
1 hour.
Drop in boiling stock, stirring often.
After all is in pot, cover, and let simmer over low flame for 30 minutes. (This is an old recipe.)

title: salsa
directions: Chop all ingredients and combine in a large pot.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 1 hour, put into hot jars and seal.

title: vegetable lasagna with cheese sauce
directions: Heat the oil in skillet. Add the onion and garlic and saute for about 1 minute. Add all the vegetables up to and including the red pepper and saute, stirring occasionally, for about 5 minutes. Add the chopped tomatoes, mixed herbs, tomato paste and water. Season and then simmer for about 15 minutes. Add the broccoli and cook for 15 minutes or until all the vegetables are tender. Meanwhile warm up the cheese sauce, recipe follows. To assemble, spoon a third of the vegetables over the bottom of a 9 x 6 x 3 inch oven proof dish. Cover with 4 overlapping sheets of lasagna. Then add a third of the cheese sauce. Repeat the layering twice, finishing with a layer of cheese sauce. Sprinkle the grated cheese on top of the final layer of cheese sauce. Transfer to the preheated
oven and bake for 40 minutes.

title: quick punch
directions: Pour fruit punch into punch bowl.
Add ginger ale.
Add sherbet.
Ladle punch over sherbet until sherbet melts over punch.

title: easy brownies
directions: Mix brownies according to directions. Pour 1/2 of mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Place candy bars on top of mix. Pour the other 1/2 of brownie mix on top of candy, covering completely. Bake according to directions on pkg. of brownie mix.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer.
Pour into buttered dish.

title: cordial fudge balls
directions: Mix cookie crumbs and liqueur in bowl.
Melt chocolate and butter in saucepan over low heat.
Remove.
Gradually stir chocolate mixture and corn syrup into crumb mixture.
Add powdered sugar and 1/2 cup of pecans.
Stir dough well until stiff.
Shape into small balls.
Roll balls in remaining pecans.
To maintain optimum freshness, store in freezer before giving or serving.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix salad dressing, sour cream, chili sauce, sugar, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt until smooth.
Stir in Blue cheese.
Add small amount of water or milk, if necessary, for desired consistency.
Refrigerate in tightly covered container no longer than 3 weeks.
Makes about 4 1/2 cups dressing.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt in mixing bowl.
Bring water, cocoa and oleo to boil in saucepan and pour over flour and sugar mixture.
Combine eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla and add to mixture.
Pour batter in greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° until done.

title: black java beef stew
directions: In heavy pan brown meat; remove meat and cook onion in hot oil. Combine flour, salt and pepper; toss with meat and return to pan. Cook and stir to brown flour.
Add remaining ingredients, cover and simmer for 2 hours.
Lift out cooked meat and onions with slotted spoon.
Boil sauce to thicken.
Adjust seasoning if necessary. Return meat and onion and heat.
Serve with sliced sauteed mushrooms if desired.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and Cool Whip. Frost cake between layers, top and sides. Drizzle blueberry pie filling on top.

title: tomato catsup or chili sauce
directions: Peel tomatoes and onions.
Remove seed and stems from peppers and grind or chop fine.
Cook slowly until soft, 30 minutes.
Add pepper, salt, vinegar, sugar and nutmeg.
Boil for 2 hours or until thick.
Then add cornstarch, dissolved in a portion of vinegar.
Tie mixed spices loosely in cheesecloth, removing all but 1 red pepper.
Boil 1/2 hour longer and bottle or put in jars and seal.
For catsup, force this mixture through a fine sieve.

title: e. miller's mincemeat pie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Heat just until boiling over medium-high heat.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer until raisins are soft (15 to 20 minutes).
Allow to cool.
Divide the resulting 18 pounds into 1 1/2 pound portions and freeze.
Makes 12 (9-inch) pies.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dump cherry pie filling into a 9x13-inch baking dish, spreading to cover bottom of dish.
Next, dump pineapple on top of the cherries, spreading to cover the cherries. Cover this with cake mix.
Melt margarine and pour over cake mix. Sprinkle with pecans and coconut.
Bake for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: tasty brisket
directions: Marinate brisket in buttermilk overnight.
Place brisket in large cooking bag.
Add Italian dressing.
Place in pan; cut slits in bag.
Set in oven on low (225°) and cook 7 to 8 hours.
Let cool; slice and enjoy.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Pour 1/2 batter into hot greased skillet or pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 of cheese on batter.
Add remaining batter and sprinkle the rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: ladyfingers
directions: Break ladyfingers or pound cake into small pieces; cover with Jell-O.
When Jell-O sets, add fruit cocktail.
Cover with custard powder.
Top with cream.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: pepperoni pizza dip
directions: In small mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, sour cream, oregano or basil and garlic powder.
Spread evenly on a 9 or 10-inch quiche pan or pie plate.
Spread sauce over top.
Sprinkle with pepperoni, onion and green pepper.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Top with Mozzarella cheese; bake 5 minutes longer or until cheese is melted and mixture is heated through.
Serve with crackers.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix together.
Pat mixture into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: de oreo (cookie press) cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg and mix well.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder; add slowly to butter, sugar and egg mixture, mixing well.
Add almond flavoring and mix well.
Add more flour if dough is too soft.
Shape dough with cookie press. Decorate cookies with red and green cherries.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: tomato soup
directions: Wash and stem tomatoes.
Cook tomatoes with parsley, onions and bay leaves until tender.
Sieve.
Mix in bowl the flour, salt, sugar and pepper.
Gradually add (by cupfuls, using about 4 cups juice) the tomato juice and stir until thin.

title: crab dip
directions: Blend together cream cheese (softened), mayonnaise, mustard, onion and seasoned salt.
Fold in parsley, garlic powder and crabmeat.
Serve hot or cold with crackers or vegetables.

title: swedish farmer cookies
directions: Cream together oleo, Karo syrup and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Make into 2 rolls.
Place in refrigerator overnight at least.
Slice thin.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: graham cracker crust cherry pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and powdered sugar. Set aside. Combine Dream Whip, milk and vanilla. Whip until fluffy. (You can substitute Cool Whip if you wish.)
Fold in cream cheese mixture and mix well. Spread mixture in graham cracker crust. Add cherry pie filling on top of the cream cheese mixture. Chill about 2 hours to set.

title: spiny lobster tails
directions: Thaw frozen lobster tails.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Remove swimmercrettes and sharp edges.
Cut 6 pieces of heavy-duty aluminum foil, 12 x 12-inches each.
Place each lobster tail on foil.
Combine butter, lemon juice and salt.
Baste lobster meat with sauce.
Bring the foil up over the lobster and close all edges with tight double folds.
Make 6 packages.
Place packages on a grill, shell side down, about 5 inches from hot coals.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Remove lobster tails from the foil.
Place lobster tails on grill, flesh side down and cook for 2 to 3 minutes longer or until lightly browned.
Serve with melted butter.
Serves 6.

title: mixed bean casserole
directions: Cut up bacon and cook until brown; add green pepper and onions, using some of the onion tops.
Cook until done.
Drain all beans, except baked beans.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: baked chile rellenos
directions: Separate eggs. Beat whites until stiff. Mix flour, salt, pepper and egg yolks. Fold in whites and pour half into greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Remove seeds from chilies and spread chilies over batter. Cover with cheese slices. Pour rest of batter over cheese. Bake for 25 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: meat loaf(great grandmother conard)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: potato salad
directions: Stir all together.
This makes about a gallon of potato salad.

title: hog spuds
directions: Cut potatoes into 4 pieces each.
Add 1 package link sausage in casserole dish.
Cover with the tomato soup from can.
Pepper to taste.
Bake in 375° oven, covered, until potatoes are tender. Approximately 30 minutes.
Serve.
Kids love this dish.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and heat for serving.

title: manicotti(batter)
directions: Beat eggs, add flour salt and water until very smooth.
Grease a 6-inch frying pan and add 2 tablespoons batter.
Move pan until batter covers bottom; pick-up edge with fork when it starts to dry ( a few seconds).
Flip over to other side a few seconds.
Take out and continue using up batter.

title: brownie pudding cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and 2 tablespoons cocoa. Add milk, oil and vanilla in a baking dish.
Mix brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Add about 1/2 to 3/4 cup chopped pecans to batter. Sprinkle over batter and pour hot water over entire mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until it tests done. Serve warm.
Makes a pudding on the bottom.

title: coke congealed salad
directions: Bring cherries and jello to a boil.
Add Cokes and cream cheese.
Let stand until room temperature.
Add pineapple and pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken with garlic and broccoli
directions: In a large frying pan, cook (covered) garlic and broccoli in oil over medium-low heat (approximately 6 minutes).
Add chicken, salt and pepper.
Cook an additional 6 minutes (approximately), stirring often.
Serves 2.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Roll out crescent rolls in 2 pans and bake until lightly brown.
Let crust cool.
Mix together sour cream, cream cheese, mayo and dressing.
Spread mixture over cooled crust.
Cut up vegetables real small or shred.
Sprinkle all vegetables and cheese over crust and sour cream mixture.
Refrigerate until ready to eat.
Cut in slices.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in bananas and mix well.
Stir in nuts. Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: oatmeal-raisin bread
directions: Start heating oven at 350°.
Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add oats and raisins. With electric mixer at medium speed or "cream" (or with spoon), thoroughly mix shortening with sugar, then with egg, until very light and fluffy (about 4 minutes) altogether.
Add buttermilk, then add this mixture in thirds to flour mixture, stirring after each addition until blended.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna by package directions.
Chop tomatoes in blender. Combine tomatoes with onion, carrots and seasonings in large pan. Simmer for 20 minutes.
Spread 3/4 cup of this mixture in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish and layer with a third of the lasagna.
Place a third of spinach, zucchini, parsley, mushrooms and the 3 cheeses. Cover with a third of tomato mixture.
Alternate layers again. Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: linguica puffs
directions: Remove casing from linguica.
Cook in large skillet, breaking up with fork.
Drain off fat.
Put into large bowl and cool completely.
Mix in rest of ingredients with fork until blended. Roll into 1-inch balls and place on large cookie sheet 2-inches apart.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, until puffed and lightly browned.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Grate cabbage, carrot and pepper.
Add salt.
Let stand 1 hour, covered.
Squeeze out juice.
Mix spices, water, sugar and vinegar.
Boil 1 minute.
Let cool.
Mix cabbage and sauce together.
Put in containers and freeze.

title: yule kaka
directions: Combine milk, shortening, sugar and spices.
Cool to lukewarm. Add yeast, softened, in warm water.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add flour; beat well.
Add fruits and remaining flour.
Let rise until double in bulk. Punch down and knead lightly.
Form into 3 loaves. Grease pans.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
While warm, brush with melted butter.

title: caleb corn muffins
directions: Mix all together well and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake pie shell 8 minutes; remove from oven.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Cut 6 slices cheese into pieces; set aside.
In large skillet, brown beef; drain fat.
Add tomato sauce, green pepper, onion and bouillon; cook and stir until bouillon dissolves.
Remove from heat; stir in eggs, flour and cheese pieces.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until hot.
Arrange cheese slices on top.
Return to oven 3 to 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Garnish with tomato and lettuce.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Reserve one cup of the pecans for rolling the ball.
Drain pineapple; combine with all other ingredients.
Shape into ball. Roll in remaining cup of nuts.
Chill in refrigerator in waxed paper or plastic bag until ready to use.
Serve with favorite crackers or tidbits.

title: italian chicken
directions: Put chicken into a Dutch oven, then place potatoes and carrots on top of chicken. Pour dressing, water and soy sauce over top. Bake at 250° all day, or can use electric skillet.

title: paul lynde stew
directions: Mix together in roaster.
Stir gently.
Cover.
Bake at 225° to 250° for 6 hours.

title: holiday dip
directions: Beat cottage cheese and milk in a small mixing bowl until creamy.
Stir in all remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least one hour.

title: carol's macaroni casserole
directions: Throw together; mix well. Dump in buttered dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: maui shrimp dip
directions: *You may use 2 cans of shrimp.

title: cup of cheer
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Strain in large bowl.
Add the grapefruit juice, orange juice and apple cider; mix and reheat to serve.

title: better'n snuff cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on box.
While cake is cooking, cook pineapple and sugar for 5 minutes in saucepan on top of stove.
When cake is done, prick with fork and pour pineapple and sugar over cake.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower into pieces.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over all.
Mix thoroughly and chill.

title: pudding cake
directions: Bake cake by directions on box.
Cook in 9-inch round pans. When cake is done and cool, cut cake so you will have 4 layers. Mix pudding and pineapple with mixer, then add Cool Whip.
Layer cake and put mixture between each layer.
Ice cake with remaining mix.
Keep in cool place.

title: sandy-ridge blackberry cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in microwave.
Mix with blackberries.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch cobbler pan.

title: clam puffs
directions: Soften cream cheese and blend in all other ingredients. Spread on toast rounds and place under a preheated broiler for about 5 minutes until top bubbles.
Serve immediately.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly, then stir in raisins.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: fudge topping
directions: Melt together margarine and cocoa.
Add sugar, 1/2 cup at a time, stirring well.
On low heat, add milk.
Slowly bring to a boil.
Boil 4 to 5 minutes, stirring often.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Makes about 1 quart (keep refrigerated).
Can eat hot or cold.

title: raisin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: brunch egg casserole
directions: Place croutons and cheese in the bottom of a greased 10 X 6 X 1 3/4 inch baking dish.
Combine eggs, milk and seasonings.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle with bacon.
Bake at 325 for 1 hour or until set.
Serve immediately.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: scalloped potatoes with pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on one side only in hot oil in skillet. Remove chops as they brown; reserve drippings.

title: leva's salsa
directions: Chop in food processor the tomatoes, peppers, onion, olives, cilantro and jalapeno peppers.
Add garlic powder and stir.
Then add olive oil and vinegar.
Stir and chill.
Serve with favorite chips.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into strips 2 inches long.
Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Heat oil in frypan over medium heat.
Add meat and brown. Mix salt, pepper, ginger and cornstarch.
Stir this into bouillon and soy sauce.
Combine this with the meat.
Bring to a boil.
Add onion and pepper.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until mixture is thickened.
Serve over rice.

title: broccoli quiche(quick)
directions: Layer cooked broccoli, onion, then cheese in a casserole dish. Blend eggs, milk and Bisquick in blender.
Pour over layered mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash in salted water until tender.
Beat with mixer. Soak bread in milk and mix with squash. Saute onion and bell pepper in oil.
Beat eggs, add to squash gradually.
Add sauteed onion and butter and grated cheese.
Put in casserole dish and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes. Makes 4-6 servings.

title: tang salad
directions: Drain peaches and pineapple.
Add dry mix and Tang.
Stir in strawberries.
Chill for few hours.
Add bananas just before serving.
Quick, easy and delicious.

title: chocolate eclairs
directions: In medium bowl mix 3 cups milk and pudding mix.
Blend in whipping cream.
Put a layer of whole graham crackers in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Take 1/2 pudding mixture and spread over graham crackers.
Repeat.
Finish topping pudding with graham crackers.

title: winter vegetable salad
directions: Chop all vegetables into bite size pieces and measure a cup of each.
Mix mayonnaise, yogurt and Equal together.
Spread over vegetables and serve when chilled.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix
well
and
bake
in greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour. While hot, brush top with butter.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Melt chips in milk.
Add other ingredients.
Stir.
Slice apples for dipping and serve.

title: warm potato salad(light and easy)
directions: Place potatoes in saucepan.
Add water to cover.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.
Drain.
Place potatoes and onion in a bowl. Combine vinegar and remaining ingredients; stir well.
Add to potato mixture.
Toss gently to coat.
Yields 4 servings.

title: pot roast in foil
directions: Put roast and soups in aluminum foil pan. Cover
tightly with aluminum foil. Bake at 325° in oven for 4 hours. Do not peek! Makes its own gravy.

title: dumplings
directions: Beat egg; add salt (to taste), milk, sprinkle of nutmeg and baking powder.
Add enough flour to make it stiff.
Do not beat; stir just enough to mix well.
Drop into soup for the last 20 to 30 minutes.
Cover and let simmer.

title: cheese jalapeno cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease well-seasoned 10-inch cast iron skillet or 9 x 11-inch baking pan; set aside.
In a large bowl mix cornmeal, baking soda and salt.
In a medium sized bowl, lightly beat eggs; stir in corn, buttermilk and shortening until well mixed.
Pour liquid mixture into dry ingredients; stir well.
Pour half the batter into prepared skillet; sprinkle with remaining cheese and half the peppers.
Add remaining batter; evenly sprinkle with remaining cheese and peppers.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown and surface springs back when lightly touched.
Cut into 16 wedges or squares.

title: corn casserole
directions: Do not drain corn.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 35-40 minutes.

title: jam and cheese loaf
directions: In a mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in hot water.
Stir in Bisquick mix, egg and 1 tablespoon of sugar.
Mix well.
Turn out on a surface dusted with additional Bisquick mix.
Knead gently about 20 strokes.

title: mark's fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and salt together until well mixed. Stir milk into dry ingredients in heavy pan. Cook at medium high heat until it comes to rolling boil. Reduce heat to medium. Boil gently, stirring occasionally just to keep from sticking.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze spinach and spin until dry.
Stir all together. Cover; refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: dip for raw vegetables
directions: Blend all ingredients together, except chili sauce.
Remove from blender and add chili sauce.
Mix well.

title: baked franks and limas
directions: Cook limas according to package directions in unsalted water; drain.
In Dutch oven, cook onion and celery in shortening until tender, but not brown.
Blend in soup.
Reserving 1 cup tomato liquid, add remaining tomatoes with liquid to soup mixture.
Blend flour with the 1 cup of reserved tomato liquid; add to mixture. Cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Thinly slice franks.
Divide franks and lima beans evenly between two 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dishes.
Pour half of the tomato mixture over each. Mix.
Combine bread crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle atop each.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Makes 25 (about 1-cup) servings.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers thin.
Add onions and pepper (cut in thin strips).
Add salt and cover with cracked ice.
Mix thoroughly. Let stand 3 hours.
Drain.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over cucumber mixture.
Heat to boiling; place in hot sterilized jars. Makes 8 pints.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Pare eggplant, cut into slices 1/4-inch thick.
Pour boiling water over slices and soak for 5 minutes.
Dry slices and saute in hot oil until golden brown on both sides. Layer in 2-quart casserole a few eggplant slices.
Sprinkle some Parmesan over slices.
Place a few Mozzarella slices next and cover with tomato sauce.
Repeat layers until eggplant is used up, topping last layer of sauce with several slices of Mozzarella. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes six servings.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and walnuts.
In separate bowl, melt shortening.
Add to it, brown sugar, water, eggs and vanilla and mix.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Add chocolate chips and mix.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: nacho dip
directions: Layer in microwave pan the cream cheese followed by chili. Top with cheese. Microwave until cheese is melted. Serve with nacho chips.

title: pecan tea tarts
directions: Mix like pie crust and roll into balls.
Press into small muffin tins.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients thoroughly and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.
Just before serving, add bananas and chopped nuts.

title: chicken broccoli lasagna
directions: Heat soup and frozen chopped broccoli in 2-quart saucepan until broccoli is thawed.
Heat 2 tablespoons olive oil over medium heat in 10-inch skillet until hot.
Cook carrots, onion and garlic until lightly browned.
Reduce heat to low.
Stir in 1/4 cup water.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until vegetables are very tender.

title: caesar salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour over salad of fresh lettuce, mushrooms, onions and croutons.
Serve cold.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in sugar, salt, eggs, shortening and 2 cups flour; beat until smooth.
Mix in remaining flour until smooth.
Scrape dough from sides of bowl; cover and let rise until double, about 1 1/2 hours.
Divide dough in half; roll each half into 12-inch circle.
Spread with melted butter; cut into 16 wedges (I like to do this with a pizza cutter).
Roll up each wedge, beginning at rounded edge.
Place rolls with point under on a greased baking sheet.
Cover and let rise until double, about 1 hour.
Heat oven to 400°.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes, until golden brown.
Brush rolls with melted butter.

title: baked honey ham
directions: Wash ham and place fat side up in roaster.
Stick in the cloves.
Pour the vinegar and peach juice over the ham.
(Reserve peaches for garnish.)
Rub with honey, then brown sugar.
Bake at 300°, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Cover and bake 2 hours.
Baste the ham every 30 minutes.
Add the diced fruits and bake 1 hour or until ham is tender.
Serve sliced ham with fruit sauce from the roaster.
Garnish with peaches.
Serves 20.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Cream together.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until center of pie is firm.

title: lemon chicken
directions: In a skillet, saute chicken in margarine and oil.
When brown, remove chicken and discard margarine and oil.
Add sherry, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Simmer 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and slowly add half and half.
Heat until sauce begins to bubble.
Add chicken and simmer 20 minutes until tender. Transfer to a serving dish and pour over top.
Garnish with lemon slices and parsley.

title: american chop suey
directions: Cook meats, onion and pepper.
Drain grease.
Add soups and noodles.
Mix and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Return
to oven, uncovered, until cheese melts.

title: apple custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Make pie crust and bake for 15 minutes. In mixing bowl blend sour cream, milk, juice, egg, vanilla and cinnamon.
Pour into shell.
Bake for 30 minutes or until set. Cool.
Put apple pie filling on top.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: yogurt popsicles
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour mixture into 3-ounce paper cups with plastic spoon inserted.
Freeze.

title: caramel layer chocolate squares
directions: Melt caramels in 1/3 cup evaporated milk and set aside. Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine butter, cake mix, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and pecans.
Press half of this into the cake pan and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Remove from oven. Sprinkle the chocolate chips over this and then spread the caramel over the chips. Cover with the remaining cake mix batter.
You may have to take little bits between your fingers and drop them onto the caramel; a little slow but well worth it. Return to oven and bake for 18 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: curry dip for vegetables
directions: Combine and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: apple crisp
directions: Grease square pan.
Peel and slice apples.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and egg.
Pour over apples.
Pour butter over and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: refreshing jello
directions: Boil nectar.
Add jello; stir until dissolved.
Pour half the mixture into mold; set.
Spoon on sour cream.
Add evaporated milk to remaining jello mixture; pour onto sour cream.
Set and enjoy.

title: mosaic cloud cake
directions: Separately dissolve 3 different flavors of Jell-O each in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Pour each in individual 8-inch square pans.
Chill until firm.
Cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Toss together. Dissolve plain gelatin in 1 1/4 cups boiling water.
Chill until syrupy.
Meanwhile, combine graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and butter.
Press mixture on bottom and sides of spring-form pan. Chill.
Whip heavy cream with 1/4 cup sugar until of mounding consistency.
Fold in gelatin mixture.
Fold in Jell-O cubes. Pour into pan.
Chill 4 hours or overnight.

title: quiche for brunch
directions: Place buttered bread in the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with bacon, mushrooms and onions.
Beat together milk and eggs; pour over bread.
Cover with grated cheese.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set like custard.

title: russian tea ball
directions: Cream the butter and eggs.
Add rest of the ingredients.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 325°, after forming small ball.
When baked, roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter; toss with dressing.
Mix 1/2 dressing with squash, cream soup and sour cream.

title: 2-step chicken broccoli divan(serves 4)
directions: In 9-inch pie plate or shallow casserole, arrange broccoli; top with chicken.
Combine soup and milk; pour over chicken and sprinkle with cheese.
Combine butter and bread crumbs; sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until hot or cover with waxed paper.
Microwave on High 6 minutes or until hot, rotating dish halfway through heating.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Make corn bread the day before.
Put all your giblets in to boil with green onions.
While boiling and it gets tender, put bread in a pan you can bake in.
Pour all in one place, then put more green onions and 3 or 4 raw eggs.
Stir good.
Put in the milk and stir.
Bake long enough for eggs to cook, then serve.

title: pecan pie muffins
directions: Combine first three ingredients in a large bowl. Make a well in the center of mixture. Beat eggs until foamy. Stir together eggs and butter. Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened. Coat muffin pans with cooking spray. Spoon batter into cups, filling 2/3 full. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done. Makes 1 dozen large muffins or 2 dozen small ones.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 3-quart baking dish.
Add all ingredients except fruit.
Stir until smooth.
Add fruit and mix well.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Crust will form on top while baking.

title: bill's clam chowder(french)
directions: Dice pork, saute, add onion and set aside.
Scrub the quahogs. Put into large soup pot, add water to 1-inch, cover.
Boil rapidly until quahogs open.
Cool, remove meat from shell, cut up, set aside, covered.
Strain broth, add about 5 diced large potatoes.
Add enough water to be able to cover by 1-inch all ingredients.
Simmer potatoes until done, add remaining ingredients.
Add salt and pepper.
This is much, much tastier the following day.
Milk may be added or tomato.

title: banana split crumb cake
directions: Mix margarine, 1/2 cup sugar and graham cracker crumbs. Reserve 1/4 cup of this mixture.
Press remaining mixture into 2-quart oblong cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Cool. Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Spread over cracker crumbs.
Slice bananas over cheese mixture.
Spread pineapple over bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip mixed with pecans and cherries and remaining crumb mixture.
Chill.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Put strawberries in pie shell.
Mix sugar, water and cornstarch well.
Cook with gelatin.
Cool.
Pour cool mixture over strawberries.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix together and form into balls.
Refrigerate for 3 hours wrapped in waxed paper.
May be frozen; just thaw and re-form into balls.

title: meat loaf with cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine meat, onion, oats, cheese, salt, mustard and pepper.
Stir in milk and egg.
Pack mixture into lightly buttered loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Remove from oven. Combine catsup, brown sugar and 1/2 teaspoon mustard.
Spread over top of meat loaf.
Return to oven and bake 10 minutes longer. Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cream butter and cheese; mix in dry sifted ingredients.
Form into small balls; place on lightly greased cookie sheet and flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes until slightly brown on edges.
Serves 10.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salt water until tender. Drain.
Add corned beef, cheese, soup, milk and onion.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole. Top with crumbs. Bake in moderate oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: millionaire pies
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese.
Add pineapple, Cool Whip and nuts.
Pour into pie shells and refrigerate until chilled.
Makes 3 pies.

title: pumpkin cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl combine cake mix, 1 egg, butter and 2 teaspoons pumpkin pie spice; beat on low speed until crumbly.
Press on bottom of 15 x 10-inch jellyroll pan.
In same mixing bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add remaining 2 eggs, pumpkin, remaining 2 teaspoons pumpkin pie spice and salt; mix well.
Pour over crust and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until set.
Cool, chill and cut into bars.
Store covered in refrigerator.
Makes 48 bars.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Add buttermilk. Add 1 egg at a time. Stir in corn. Fold in jalapeno peppers, and cheese. Heat oil in baking dish until very hot. Pour hot oil into batter and stir. Then pour batter into baking dish. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cook raisins in small amount of water and cool.
Measure dry ingredients and sift together.
Cream sugar and butter thoroughly. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Alternate applesauce and dry ingredients using dry ingredients for last addition.
Stir in nuts and raisins which have been covered with a small amount of flour.
This prevents them from going to the bottom of pan.
Bake in loaf pan or layers which have been greased and floured.
Bake at 325°.
Test center of cake with cake tester or toothpick. Usually when cake slightly leaves the edge of pan, cake is done. Ice with icing desired.

title: luau beans
directions: Brown together hamburger, onion and pepper.
Combine meat mixture with pork and beans, pineapple and brown sugar.
Pour into baking dish and top with strips of bacon.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese soup
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, melt butter.
Add celery and onion.
Cook and stir over medium heat until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Blend in chicken broth and milk.
Cook and stir for 8 to 10 minutes or until mixture comes to boil and thickens.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese, one cup at a time, stirring to melt after each addition.
Stir in liquid smoke. Garnish each serving with bacon bits, if desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: holiday cranberry sauce
directions: Bring ingredients to boil; stir up, cover and boil until cranberries burst, 4 to 5 minutes.
Sauce jells when cold.

title: corn flakes muffins
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. Set aside. Measure corn flakes and milk in a large mixing bowl.
Stir to combine.
Let stand about 2 minutes or until cereal softens. Add egg and oil. Beat well.

Add flour mixture, stirring only until combined. Spoon batter evenly into twelve 2 1/2-inch muffin pan cups coated with cooking spray. Bake at 400° about 20 minutes or until lightly browned. Serve warm.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: applesauce cake(grandma bissonnette)
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Dissolve soda in hot water and add to applesauce.
Add flour and spices.
Add 1 cup raisins. Bake at 325° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: christmas fruit cake(recipe from 1935)
directions: Grease pan and set aside.
Cut up all fruit and add dry ingredients well with fingers, separating pieces of fruit so all is coated with dry ingredients.
Beat eggs until fluffy, and gradually beat in sugar.
Add to fruit mix.
Add nuts and pack into well-greased pan, pressing down with hand, to make sure pieces of fruit and nuts fill any empty spaces.
Cook about 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Let stand 5 minutes, then run a spatula around edges.
Turn over onto wire racks until cool.

title: mom's rhubarb crunch
directions: Put rhubarb in a 11x7 pan.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, and water.
Cook and stir until thick and clear; add vanilla.
Pour over rhubarb.
Combine remaining ingredients, and crumble over rhubarb.
Bake 350° 40-50 minutes.

title: zucchini stuffing
directions: Melt margarine in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cook zucchini and onion in small amount of water until tender.
Drain and place on top of margarine.
Mix stuffing as directed on box.
Put on top of onion and zucchini.
Mix chicken soup with sour cream.
Spread on top of stuffing.
Dot butter over the top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Very rich, very good.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk, water, vanilla and salt. Pour into 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Break bread, put into liquids and saturate crust side up.
Sprinkle on nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Cut in margarine with fork or pastry blender until mixture is fine crumbs. Stir in buttermilk. Knead dough lightly on floured surface and put into 7-inch circle.
Put on greased cookie sheet and cut a cross on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes, until loaf sounds hollow.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Stir dry ingredients and set aside.
Combine eggs, oil, vanilla and potatoes.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Fold in pecans.
Divide batter into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Makes 2 loaves. Contains 180 calories, 2 g protein, 9 g fat, 25 g carbohydrates, 48 mg sodium and 23 mg cholesterol.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Dissolve cream cheese and jello in the cup of boiling water with beater.
Mix other ingredients.
Chill.

title: green chili bake
directions: Brown and drain ground beef; add garlic powder, cream of chicken soup and water.
Layer in the following order in a casserole dish:
tortillas, cheese and meat mixture.
This mixture makes a casserole of 3 to 4 layers.
Any cheese that is left may be put on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Partially drain hominy.
Mix well with all, except taco chips; save for topping.

title: sicilian-style pizza
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve the yeast in warm water.
Add the sugar, salt and olive oil and stir to mix well.
Let stand for 5 minutes.

Using a wooden spoon, stir in the flour and mix until it forms a doughy batter that pulls away from the sides of the bowl. Push down into the bowl; cover and let rise in a warm place until it doubles in bulk, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Push down with a spoon and chill for 30 to 60 minutes.

title: carolyn corey's chicken delight
directions: Place chicken pieces in large roasting pan.
Mix all other ingredients together; mix well.
Pour over chicken.
Cover.
Bake 1 hour in a 325° oven.
Stir frequently.
Guests rave over this dish.

title: veggie salad
directions: Drain canned vegetables into a bowl.
Add green peppers, celery and pimento.
Mix together oil, vinegar, sugar, water, paprika and mustard until sugar melts.
Pour over vegetables.
Marinate for 24 hours.

title: milky way icing
directions: Melt bars in butter.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Blend in just enough milk or cream to make it spreadable.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Beat egg and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add milk, then butter and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt; add to liquid mixture and mix well.
Bake 45 minutes in moderate oven.

title: diabetic pumpkin pie
directions: Add salt, spices, Sweet 'N Low and egg to pumpkin; gradually add the milk.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar together; add remaining ingredients. Bake in 9 X 12 pan at 325° for 1 hour.
Note:
DO NOT test for doneness or open oven door until cake pulls a little from sides of pan and is brown on top, or it will fall.

title: donna's coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients for 8 minutes at high speed.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream Crisco, oleo and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time. Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites last.
Bake in 3 greased and floured pans at 350° for 30 minutes.
Decorate with Italian Cream Cake icing.

title: refrigerator cole slaw
directions: Chop cabbage, tomatoes and onions and toss together.
Mix other ingredients.
Pour over other mixture.

title: hardy potatoes
directions: Fry potatoes on one side.
Turn them and add onion, red and green peppers and mushrooms.
Completely cook, then cover with slices of cheese.
Cover pan and let cheese melt.
Serve hot.

title: maple pecan pound cake
directions: Sift flour and soda three times.
Separate yolks and whites of eggs.
Cream butter and sugar well.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, and beat well.
Add flour and sour cream alternately, beginning and ending with flour.
Add flavoring and nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.

title: guacamole
directions: Chop onion very fine.
Add chopped tomato and chili.
With a fork or potato masher, mash to a pulp the ripe peeled avocados. Add salt and lemon.
Save 2 or 3 of the pits and place on top of the combined mixture to prevent darkening.

title: cranberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve raspberry gelatin in boiling water.
Soften plain gelatin in cold water and add to raspberry gelatin.
Mash slightly the cranberry sauce and add gelatin mixture and pineapple.
Pour into mold and chill until set (Tupperware bacon keeper is perfect fit!).

title: best rum cake ever
directions: Before you start, sample rum to check for quality.
Good, isn't it?
Now, go ahead.
Select a mixing bowl, measuring cup, etc. Check rum again.
It must be just right.
To be sure rum is to the highest quality, pour one level cup into a glass and drink it as fast as you can.
Repeat.
With electric mixer beat 1 cup butter in a large fluffy bowl.
Add 1 seaspoon of thugar and beat again. Meanwhile, make sure rum is of the finest quality.
Try another cup.
Open second quart, if necessary.

title: cheese balls
directions: Tear ham into small bits, then combine all ingredients together.
Shape in a ball.
Chill and serve.

title: 3 cheese lasagna rolls
directions: About 2 hours before serving:
Cook noodles as directed; drain and cool.

title: hot green pepper jelly
directions: Use blender to grind peppers.
Mix all ingredients, except pectin and food coloring.
Bring to a boil for 3 minutes.
Add pectin and boil 1 minute.
Cool five minutes.
Add a dash of green food coloring.
Makes 7 one-pint jars.
Cover with paraffin.

title: rice-coconut-chocolate squares
directions: Mix sugar, salt and water in a saucepan.
