Bring to full boil. Stir in rice.
Cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes. Add coconut and chips to hot rice and stir until chips are melted. Cover and chill.
Fold whipped topping into rice mixture.
Pour into waxed paper lined square pan (8-inch or 9 x 5-inch loaf pan). Cover and chill until firm.
Remove paper and put on a serving plate.
Cut into squares or slice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream butter, sugar and shortening together.
Add all ingredients together.
Bake 1 hour and 25 minutes at 300°.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix together butter, sugar, flour, cornmeal, vanilla, lemon juice, and milk.
Add eggs and mix well.
Pour inter unbaked pie shells and bake at 350 degrees approximately 50 minutes.

title: crab dip or spread
directions: Mix cream cheese and crab meat together.
Pour into lightly oiled mold pan.
Chill for 12 hours.
Unmold and pour cocktail sauce (about 4 oz.) over the top.
Serve with crackers or Tostitos chips.

title: rice krispie treats
directions: Melt butter over low heat; add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add cereal and stir until well coated.
Press mixture evenly into buttered pan.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Fry chicken until crisp; use no flour.
Slightly salt 1 side of
the
washed chicken before frying.
Drain chicken on paper towels to remove excess oil.

title: baking-powder biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix dry ingredients in a bowl.
Mix in oleo with pastry cutter.
Add milk and stir with a fork.
Place dough on a lightly floured surface and knead 12 to 14 times (until it is no longer sticky).
Press dough or roll out 1-inch thick and cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle cinnamon on top.

title: microwave lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger; drain and rinse.
Mix with 1/2 cup water and sauce (do not heat).
Set aside.
Mix egg with cottage cheese and salt and pepper to taste.
Set aside.

title: sunny orange bread pudding
directions: Spray pan with nonstick spray. Spread bread (cut into small pieces) in pan. Combine all other ingredients and pour over bread. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: shrimp antipasto
directions: Place shrimp, cheese and olives in large shallow dish.
In 1-pint jar with tight-fitting lid, combine remaining ingredients except salami and pepper.
Shake well.
Pour over shrimp mixture. Cover; refrigerate 6 hours or overnight, stirring occasionally. Add salami and pepper; toss.
Drain; garnish as desired. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl. Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.

Do not beat with mixer. Stir in nuts, vanilla and pineapple. Finally add the bananas; spoon batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool 10 minutes.

title: quick buns
directions: Mix dry yeast, sugar, shortening and salt.
Add 1 cup scalded milk, cooled, with 1 cup cold water.
Add enough flour for soft dough.
Let raise and make into buns.
Let raise and bake at 350°.

title: roast raccoon
directions: Marinate the animal 4 to 6 hours; drain and blot dry inside and out.
Reserve the marinade liquid.
Put the coon in a large pot; cover with cold water to which has been added 1/2 cup per quart of the strained marinade.
Stick the cloves in the onion. Quarter the carrots; add them and the bay leaves, chili pod and salt to the pot.
Cover; simmer slowly for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Remove the raccoon; drain and blot dry.

title: chocolate macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in sugar and salt; beat again.
Add vanilla; work in coconut.
Add cocoa mix.
Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 275° about 20 minutes.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Pour over beef.
Cook in crock-pot for 6 to 7 hours or in electric frying pan with cover for 2 to 3 hours.
Beef should be very tender when done.
You can pour off sauce and freeze to use again.
Chicken, minute steak or pork chops can be used in place of beef.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together. Cream shortening with sugar and vanilla until fluffy. Add beaten egg yolks and beat thoroughly. Add sifted dry ingredients and milk alternately in small amounts beating well after each addition. Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry and fold into batter. Pour into greased pans and bake in moderate oven at 350° about 30 minutes.
Makes three 9-inch layers.

title: outrageous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat margarine, sugars, peanut butter, vanilla and eggs in large bowl until creamy.
Mix in flour, oats, baking soda and salt; stir in chocolate chips.
Drop dough by tablespoons 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 1 minute.
Remove from cookie sheet to wire rack.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: kiwi lime pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, flour and 1/8 teaspoon salt. Stir in milk.
Stir over medium heat until bubbly.
Reduce heat; cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Stir 1 cup of hot mixture into eggs.
Return to saucepan; cook and stir until thickened.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Do not boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in margarine, lime peel and juice.
Fold in yogurt.
Tint with food coloring.
Cover surface with plastic wrap; cool.

title: speedy oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine the brown sugar, oleo or shortening, soda, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Add the flour, oatmeal and nuts. Stir until smooth.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased baking sheet. Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pork chops and yams
directions: Brown chops over medium heat.
Place drained yams over chops. In mixing bowl, combine soup, sour cream and water; stir until blended.
Pour over yams and chops.
Cook over medium heat for 45 to 60 minutes, or place in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: salsa cruda with roasted chiles
directions: Combine all ingredients and let sit to develop flavors.
Check seasonings after 20 minutes or so.
Stores well in refrigerator.

title: strawberry nut cake
directions: Mix together and bake in tube pan for 45 minutes at 325° or 3 layers for 25 minutes or until done.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt butter, chocolate chips and peanut butter together over low heat.
Pour in cereal; coat well.
Pour into a large bowl; coat with powdered sugar.
Let cool completely.
Seal in an airtight container.

title: barracks
directions: Mix cabbage and onion and cook and drain well. Cook hamburger meat and drain.

title: quick rum cake
directions: Sprinkle chopped pecans on the bottom of a greased tube or Bundt pan.
Mix together cake mix, pudding, water, Wesson oil and rum.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Pour batter into pan and bake 1 hour at 325°.
Let cool.

title: cowboy stew
directions: While browning meat, add onion to cook.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients in a large pot, including the juices from the canned vegetables.
Simmer about 1 hour.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Mix mayonnaise with water and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients.
Add nuts.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Heat applesauce, stir in shortening, sugar and dry ingredients.
Stir in raisins and walnuts.
Bake about 1 hour at 325°.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine cake mix, fruit cocktail, 1 cup coconut and the eggs. Beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into a large greased pan; sprinkle with brown sugar.

title: cream puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Bring water, butter and salt to boiling point.

Add flour, all at once; stir quickly over low heat for 1 minute or until mixture leaves sides of pan and forms a ball. Remove from heat; add eggs, one at a time, and beat until smooth. Drop batter spoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes; cut center while warm.
Cool; fill with pudding.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes 12 puffs.

title: fudge crispies
directions: Combine chocolate, butter and syrup in double boiler and melt until smooth. Take off heat. Add vanilla, confectioners sugar and Rice Krispies.
Mix until everything is coated.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
May chill until firm and cut into squares.

title: swordfish and fruit kabobs
directions: Remove all bones and skin from fish.
Cut fish into 1-inch pieces.
Place in a plastic bag, then set bag in a bowl.
If using pineapple, drain it, reserving 1/4 cup juice.
For marinade, combine orange juice or reserved pineapple juice, chopped onion, sherry, oil, sesame seed, garlic, salt and pepper.
Pour over fish. Close bag and refrigerate for 4 to 6 hours, turning bag occasionally.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet to make crust.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
Cool.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pan-fry sausage, crumbling as it cooks; drain.
Place bread crumbs in the bottom of a 10 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Place sausage on top of bread.
Mix other ingredients together; pour on top of sausage.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: one pot dinner
directions: Brown
ground beef in skillet;	drain off fat
and
put beef in crock-pot.
Brown bacon and onion; drain.
Add
bacon, onion and remaining ingredients in crock-pot.
Stir
together. Cover and cook on low for 4 to 6 hours.

title: light style chicken mexicana
directions: Sprinkle chicken with garlic salt.
Heat margarine in nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken; cook 5 minutes.
Turn chicken over.
Add onions and green pepper around edges of chicken.
Cook 5 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Place rice on serving platter.
Remove from skillet and place over rice. Keep warm.
Add picante sauce and cheese to skillet.
Cook and stir until cheese is melted and sauce is hot.
Pour over chicken and rice.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Combine sugar, oil, melted chocolate and vanilla.
Beat in eggs, flour and baking powder into chocolate mixture.
Cover and chill.
Shape into balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Bake in a greased cookie sheet in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
While still warm, roll again in powdered sugar.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: easy peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and peanut butter at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add Cool Whip and confectioners sugar gradually, beating until smooth.
Spoon into pie shells.
Freeze 8 hours or overnight.
Garnish with chocolate shavings or chocolate syrup and whipped cream.
Makes 12 servings.

title: creamy chicken and broccoli soup
directions: Saute mushrooms and onion in butter in a medium saucepan over low heat until tender.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add half and half and chicken broth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Stir in diced chicken and remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: hot wieners
directions: Combine ingredients in a slow cooker.
Cook until hot and then drop in wieners.
Simmer until ready to serve.
This is good for a picnic.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: In 9 x 13 pan, place ice cream sandwiches in layer. Spread 10 ounces of fudge topping. Crush 3 candy bars over topping. Spread Cool Whip over top. Drizzle rest of topping. Sprinkle last candy bar over top. Place in freezer overnight.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine in a 3-quart saucepan. Heat on medium heat until it starts to boil, stirring constantly. Boil for about 3 to 5 minutes; continue stirring.
Remove from heat and let cool 1 minute.
Add vanilla, peanut butter, salt and oats; stir well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper.
Let cool.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Add onion and celery to 2 cups water in large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until tender.
Add soup, tuna, salt and pepper; simmer.
Combine cooked noodles and tuna mixture in a 4-quart casserole dish.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: dump cake
directions: Combine ingredients in the order given above in a 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until done. Top with ice cream or whipped cream if you wish.

title: quick chicken pie
directions: Mix cream of chicken soup and chicken broth until texture is smooth.
Mix in the other ingredients and place in a 9 x 13-inch greased casserole dish.

title: broccoli-potato bake casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook, drain, dice and mash potatoes with oleo, salt and milk.
Cook broccoli to package directions. Drain well.
Fold in mashed potatoes.
Put in casserole. Sprinkle with cheese.
Spray casserole with Pam.
Bake for 15 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: cajun taters
directions: Peel, dice and cook the potatoes; drain. Cook sausage and ground beef; drain. Cook onion and pepper.
Stir in potatoes, diced cheese and tomatoes with seasoning. Cook on low in crock-pot for 2 to 3 hours.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Arrange chicken pieces in pan.
Top with Swiss cheese.
Combine undiluted soups, dry stuffing and seasoning packet.
Pour over chicken.

title: fruit delight
directions: Cut fruit into bite-size pieces.
Drain all fruit juices into saucepan and mix boxes of vanilla pudding.
Cook until thickened and cool in fridge overnight or 3 hours.
Mix fruit, except bananas, and chill in separate bowl.
When ready to serve, mix fruit, pudding and sliced bananas.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350°.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine soup, milk, and pepper. In baking dish layer potatoes, onions, cheese, and soup mixture. Layer twice. Pour butter on top. Sprinkle with paprika. Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour. Uncover and bake additional 15 minutes or until done.

title: sheryl's pasta surprise
directions: Prepare pasta according to instructions.
Prepare bacon and drain.
In large bowl, combine softened cream cheese, sour cream, margarine and milk.
Microwave or boil until ingredients become a sauce, stirring occasionally.
In large casserole, place the boiled pasta.
Shred bacon over pasta.
Then add melted cheese sauce.
Microwave on Medium power for 15 to 20 minutes (or until ingredients form casserole consistency).
Or bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: apple butter
directions: Combine and cook slow for abut 1 1/2 hours until dark and thick.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in three 9-inch pans at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: s'mor
directions: You take 2 graham crackers and a Hershey chocolate bar.
You halve the chocolate bar and put it on the graham cracker, then you put the marshmallow on last.
You put on the other graham cracker and put it in the microwave for 50 seconds.
Then you have a S'Mor.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, celery, mayonnaise, onion, salt and pepper.
Put in a shallow casserole dish.
Top with crumbled crackers or onion rings.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° until bubbly or brown.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Dip chicken in egg and milk mixture, then flour, egg, flour and salt and pepper to taste.
(Use 1/4 cup of milk for each egg used.)

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil, eggs and sugar in bowl. Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and baking powder. Add to cream mixture. Stir in chopped apples and nuts. Spread mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Put butterscotch chips on top. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes. Cool and cut into squares. For best results, bake a day or 2 ahead.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shake well; chill.
Use on fresh salads.

title: pralines
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and cook to soft boil stage. Remove from fire. Add salt, vanilla and
butter. Beat until creamy. Add 2 c. pecans. Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper. Makes about 3 dozen Pralines.

title: celestial cheesecake
directions: Sprinkle crumbs in bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan sprayed with Pam.
Place cheeses, sugar, egg whites, vanilla and lemon juice in blender.
Whip until smooth.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Stir together Dream Whip, sugar and sour cream.
Spread on cooled cheesecake.
Chill.
Remove sides of pan to serve.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Take cream cheese at room temperature and cream well.
Add mayonnaise and mix well for a good consistency. Add lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder and hot sauce, also onion. Mix well.
Use as much mayonnaise as needed for right consistency. Fold in shrimp.
Use your favorite chips or crackers to dip.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together the margarine, peanut butter, sugar and egg. Add flour and vanilla.
Mix together. Form dough about the size of a marble.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and press with fork. Bake at 325° until done.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Spread cream cheese onto tortilla shells.
Leave about 1-inch uncovered on ends.
Add grated cheese.
Sprinkle with peppers and chopped black olives.
Roll up very tight.
Refrigerate a few hours or overnight.
Slice down into pinwheel shape.
Dip in salsa.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Add brown sugar.
Blend well. Cool.
Stir in egg.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together. Stir into butter mixture.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread in well-greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
Cut bars while warm.

title: pork chop casserole for one
directions: Place cooked noodles in lightly greased individual casserole. Add onion, salt, pepper and sage to tomato juice.
Pour over noodles.
Brown pork chop on both sides.
Remove and place on top of noodle mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Yields 1 serving.
Each serving contains approximately (Exchanges):
2 meat, 1 bread and 1 vegetable.

title: party chicken
directions: Line a shallow baking pan with dried beef.
Place chicken breasts on dried beef.
Put 1 strip bacon on each chicken breast. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, mix first 9 ingredients until well blended. Shape into a loaf.
Place in loaf pan and top with 2 tablespoons of spaghetti sauce.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: elegant crab salad
directions: Combine crabmeat, celery and onion.
Mix together remaining ingredients, except lettuce and paprika.
Combine crabmeat with dressing and chill in refrigerator for 30 minutes or more.
Line salad bowl with shredded lettuce, add crabmeat mixture and sprinkle lightly with paprika.

title: lemonade pies
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into crusts. Refrigerate 1 hour or longer.

title: buffalo chicken salad
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper and red pepper.
Coat both sides of chichen with flour mixture, heat oil in 12 in non-stick skillet.
Stir in hot pepper sauce.
Add chicken and cook 6 - 8 minutes per side until browned.
Transfer to cutting board, cover loosely and let stand 5 minutes.
Slice celery diagonally into 1/2 inch thick pieces; combine in medium bowl with lettuce and apples. Slice chicken into 1/2 inch thick strips; add to salad, then toss with blue cheese dressing.
Makes 6 servings.
285 calories, 15 g fat.

title: no cook mint patties
directions: Blend corn syrup, butter and peppermint.
Divide into 3 parts. Make 1 red, 1 green and leave one white.
Shape into balls and flatten with fork (on wax paper).
Let dry.
Can coat with chocolate, if you like.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine ham, pork, crumbs, eggs, milk and pepper. Mix well. Shape like a ham and score with spoon handle.
Bake in shallow roasting pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Garnish with maraschino cherry halves pegged with whole cloves.

title: ham a la king
directions: Saute green pepper in the butter in saucepan over low heat 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms and saute about 1 minute.
Remove green pepper and mushrooms and set aside.
Stir flour into pan liquid. Gradually add milk and cook, stirring, until thickened.
Add ham and heat, then add green pepper, mushrooms and pimento.
Heat, stirring gently.
Add paprika and salt to taste.
Serve on noodles, rice or biscuits.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cocktail pizzas
directions: Crumble and well cook sausage; drain well.
Add remaining ingredients, except biscuits.
Separate each biscuit into 3 rounds.
Spread each round with sausage mixture and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
May be frozen before baking and stored in plastic bags until ready to use.
Makes 90.

title: dessert pizza
directions: Lightly grease a 12-inch pizza pan.
Press cookie dough evenly onto prepared pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Combine sugar and cornstarch in a small saucepan.
Stir in pineapple juice.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Transfer mixture to a bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap; cool.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Cream together
first 4 ingredients.
Sift together and add flour, cinnamon,
cloves
and
allspice.
Add nuts, applesauce and soda.
Pour into muffin cups and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Can refrigerate
batter and use later.
Serve hot or cold sprinkled with powdered sugar.

title: gingerbread
directions: In glass bowl, blend flour, sugar, margarine, ginger, cinnamon, allspice, cloves and nutmeg as for pie dough.
Reserve 3/4 cup of mixture for topping.
Add soda and sour milk; mix with metal spoon until it makes a dull sound in bowl.
Add eggs, salt and molasses and pour into 9 x 13-inch floured pan.
Cover with reserved dry ingredients for topping.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or less.

title: butterscotch cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium pan, melt chips and margarine. Stir in crumbs and nuts.
Press half of mixture onto bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
In bowl, mix cheese until fluffy.
Beat in Eagle Brand, egg and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into pan on top of crumb mixture.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool to room temperature.
Chill before cutting into bars.
Refrigerate.

title: throw me down cake
directions: Layer in pan in order listed.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour covered with foil.
Remove foil and bake 15 minutes more.
Remove from oven.

title: chicken-fruit salad
directions: Toss together chicken, celery, lemon juice and seasonings. Mix in mayonnaise and grapes.
Serve on lettuce cups.

title: three cheese enchiladas
directions: Combine 3 cheeses, saving 1/4 cup each of Cheddar and Monterey Jack cheeses.
Add picante sauce and mix well.
Put 1/4 cup of mixture on each tortilla shell.
Roll up, placing fold on bottom of pan.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes, onions and olives. Serves 4.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Peel, dice and parboil eggplant.
Saute onion, celery and shrimp in olive oil.
Add tomato and cook.
Season with salt, pepper, a dash of Tabasco sauce, a dash of Worcestershire sauce and 1 bay leaf. When all are blended together, fold in the eggplant.
Place in baking dish. Top with seasoned bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lemon green beans
directions: Wash beans and remove strings.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces if desired.
Cook, covered, for 12 to 15 minutes in small amount of water.
Drain and set aside, but keep warm.
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Stir in lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Add beans and cook 1 minute or until thoroughly heated, stirring constantly. Serves 2.

title: 60 minute rolls
directions: Sift flour, salt and sugar together.
Cut in lard.
Add the yeast, dissolved in 2 tablespoons of water and warm milk.
Work lightly until smooth.
Roll out like biscuits and cut with cutter or shape in balls for cloverleaf.
Let rise 1 hour and bake in oven at 375°.

title: sugar and honey pecans
directions: Combine sugar, honey, salt and 1/2 cup water in medium saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until sugar is dissolved, stirring constantly.
Continue cooking, without stirring, until a little in cold water forms a firm ball or to 242° on candy thermometer.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: In a nonstick skillet coated with nonstick cooking spray, brown chicken over medium heat. Transfer to a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish coated with nonstick cooking spray. Re-coat skillet with nonstick cooking spray; cook onion over medium heat until tender. Stir in the remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes. Pour over chicken. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until chicken juices run clear and a meat thermometer reads 170°. Yield: 6 servings.

title: creamy chocolate pie
directions: Melt marshmallows, water and chocolate together.
Add vanilla; cool.
Whip whipping cream until fluffy; fold into chocolate and marshmallow mixture.
Fold into pie shells.
Chill for 3 hours. Top with Cool Whip and grated chocolate.

title: skillet gumbo
directions: Combine all ingredients in skillet (except rice).
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in rice.
Cover and simmer until tender.

title: homemade chicken stew
directions: Boil your chicken and keep broth.
Take all chicken off bone. Put back in chicken broth and add vegetables and gravy.
Simmer on medium low heat for 1 hour.
Serve.

title: scripture cake
directions: Cream the Judges until light.
Blend in the Jeremiah 6:20. Stir together the Kings 4:22, Amos 4:5, Leviticus 2:13 and Chronicals 9:9.
Mix Jeremiah 17:11, Judges 4:19 and Samuel 14:25. Add wet and dry ingredients alternately to creamed mixture and mix well.
Stir in Samuel 30:12, Nahum 3:12 and Numbers 17:8. Turn mixture into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Loosely cover with foil.
Bake 50 minutes more.
Let cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.
Brush all sides with Proverbs 31:6 or orange juice.

title: chicken pie
directions: After chicken is cooked and cut up, place in a large baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Mix cream of chicken soup and chicken broth and heat in saucepan until creamy.
Add salt and pepper, pour over chicken.
Melt margarine and add to flour and milk; mix well until lumps are smooth.
Spoon this over chicken (do not pour).
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Fold in sour cream, marshmallows and fruit.
Chill.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Beat together eggs, vanilla, orange juice and vegetable oil. Mix together cinnamon and sugar.
Mix flour and baking powder. Peel and slice apples in small bowl.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Add flour and baking powder mixture slowly to the beaten egg mixture.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour 1/3 of batter in cake pan.
Cover with 1/3 of apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Repeat 2 more times, ending with sugar and cinnamon mixture on top.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 12.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip softened cream cheese until smooth.
Add 10x sugar, peanut butter and milk.
Blend until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Freeze at least 2 hours.

title: cobbler pie
directions: Melt margarine, add sugar and flour.
Add milk gradually while mashing out all lumps.
Sweeten fruit to taste.
Cover with water, boil for approximately 5 minutes, then pour into dough.
Gently mix dough with fruit.
Bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Cook chicken breast and cut in pieces (1/2 to 1-inch).
Add lemon juice, mayonnaise and curry powder to soup and mix well.

title: cracker candy
directions: Line a jelly roll pan with aluminum foil.
Completely cover it with a single layer of saltine crackers.
Boil margarine, white and brown sugars for 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Let melt and spread.
Cool in refrigerator and break in pieces.
Could be cut into squares with pizza cutter or spatula.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients but vanilla in top of double boiler. Beat 1 minute to blend.
Place over boiling water and beat constantly with rotary beater or at high speed of mixer for 7 minutes or until frosting stands in stiff peaks, stirring occasionally with rubber scraper.
Remove from boiling water and pour at once into large bowl.
Add vanilla and beat one minute, until thick enough to spread.
Makes 4 1/2 cups.

title: peanut butter play dough
directions: Mix peanut butter, dry milk and honey.
Taste. If not sweet enough, add more honey.
Fun to play with but even better to eat!

title: cream puffs
directions: Bring water to boil; stir in margarine (make sure margarine melts).
Stir in flour.
Stir vigorously until mixture comes away from sides of pan, making a ball.
Remove from heat.
Stir in eggs, one at a time, beating 1/2 minutes.
Drop on greased cookie sheet by tablespoon.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.
Makes 12 to 15.
Let cool.

title: meatballs
directions: Bring to a boil, then turn down on medium; add meatballs and cook for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
The sauce and meatballs can be frozen for a couple of weeks.

title: sponge cake
directions: Sift flour once, measure and sift 4 times.
Add water and 1/2 cup sugar, vanilla and almond to egg yolks and beat with mixer until very thick and light.
Add flour all at once and stir until just blended.
Beat egg whites and salt with mixer.
When foamy, add cream of tartar.
Continue to beat until egg whites are stiff enough to hold up in peaks, but not dry.
Add remaining 3/4 cup sugar.
Fold in egg yolk mixture.
Bake in ungreased tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: country ham chowder
directions: Simmer potatoes and carrots in 3/4 cup water, covered, about 10 minutes or until tender.
Reserve any liquid for soup.
Melt butter in large saucepan.
Saute onions and celery until golden brown and soft.
Stir in flour and cook for 2 minutes, stirring well.
Add milk, potatoes with liquid, pepper, salt and mustard.
Bring to a slow simmer.
Add ham and cheese.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until soft, drain and mash.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add potatoes and remaining ingredients except paprika; beat until combined.
Spoon into buttered casserole. Sprinkle paprika.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: cucumbers and sour cream
directions: Use a large bowl.
Combine all ingredients until well blended. Chill for a couple of hours.
Serve with favorite meat and breads.

title: ski salad
directions: Drain fruit and place juice in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat.
Add gelatin.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add to gelatin mixture.
Mix well.
Add fruit and Ski, 1 to 2 cups, depending on how firm you want your salad.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish and refrigerate for several hours.

title: chicken stir-fry delight
directions: Cut chicken into slices (thin strips) or bite size squares. Warm electric skillet or wok, placing 2 tablespoons butter in until it melts.
Place chicken in, turning frequently, until chicken is cooked.
Mix stir-fry seasoning by directions on packet and pour over chicken.
Let simmer.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Put eggs in another bowl and beat well.
Add vanilla and cocktail; stir and fold into dry ingredients. Mix well.
Pour into greased pan and bake 40 minutes.

title: butter-cheese sauce
directions: Stir melted butter and cream together.
Add cheese and blend well.
Makes sufficient sauce for 1 pound of cooked and drained, hot fettuccine.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Fold all together and refrigerate 8 to 12 hours before serving.

title: beef and vegetable fried rice
directions: In a large skillet, brown beef, garlic and ginger over medium heat 8 to 10 minutes.
Break up cooked beef until crumbly. Meanwhile, cook rice according to package directions.
Remove beef and pour off drippings.

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 400°.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and Crisco.
Add egg, water and vinegar. Makes 2 (2-crust) pies.

title: swiss steak
directions: Have steak cut 1 1/2 to 2 inches thick; season the flour with salt and pepper.
Dredge both sides of steak with flour so that as much as possible is taken up.
Brown steak on both sides in hot lard.
Add tomatoes and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer for 2 1/2 hours.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook rigatoni until done.
Drain and cool.
Dice tomato and green pepper.
Add salad dressing, tomatoes and green pepper to rigatoni and toss well.
Add Parmesan cheese, garlic and pepperoni.
Toss well and refrigerate.

title: herbed potatoes
directions: Slice
potatoes 1/4-inch thick and place in rectangular baking dish.
Place
butter
on potatoes.
Sprinkle with soup mix. Cover with foil and bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Remove foil and continue to bake for 15 minutes.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Fill bread pan 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy calzones
directions: Thaw loaves of bread dough.
Divide each loaf into 5 parts. Roll each dough piece, making ten 7-inch squares.
Fold each dough square over half a cheese slice to form a turnover and pinch edges to seal.
Place calzones 2-inches apart on baking sheet sprayed with Pam.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for about 15 to 20 minutes. Ladle hot spaghetti sauce on top of calzones and serve.
Serves 10.

title: shrimp and vegetable stir-fry
directions: In large skillet or wok, heat oil, butter, lemon juice and garlic.
Stir-fry peppers, carrots and onion over medium-high heat until crisp-tender.
Add broccoli, squash, mushrooms and shrimp; stir-fry 5 minutes or until shrimp is cooked through.
Stir in tomato sauce; heat an additional minute.
Serve over cooked rice or pasta.
Serves 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender. Shred into baking dish. Pour dry stuffing mix over the chicken.
Mix broth with cream of mushroom and cream of chicken soups.
Pour over the layer of Stove Top mix.
Poke holes in the layers to let the liquids go through. Dot with butter.
Bake at 400° until brown on top (30 to 40 minutes).

title: walnut or raisin bread
directions: Beat eggs and sugar thoroughly.
Add milk and blend well. Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Stir in nuts or raisins.
Mix 1 hour in moderate oven.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: angel strawberry bavarian
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare, bake and cool cake following package directions.
Cut cooled cake into 1-inch cubes.
Drain strawberries, reserving juice.
Combine strawberry gelatin and boiling water.
Stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Add enough water to strawberry juice to measure 1 cup.
Add to gelatin; refrigerate until gelatin is slightly thickened.
Beat gelatin until foamy. Beat 1 cup whipping cream until stiff peaks form.
Fold into gelatin along with strawberries.
Alternate layers of cake cubes and strawberry mixture in tube pan.
Press lightly.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Unmold cake onto serving place.

title: cracker jacks(or microwave corn)
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients in a 2-quart dish in microwave until boiling and cook 2 minutes longer on High.
Stir in soda and pour over popped corn in a brown grocery bag.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes and shake bag hard.
Cook 1 1/2 minutes more and shake.
Try 1 1/2 minutes more (possible burn, watch last 1 1/2 minutes).
The point is so corn will be crunchy and not sticky.

title: venison casserole
directions: Place meat in casserole dish and spoon on mushroom soup.
Add dry soup mix and tomatoes.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: hard candy
directions: Sprinkle an 18 x 24-inch strip of heavy-duty aluminum foil with powdered sugar.
Mix first 3 ingredients in large, heavy saucepan. Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Boil, without stirring, until temperature reaches 310° or until drops of syrup form hard threads in cold water.
Remove from heat; stir in flavoring oil and coloring.
Pour onto foil.
Cool and break into pieces.
Following is a list of flavors and colors:

title: heavenly dessert
directions: Mix and put 2/3 in bottom of a pan, then put whipped cream on top with the rest of the cracker crumbs on top.

title: potatoes supreme
directions: Grate cooked potatoes coarsely. Mix in remaining ingredients and put in a shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: ann's holiday fruitcake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and oil.
Add egg yolks.
Beat well.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder several times.
Add 1 2/3 cups flour mixture to fruit and nuts in large bowl.
Add remaining flour mixture to cream mixture.
Mix into the fruit and nuts.
Last, beat the egg whites stiff, but not dry.
Fold into mixture and bake in large tube pan, greased and floured.
If you use a large tube pan, bake in 250° oven 3 to 3 1/2 hours.
If you use two smaller pans, bake about 2 hours and 20 minutes.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°, then turn down oven for rest of time.
Watch closely last half hour.

title: sour cream apple squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl combine Chex crumbs, flour, brown sugar and butter.
Blend at low speed with mixer until crumbly.
Stir in nuts.
Press 2 3/4 cups evenly into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: easy tamale casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well. Bake in uncovered casserole at 350° for 1 hour.

title: inside out ravioli
directions: Fry hamburger, onion and garlic in 1 tablespoon of oil.
Cook spinach and drain.
Add enough water to spinach liquid to make 1 cup.
Add to meat plus sauces, paste, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Combine spinach, cooked shells, cheese, crumbs, eggs and oil in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with meat sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Allow to set before serving.

title: stromboli
directions: Prepare pizza crust.
Fill with ingredients.
Top with small amount of pizza sauce.
Fold dough over and seal.
Brush with olive oil.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and parsley flakes.
Cut slits in top.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Serve pizza sauce on the side.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in greased 9 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: eggplant fries and salsa
directions: Peel eggplant.
Cut into strips.
Combine flour, cornmeal and salt.
Stir in milk and egg until moistened.
Roll eggplant in batter.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Drain well.
Serve salsa.

title: flowerpot dirt cake
directions: In food processor or blender, crush cookies until fine.
Set aside.
In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, butter and sugar until smooth.
In another bowl, mix pudding and milk until well blended. Fold into cream cheese mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Line a new flowerpot with foil.
Alternate layers of crumbs and pudding, ending with crumbs.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Decorate with silk flowers and gummy worms.

title: famous brownies
directions: Mix flour and sugar in bowl. In a saucepan, mix the cocoa, margarine and water. Bring this mixture to a boil. Then add flour and sugar mixture to cocoa mix. Then add eggs, soda, vanilla extract and buttermilk. Pour into pan and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: granny tish's tea cakes
directions: Cream all ingredients, except flour.
Add flour, mixing by hand, until thick enough to roll.
Roll on floured cloth and cut into cookie shapes.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° just until bottoms begin to brown.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Grease bottom of 9 inch round cake pan with 1 tablespoon butter.
Set aside.
Combine remaining melted butter, corn, sour cream and eggs in large bowl.
Corn meal, stirring until moistened.
Stir in cheese and chopped peppers.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until golden.

title: banana cream cheesecake
directions: In a small bowl, combine cracker crumbs and sugar; stir in butter. Set aside 1/2 cup for topping. Press remaining crumb mixture onto the bottom and up the sides of a greased 9-inch square baking pan. Bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes. Cool on a wire rack. In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth. Fold in 2 cups of whipped topping. Arrange half of the banana slices in crust; top with half of the cream cheese mixture. Repeat layers. In a bowl, beat milk and pudding mix until smooth. Fold in remaining whipped topping. Pour over the cream cheese layer. Sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture. Refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours or until set.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a mixing bowl, adding chocolate chips and nuts last.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in a Bundt pan (greased and floured).
Cake is done when it bounces back when touched or toothpick comes out clean when inserted.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: coconut cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients the day before; put in refrigerator.
Bake yellow cake mix per directions on box.
Cut layers into 4 layers.
Ice.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Pat browned beef into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place onion on top.
Layer Tater Tots over this.
Mix 2 cans of soup with 1 can water and pour over.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blueberry streusel muffins
directions: Cream the butter. Gradually add 1/3 cup sugar, beating at medium speed of an electric mixer until light and fluffy.

Add egg, beating well. Combine 2 1/3 cups flour, baking powder and salt. Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, stirring well after each addition. Stir in vanilla extract and fold in blueberries. Spoon batter into greased muffin pans, filling 2/3 full. Combine 1/2 cup sugar, 1/3 cup flour and cinnamon. Cut in 1/4 cup butter with a pastry blender until mixture resembles crumbs. Sprinkle on top of muffin batter. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown. Remove from pans immediately.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; crumble.
Heat oven to 350°; grease 8 or 10-inch pie plate.
Put remaining ingredients in blender. Cover and blend on high 1 minute.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until brown, 50 to 55 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes; cut and serve.

title: fillet of sole with cheese
directions: Steam onions for 3 minutes in a covered vegetable steamer basket.
Add mushrooms and steam an additional 2 minutes.
In a baking dish, layer half the onions, half the mushrooms and half cheese.
Arrange sole over the cheese.
Top with the remaining onions, mushrooms and cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until fish flakes with fork.

title: ginger ale citrus cooler
directions: In large saucepan, cook and stir sugar and water over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to boil for 5 minutes and then cool.
Stir in juices; cover and refrigerate until chilled before serving. Stir in ginger ale and cherry juice.

title: lace cookies
directions: Add ingredients in order listed. Mix well. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes on aluminum foil. Peel from foil when cooled.

title: crawfish pie
directions: Simmer crawfish 10 minutes.
Mix with seasoning. Simmer 15 minutes.
Bake one pie shell until light brown.
Pour mixture into pie shell. Cover with the other shell. Brush top of shell with melted butter. Bake until golden brown.

title: broccoli and cauliflower casserole
directions: Soften Cheez Whiz in bowl over hot water.
Saute celery and onions in margarine.
Combine soup with milk; mix with celery, onions, broccoli, cauliflower and 1/2 of the Cheez Whiz.
Turn into buttered baking dish.
Pour remaining Cheez Whiz over top. Crush Ritz crackers and cover entire surface.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pot roast meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart bowl.
With wet hands, shape into loaf in center of pan.
Peel and slice 1/4-inch thick, medium potatoes, onions and carrots.
Place vegetables in layers around meat.
Sprinkle with salt.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes to brown.

title: paska (easter bread)
directions: In small saucepan, heat milk, just until bubbles start to form around edge of pan.
Cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast over water in large bowl, stirring until dissolved.
Stir in milk mixture. Add 2 eggs and 3 cups flour.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Gradually add 3 more cups flour, mixing with hand until dough is stiff enough to leave side of bowl.
Turn out dough onto pastry cloth or board floured with remaining 1/2 cup flour.

title: no-fail pie crust
directions: Chill about 15 minutes before rolling.
Makes two 9-inch double and one 9-inch single.
(Store in refrigerator if not all used.)

title: seaweed salad
directions: Make day before.
Combine jello and water, then add other ingredients, leaving cottage cheese and nuts last.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to use.
Serve on lettuce leaf, if desired.

title: cream cheese chocolate chip brownies
directions: Cut 1 roll and press into bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Pour over cookie dough.
Cut second roll and press on top of cheese mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: french cherry delight
directions: *I get box of crackers and use food processor to crush.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Put all
ingredients
in
a large pan or roaster.
Stir seasonings into
melted
butter.
Pour
1/3 over at a time and stir each time.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Cool before storing in jars.

title: miracle cookie(no flour required)
directions: Combine peanut butter and sugar; mix thoroughly.
Add beaten egg and vanilla; mix well.
(Optional:
stir in chopped pecans.) Roll into 3/4-inch balls; flatten with floured fork on greased cookie sheet, 1 1/2-inches apart.
Bake at 350° about 10 to 13 minutes.
Allow to cool on cookie sheet before removing.
Yields about 4 dozen.
Keeps well in airtight container.

title: cheddar tomato soup
directions: Combine tomatoes, onions and celery in food processor and blend until coarsely chopped.
Pour into large sauce pan, add chicken stock and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Simmer uncovered for 20 minutes.
Add cream.
Season with basil, salt and pepper.
Cook over very low heat for 5 minutes.
Add cheese and cook, stirring constantly, until cheese melts.
Serve at once.

title: sugar custard pie
directions: Mix eggs and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Add melted butter.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 350° until center is done.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Mix cream of chicken soup and chicken broth.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over chicken.
Mix flour, buttermilk and oleo and spoon on top.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: garden fresh turkey burgers
directions: Lightly grease rack of broiler pan.
Combine first 7 ingredients; mix well.
Shape into 6 burgers.
Place on rack of prepared pan or over medium hot coals on an outdoor grill 6 inches from heat.
Broil 7 to 9 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
Serve on rolls with rounded tablespoonful of sour half and half per serving.
Garnish with lettuce and sliced tomato, if desired.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place half of the stuffing mix in a large shallow casserole. Melt oleo and pour over mix.
Mix together chicken, celery soup, cream of chicken soup and broth.
Pour this over casserole and top with remaining stuffing mix. Bake at 350° about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: crabmeat strudel
directions: Saute onions in olive oil, until golden brown.
Add cleaned spinach, salt, pepper and nutmeg; toss lightly.
Remove from heat; spinach should remain wilted.
When cold, add crabmeat, Ricotta cheese and one egg.
Mix well without breaking the crabmeat.
Lay out 2 stacks of 4 layers phyllo dough, side by side.
Place mix on top and roll dough, while brushing it with melted butter.
Place on buttered sheet pan and bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 375°. Serve with boiled potatoes and remaining melted butter.
Garnish with dill or chives.
Serves 5 to 7 persons.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Drain spinach well.
Mix 1 cup cheese with sour cream, soup, spinach and hash browns.
Mix in ham.
Pour mixture in a greased baking pan.
Top with rest of cheese.

title: cheese potato crisps
directions: Peel and cut lengthwise the potatoes into 1/4-inch slices. Place in shallow baking pan.
Drizzle with 1/4 cup melted butter or margarine.
Sprinkle with the salt and cheese.
Top with corn flakes.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix together, in a 2 quart microwave safe bowl, the raw peanuts, sugar and white syrup.
Cook 6 minutes on high.
Take out and add 1 tsp. vanilla and 1 tsp. oleo. Stir well.
Put back in microwave and cook 7 minutes.
Remove and add 1 tsp. baking soda.
Stir well and pour onto a well buttered cookie sheet stretching as thin as possible.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Break or cut up broccoli and cauliflower into small pieces. Add all other ingredients.

title: apricot dainties
directions: Mix the apricots, coconut and Eagle Brand milk together.
Roll into small balls.
Then roll them in powdered sugar.
Serves 24.

title: chocolate clair
directions: Mix pudding with milk until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour 1/3 into 9 x 13 size dish.
Top with 1 layer of graham crackers, 1/3 pudding, 1 layer graham crackers, 1/3 pudding, 1 layer graham crackers.
Top with chocolate frosting.
Refrigerate.
It is best if you refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: bourbon sauce
directions: Mix together cornstarch and butter; add brown sugar and water. Stir mixture over low heat until thickened.
Remove and add bourbon.
May be served over pound cake, gingerbread, pancakes or ice cream.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Mix together until all the flour is mixed into the eggs.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13 pan. Pour mixture into buttered pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hickory sausage breakfast pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375° F. In large skillet, cook sausage over medium-high heat, stirring frequently until thoroughly cooked and no longer pink. Separate crescent rolls into eight triangles. Place in ungreased 12-inch rimmed pizza pan with points toward the center. Press together, seal perforations and form a circle 1 inch larger in diameter than bottom of pan. Turn edges under to make a slight rim. Sprinkle cooked sausage evenly over crust. Top with potatoes; add peppers and/or onions if desired. Sprinkle with cheddar cheese. Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper in small bowl; stir well. Pour evenly over pizza. Sprinkle with Parmesan. Bake 20 minutes or until eggs are set and crust is golden brown.

title: no salt herb blend
directions: Place leaves in a bowl and crush a small amount at a time. Place in a shaker.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Put gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Dissolve jello in 1 cup of boiling water.
Put these ingredients plus 1/2 cup cold water or pickle juice, corned beef (broken into several pieces), salad dressing, mustard and Worcestershire sauce into blender.
Mix in blender, then add all other ingredients.
Pour into rectangular Pyrex dish.
Chill overnight in refrigerator.
Serves 10.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix peanut butter, powdered sugar and butter; shape into balls.
Place on waxed paper and chill for an hour.
Melt the chocolate chips with the paraffin over hot water.
Dip the peanut butter balls into chocolate, leaving a small portion on the top uncoated to look like buckeyes.
Place on wax paper and refrigerate.

title: alpine chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in greased pan.
Layer Swiss cheese over chicken.
Combine soups with milk or water and pour over chicken. Toss stuffing with butter and spoon over all.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour and bake uncovered 1 hour.

title: four layer chocolate dessert
directions: Mix together the flour, oleo, 1/4 cup powdered sugar and nuts. Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Let cool.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie tin.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Yields 2 to 3 dozen cookies.

title: casserole
directions: Brown meat; add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: rice krispies candy
directions: Melt oleo and peanut butter.
Mix with sugar and Rice Krispies. Make into bite-size balls.
Put on cookie sheet and freeze.
Melt 1 1/2 cups of chocolate chips and 1/2 cake of Parowax.
Using a toothpick, dip balls in the mixture.
Put on wax paper to dry, then store them.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Bring pineapple to boil in saucepan.
Stir in jello.
Mix well, then chill until partly set.
Stir in buttermilk.
Chill again until partly set.
Fold in whipped topping.
Chill until firm.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers and graham crackers on cutting board. Add cherries (1 cup cherries in 4 pieces.)
Add pecans and raisins to dry mixture. Mix until all are mixed. Add condensed milk and mix thoroughly.
Pack in dish. Cover and refrigerate.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt one stick butter, blend with graham cracker crumbs. Place in bottom of pan. Mix two sticks of butter with powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Beat with mixer until well blended. Spread over cracker crumbs.
Drain pineapples dry.
Place over cream cheese mixture.
Place bananas over pineapple.
Place Cool Whip over bananas.
Garnish with pecans and cherries.
Keep refrigerated.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Add taco seasoning.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.
If you use a crock-pot, set on low.
Simmer the soup longer as flavor improves. Sprinkle cheese and crumbled nacho chips on top before serving.

title: peanut butter and jelly french toast
directions: Make 6 peanut butter and jelly sandwiches.
Set aside.
In mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Add milk and salt.
Mix well.
Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat.
Dip sandwiches in egg mixture, coating well.
Place in skillet and brown both sides. Serve warm.
The kids will love them.
Easy to make.

title: etta's coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour and add remaining ingredients. Beat well. Pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: easy rice pilaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into buttered casserole. Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stewed tomato salad
directions: Mix all and put into lightly oiled mold.
Serves 12 or 1/3 recipe serves 4 to 6.
Nice in individual molds.

title: fresh spinach omelet
directions: In skillet over medium-low heat, cook garlic 1 minute in butter or margarine. In small bowl, beat eggs, salt, pepper and 2 tablespoons of water. Stir in spinach. Tilt skillet to grease sides. Pour egg mixture into skillet; cook until set around sides. With a spatula, lift edges, tilting skillet to allow uncooked portion to run under omelet. Shake skillet occasionally to
keep omelet moving in pan. Increase heat slightly to brown bottom of omelet. With spatula, fold omelet in half; slide onto warm platter. Serve immediately. Yield:
3 servings.

title: bubbles (for blowing)
directions: Add Joy or Dawn (do not use inexpensive dish soap) to water. Drizzle in glycerine (obtained from drugstore).
Mix gently so as not to cause a foam to form in the mixture.

title: easy 5 cup salad
directions: Stir together and chill.

title: 24 hour open jar sweet pickles
directions: Cut tips and ends off of larger pickles.
Slice pickles in spears.
Put some dill and sliced onion in the bottom of the Tupperware Fix-N-Mix bowl.
Fill with the long sliced pickles. Boil the juice good and pour over pickles.
Let stand 24 hours and then put in jars.
Refrigerate.
(Put a large plate on top of pickles in bowl so they are covered with juice and don't float and these are very good and a "hit" with many people.)

title: mama's nut cake
directions: In large bowl, sift together flour, salt, baking powder and soda. Stir in sugar. Add sliced Crisco, butter, milk, vanilla and eggs. Beat all at one time for 3 minutes. Scrape sides and beat 2 more minutes. Add nuts; stir in well. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, celery, onion, almonds, mayonnaise and soup. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread cheese and chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: eggplant salad
directions: Broil eggplant until soft, turning every 5 minutes.
Peel and smash inner part.
Add garlic, salt and olive oil.
Mix well. Spread out.
Sprinkle tomatoes and Feta on top.
(Goes great with bread.)

title: hot pizza dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and Italian seasoning.
Spread into the bottom of an 8 inch baking dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup mozzarella and 1/2 cup parmesan evenly on top of the cream cheese mixture.
Pour pizza sauce uniformly over the cheeses.
Sprinkle remaining cheeses evenly over pizza sauce.
Top with chopped onion.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350 degrees.
Serve with bread sticks.

title: round steak in red devil gravy
directions: Roll steak in seasoned flour and pound with mallet or the edge of a saucer.
Cut in serving pieces.
Brown meat in shortening. Remove steak and brown onions in same shortening and pan.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well and return steak to sauce.
Cover and cook 1 1/2 hours, until tender.
Add a little more water if gravy is too thick.
Serve with rice.

title: pumpkin cake bars
directions: Mix eggs, pumpkin, sugar, salt and spices well.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over top.
Drizzle melted butter over mix.
Spread chopped pecans over all.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Top with favorite glaze or enjoy plain.

title: strawberry-raspberry favorite
directions: Add boiling water to gelatin in a large bowl.
Stir until dissolved.
Beat in sour cream.
Fold in yogurt.
Add lemon juice and mashed raspberries.
Spoon in individual dessert dish.
Chill 1 hour.
Garnish with strawberries.

title: peach truffle
directions: In large bowl, pour can of peaches in and mix jello with syrup in peaches.
Break pound cake into the peaches and Jello mixture. Press down. Mix instant vanilla pudding (large) according to direction.
Pour over cake.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: In 9 x 13-inch greased pan, spread 2 pounds frozen hash brown potatoes, partially thawed.
Drizzle with 1/2 cup melted margarine over potatoes.
Mix 1 can cream of chicken soup, 1 cup sour cream, 2 cups cubed Cheddar cheese and 1/2 cup onion. Pour over potatoes. Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: frying pan cookies(an oldie)
directions: Put sugar, dates
and eggs in greased frying pan.
Stir constantly, 7 to
minutes, mashing dates as you stir.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir
into
mixture
until well mixed. Start pan on hot.
When
hot, turn to low.
When all is mixed, turn out on wax paper.

title: easy white chicken enchiladas
directions: Spread tortilla chips to cover bottom of 9 x 13 Pyrex.	Mix all ingredients except cheese.	Spread over chips.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cover with cheese and bake another 5 minutes.
Very easy and kids love it!

title: summer salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed, 12 to 14 minutes.
Rinse in cool water and drain well.
Mix pasta and all other ingredients together and serve with hot French bread.

title: chicken peg legs
directions: Roll peg legs in coating mix.
Place in wheel arrangement with bone end toward center, in round glass baking dish.
Cover with paper towel to prevent spattering.
Cook on Full power 8 minutes.

title: marie's cottage cheese salad
directions: Sprinkle Jell-O over cottage cheese and mix well.
Add drained crushed pineapple and Cool Whip.
Mix everything together and chill.

title: dirt cake
directions: Put Oreos through food processor.
Put aside.
Make pudding according to package directions.
Let get firm, then fold in 1 cup of Cool Whip.

title: summer pasta salad
directions: Thaw Birds Eye Farm Fresh mixtures under water; drain. Combine all ingredients and mix.
Serve cold.
Makes 5 servings.

title: ella cookies
directions: From Great Aunt Ella Hershberger.

title: banana bread
directions: Makes one 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Heat bouillon in 1 1/2 cups of water until dissolved; add broccoli.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.
When cooked, add milk, cheese, nutmeg and a dash of pepper.
Combine flour and water; pour into cheese and broccoli.
Cook until thick and bubbly.

title: the dreamers fudge cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar in a large mixing bowl, beating well.
Add 2 whole eggs and 2 yolks and beat very well.
Dissolve baking soda in butter, stirring well.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with flour.
Start and end with flour.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Add 1 cup mini morsels, melted chocolate, chocolate syrup and vanilla, stirring just until blended (do not beat).

title: lauren's caramel cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg and vanilla thoroughly.
Measure flour by dipping method or by sifting.
Stir flour, soda and salt together, stir in.
Form in roll 2 1/2-inches across.
Wrap in wax paper.
Chill until firm.
Heat oven to 400°.
Cut in 1/8-inch slices.
Place slices a little apart on ungreased baking sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until a little brown. Makes 5 dozen.

title: mexican surprise
directions: In a pretty, ovenproof pie plate spread cream cheese on the bottom.
Top with can of chili and spread.
Put cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes until lightly brown.
Serve with chips after mixture cools slightly.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet. Drain well. Add mushroom soup to hamburger. Pour mixture into a 9 x 12 baking dish. Layer Tater Tots on top. Cook in oven at 400° or until Tater Tots are brown.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables and celery for 10 minutes; drain.
Add onion, chestnuts and 1/2 of grated cheese.
Blend mayonnaise and soup; fold into vegetables.
Lightly cover bottom of medium size Pyrex dish with dressing.
Pour in vegetable mixture.
Then spread on dressing mix and remaining cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: homemade chilli
directions: Brown hamburger meat and add chilli seasoning mix.
Combine tomato soup, water, kidney beans and onions in a boiler.
Bring to a boil.
Then add hamburger meat mixture, after you drain it, to the soup mixture.

title: tuna puffs
directions: Drain and flake tuna.
Combine all ingredients, except Puff Shells; mix thoroughly.
Cut tops from Puff Shells.
Fill each shell with approximately 2 teaspoonfuls salad.
Yield: About 55 hors d'oeuvres.

title: piscado italliano
directions: Melt butter and garlic in skillet.
Salt and pepper fish.
Saute in butter over medium heat about 8 minutes, turning once.
Put pasta onto serving dishes.
Place one fillet on pasta on each dish. Smother with Italian sauce and Monterey Jack cheese.
Sprinkle with parmesan and green onions.

title: sugarless orange cookies
directions: In a bowl, beat egg into butter.
Stir in orange rind and orange juice.
In another bowl, combine dry ingredients, then add to wet ingredients.
Beat by hand until well blended.
Stir in nuts and raisins.

title: popovers
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat at low speed with an electric mixer just until smooth.
Place a well-greased 3 1/2-inch muffin pan in a 450° oven for 3 minutes.
Remove pan from oven and fill half full with batter.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 20 to 25 additional minutes.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat on low heat the jello, sugar and crushed pineapple until jello is dissolved.
Allow to cool.
Add buttermilk and whipped topping.
Mix with beater.
Stir in pecans.
Spoon into 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain.
Add 1/3 cup melted butter. Add all ingredients, except toppings (crumbs and cheese), to butter.
Put in casserole dish.
Dot with 3 tablespoons butter. Sprinkle with crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together; let set in refrigerator a few hours before using.
Dip in any raw vegetables.

title: markie's pineapple dish(good for brunch)
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Cover with crushed Ritz crackers. Pour 1 stick of melted butter over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate squares
directions: Melt chocolate.
Add remaining ingredients, saving out enough nuts to sprinkle on top of batter.
Spread thinly on cookie sheet. Bake at 400° approximately 15 minutes.

title: island chicken kabobs
directions: Stir together barbecue sauce, dressing, juice, vanilla and allspice.
Arrange chicken, pineapple and peppers on skewers. Pour sauce mixture over kabobs.
Cover.
Marinate in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Drain; reserve marinade.
Place kabobs on greased grill over low heat.
Grill 10 minutes on each side.
Brush frequently with marinade.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix; roll (shape like an egg on plate).
Put shaved almond slices on sides and top.
Serve with any type of crackers.

title: date filled oatmeal bars
directions: Combine flour, oats, soda, salt and brown sugar.
Cut in butter with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal. Press half of mixture into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix together and form into balls.

title: triple chocolate cookies(makes 4 dozen)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a mixing bowl, beat butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until blended.
Add eggs and milk; beat well.
Stir together flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; gradually add to butter mixture, blending well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 minutes.
Press kisses in center of each cookie.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Melt butter, saute broccoli and onion, add salt.
Add cheese until it starts to melt, mix with other ingredients in casserole and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: granny goo bars
directions: Mix with fork the cake mix, butter and 1 egg.
Press into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Beat with mixer at medium speed the remaining eggs, confectioners sugar and cream cheese.
Pour over previous mixture.
Sprinkle with crushed pecans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar while hot.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Beat butter 30 seconds.
Add sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add vanilla and 2 teaspoons water; beat well.
Stir flour and pecans.
Shape into 1-inch balls or 1 1/2-inch fingers. Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Heat in a 325° oven for 20 minutes.
Cool completely.
Gently shake in a bag of powdered sugar.
Makes 36.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine milk and eggs, pour over bread cubes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour mixtures in 8 -
inch round baking dish.
Place in shallow pan on oven rack; pour hot water around it 1 -
inch deep.
bake at 350 degree for 45 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and outside comes out clean.

title: scalloped oysters and ham
directions: Arrange 1/3 of the cracker crumbs in a buttered shallow dish about 1 quart size.
Cover with half of the oysters and half of the ham.
Blend oyster liquor and light cream, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper after using the other part of oysters, crackers and ham.
Dot with margarine.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: lemon kiss cookies
directions: In large bowl, beat butter, sugar and lemon extract until fluffy.
Add flour and almonds.
Beat at low speed until blended. Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Shape dough around each kiss, covering completely.
Roll to form ball.
Bake at 375°.
Place on ungreased sheets for 8 to 12 minutes.
Cool completely.
Sprinkle cookies with powdered sugar.
Melt chocolate chips and shortening over low heat.
Drizzle over cookies.

title: peach stuff
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, pecans and margarine.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Bake until lightly browned. Cool completely.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar. Layer on cooled cake.
Layer on sliced peaches.
Mix jello, cornstarch, sugar and water.
Bring to boil and cook approximately 1 minute or until thick.
Cool and drizzle over peaches.

title: ham and asparagus casserole
directions: Put asparagus in colander to drain all juice off.
Roll asparagus in slices of ham and put in large casserole dish.
Make cheese and pour over top of ham rolls.
Put in 400° oven and bake for 20 minutes.

title: hamburger minestrone
directions: Saute onion, celery and hamburger until brown.
Drain.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Thaw frozen spinach (do not cook); drain excess liquid.
Mix together next 7 ingredients, then add spinach and reserve.
Cook pasta shells.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Spread thin layer of sauce on bottom of two 13 x 9-inch baking pans.
Stuff shells with cheese mixture.
Place in pans, pour layers of sauce over shells and sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: tomato pasta
directions: Mix all and let stand for one to ten hours.
Toss with hot pasta.
Serves 4.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in bowl, add eggs and vanilla, then add pumpkin, raisins and carrots.
Mix well.
Spray 12 muffin tins with non-stick cooking spray.
Put mixture into muffin tin.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix together and press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: 2 month bran muffins(low cholesterol!)
directions: Combine 2 cups Bran with 2 cups boiling water.
Let stand. Combine oil, sugar, Egg Beaters and buttermilk.
Sift together and add flour, salt and soda.
Stir in remaining dry All Bran.
Stir in soaked All Bran.
Store in tightly covered container up to 2 months in refrigerator.
Spoon into muffin pan sprayed with oil or oiled, 2/3 full of batter.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Saute rice as box directs.
Stir in 2 cups water, ham, onion, tomatoes, garlic, hot pepper sauce and contents of seasoning packet.
Bring to boil over high heat.
Cover; reduce heat to low. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in shrimp and green pepper.
Cover; simmer 8 to 10 minutes more, or until most of liquid is absorbed and shrimp turns pink.
Serves 5.

title: hungry man casserole(this casserole won't leave you hungry!)
directions: This is a great meat ball and sauce recipe for spaghetti or mostaccioli noodles.

title: grandma's molasses cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add molasses.
Dissolve baking soda in hot coffee; add to creamed mixture.
Gradually add flour and spices.
Stir to combine.
Stir in raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheets.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with sugar when hot out of oven.
Makes 4 to 6 dozen.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until done; drain.
Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Spray casserole with nonstick spray and pour in mixture. Cover with grated cheese and bake at 350° until heated completely through and bubbly.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Spread into greased oblong 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top with slices of white American cheese.
Cut diagonally (which may be topped with thin slices of tomato).
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake until slightly brown, about 30 minutes.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook rice in water.
Add mushroom soup, cheese and oleo.
Mix well with broccoli.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and cover with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cranberry cream cheese mold(prep time:  25 minutes.  setting time:  6 hours.)
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in a large bowl at least 2 minutes or until dissolved.
Stir in cold water and cinnamon.
Pour 2 cups of gelatin into medium bowl.
Refrigerate about 1 1/2 hours or until thickened.
Reserve remaining gelatin at room temperature. Stir apples and cranberry sauce into thickened gelatin.
Spoon into 6-cup mold.
Refrigerate about 30 minutes or until set but not firm.
Stir reserved gelatin gradually into cream cheese in small bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Pour over gelatin layer in mold.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until firm.
Unmold.
Store leftover in fridge.
Makes 12 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, allspice, nutmeg, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Mixture will be thick. Add fruit and nuts. Spoon into oblong pan and pat down with fingertips.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: chicken tarragon
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Cook chicken, asparagus and red pepper in olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add wine and tarragon.
Simmer 1 1/2 minutes. Heat thoroughly.
Serve over rice.
Yields 4 servings.

title: crab salad
directions: Combine ingredients lightly. Chill and serve.

title: blueberry pizza
directions: Mix cake mix with 1 cup of oatmeal and 6 teaspoons margarine until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup of mixture for later.
To remaining mix, add egg.
Press into a greased pizza pan.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.

title: asparagus tomato quiche
directions: Beat eggs with next 5 ingredients.
Stir in cheese.
Save 6 asparagus spears for top.
Chop the rest into 1-inch length.
Lay on bottom of pie shell.
Pour in liquid.
Bake 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and quickly arrange tomato and asparagus on top in pinwheel pattern.
Bake another 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatin in water 5 minutes. Beat egg yolks and add 1/2 cup sugar, pumpkin, salt, spices and milk. Cook over low heat stirring constantly until mixture begins to thicken. Add gelatin to hot pumpkin and stir until dissolved. Cool. When mixture begins to thicken, beat egg whites until almost stiff and beat in remaining sugar, one tablespoon at a time. Fold into pumpkin mixture and pour into two 9-inch baked pie shells and chill until firm. Cover with whipped cream and serve. Keeps well without the cream.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream egg yolks, sugar and butter.
Put in other ingredients. Whip egg whites to snow and then blend carefully with batter. Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: pasta salad with shrimp
directions: Cook linguine according to package directions. Drain, rinse with cold water and drain again.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt chocolate with butter.
Beat eggs and add rest of ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for about 30 to 35 minutes.
So easy!
Our boys' favorite!

title: spinach salad
directions: Remove stems from spinach.
Clean in cold water with a little vinegar, then dry the leaves.
Place dry spinach leaves and watercress in a salad bowl.
Cut bacon in 1/2-inch squares and fry until crisp.
Add sugar, wine vinegar and Lea & Perrins.
Heat to a boil and stir in dressing over spinach leaves, leaving bacon in skillet.
Squeeze lemon over leaves, then toss until wilted. Drain dressing off salad and place spinach on plate.
Add cognac to bacon, ignite and spoon over spinach leaves at once.

title: poor man's crab cakes
directions: Combine ingredients; form into cakes.
Dip in flour or bread crumbs (I prefer bread crumbs).
Fry in hot oil as you would crab cakes.

title: the best zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil, vanilla and yogurt together.
Add all of the dry ingredients.
Add zucchini and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 sprayed loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: fried rice
directions: Break up noodles into small pieces.
Brown in vegetable oil in a large frying pan.
Add all other ingredients; mix well.
Cook until water is absorbed on a low flame.

title: potato-cheese scallop
directions: Saute onion slices in butter.
Place 1/4 potatoes in bottom of greased 2-quart dish or casserole.
Add 1/2 each onion slices, cheese, flour, salt and pepper.
Repeat layers.
Pour milk over. Cover and bake for 1 hour.
Remove cover and bake 15 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread oleo out evenly.
Add ingredients as listed (in layers).
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.
Let cool in pan.
Cut in squares.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, cocoa and milk.
Stir over medium heat.
When it comes to a hard boil, cook and stir one minute. Remove from heat; add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Spoon onto wax paper.

title: cabbage and beef dish
directions: Brown ground beef or ground turkey and onion. Drain and season to taste. Spread in baking dish. Top with cabbage. Pour diluted tomato soup on top and cover. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 6 servings, 1/2 cup each.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk.
Add lemon juice.
Mix well.
Pour in pie shell.
Chill and serve.

title: country style cream corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into round baking pan.
Cook in oven at 400° until brown.

title: best ever lemon pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in saucepan.
Set aside.

title: corn stuffing balls
directions: Cook onion and celery in butter.
Add corn, water, salt, pepper, poultry seasoning and thyme.
Bring to boil.
Pour over bread stuffing and mix lightly.
Add egg yolks and shape into 12 balls.
Place in shallow pan and pour melted butter over all. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: quick and easy tamale casserole
directions: Spread chili in bottom of a Pyrex dish.
Unwrap tamales and put on top of chili.
Spread another layer of chili.
Add desired amount of cheese on top.
Heat either in microwave or in oven until hot and bubbly (add cheese last 5 to 10 minutes).

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook slowly 2 to 3 hours.
This is very good on spareribs or any meat.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into large (11 x 13-inch) buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with topping.

title: bar-b-que wieners
directions: Fry onion in butter. Add other ingredients. Cut wieners into 1 inch pieces and cook in sauce for about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: fruit pudding
directions: Bring to a boil 3/4 cup peach syrup, 3/4 cup pineapple syrup and the pudding mix until mixture becomes clear like.
Let mixture cool for approximately 1 hour.
Add pineapple, peaches and cherries.
Chill.
Add sliced bananas just before serving.

title: peppered cheese ball
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Shape mixture into a 5-inch ball.
