Combine cracked peppercorns.
Roll cheese ball in mixture until evenly coated.
Wrap in heavy-duty plastic wrap. Chill until firm. Serve with assorted crackers.
Yields one 5-inch cheese ball.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Mix together in a buttered casserole dish the canned tomatoes, 1 cup prepared stuffing, sugar, salt and black pepper.
Top with 1 cup poultry stuffing mixed with butter.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: holiday ham balls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease jelly roll pan.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Place about 2 inches apart on pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Immediately remove from pan.
Serve warm.
Makes about 7 dozen appetizers.

title: chili
directions: Saut onion and ground beef. Add rest of ingredients. Cover and cook 45 minutes. You may substitute soy burger or ground turkey for beef. Freezes well.

title: oatmeal cake(with topping)
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal.
Set aside.

title: cream of vegetable soup
directions: Boil rice in water until almost tender.
Add salt and vegetables. Continue boiling until vegetables are tender.
Add milk and cook until heated.

title: coconut salad
directions: Mix together and let sit before serving.

title: christmas jam cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in 3 layers in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Cool.

title: granny cake
directions: Stir together first 4 ingredients and add eggs and pineapple. Put batter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crab mousse
directions: Heat soup and add gelatine mix.
Let cool.
Mix together cream cheese, clam, mayonnaise, green onions, juice of lemon and Tabasco with mixer on low.
Add soup mixture and mix again.
Grease mold with mayonnaise and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with cocktail break or crackers.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar, Crisco and salt.
When crumbs are made, remove 1 cup for topping.

title: rice casserole
directions: Put all ingredients in 3-quart greased casserole.
Mix lightly.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple harvest coffee cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar together; let set for 1 hour.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat eggs and add oil, vanilla and apple mixture.
Add flour mixture and chopped nuts.
Bake in a large greased Bundt pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Best made at least 1 day in advance because flavor is much better the second day.
Sprinkle cool cake with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: rudolph sandwich treat
directions: Slice bread diagonally.
Spread peanut butter on each slice of bread.
Turn each slice with point down.
Place a cherry half on the point for Rudolph's nose.
Place raisins for eyes.
Place pretzel sticks at the top of the triangle for antlers.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: Mix tomato soup and milk together in saucepan.
Add celery seed, Sweet 'N Low, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Add butter and serve.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix together and refrigerate cole slaw and onions.
Mix together next 6 ingredients.
Refrigerate for several hours. Toast almonds and sesame seed in 350° oven.
Just before serving, crumble Top Ramen noodles; mix with almonds and sesame seed. Place over slaw.
Pour dressing over and serve.

title: grandpa's favorite mockingbird brownies
directions: Combine first three ingredients in a small saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Combine buttermilk and soda, stirring until soda dissolves.
Combine flour, sugar and cocoa in a large bowl.
Add hot mixture and stir well.
Add buttermilk mixture and eggs.
Mix well.
Spoon into a greased jelly roll pan (15 x 10 x 1-inch). Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Frost with Buttermilk Frosting while still warm.
Sprinkle with nuts. Cool and cut into squares.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend with mixer until smooth and creamy.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Brown the chicken breast in small amount of oil in large skillet. While chicken is browning peel potatoes, cut in half lengthwise and place flat side down in 9 x 13 inch baking dish. Lay browned chicken breasts on top of potatoes.

title: double almond crunch candy
directions: Spread almonds in separate shallow pans.
Place in a slow oven (300°) until nuts are delicate brown.
Watch carefully.
Melt butter over low heat in a 2-quart heavy saucepan.
Add sugar, corn syrup and water.
Cook, stirring occasionally, to hard crack stage (300°).
Quickly stir in warmed, toasted coarsely chopped almonds. Spread in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool thoroughly.
Spread with melted chocolate chips and top with fine chopped nuts.
Break in pieces.

title: spicy pumpkin bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Mix in pumpkin and water.
Combine dry ingredients and stir in.
Add nuts.
Pour into two greased and floured bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: buttermilk rolls
directions: Soften yeast in small amount of buttermilk heated to lukewarm. Add remaining buttermilk and oil. Beat in 3 cups flour; add sugar mixed with salt, soda and baking powder. Add remaining flour; turn onto floured surface and knead lightly. Grease dough and put into refrigerator until ready to use. About 2 hours before baking, form into balls and let rise about 1 1/2 hours. Bake in 400° oven about 20 minutes. Makes 2 dozen rolls.

title: ham 'n yam(microwave)
directions: Place ham slice in 2-quart glass baking dish.
Arrange sweet potatoes around ham slice.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over ham and sweet potatoes.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on roast for 12 to 14 minutes or until heated through.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes before serving.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion together until tender.
Mash cooked squash;
add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Top with grated cheese.
(I use 1/2
c. mild cheddar cheese and 1/2
c. Velveeta cheese.)
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until bubbly and brown.

title: beef and cabbage casserole
directions: Brown beef in shortening.
Add onion and celery.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Place half in bottom of casserole.
Cover with half of cabbage; repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix white cake mix, water, 1/2 package
strawberries, oil, eggs and Jell-O.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage.
To make sauce, melt butter.
Add flour and milk.
Cook.
Layer cabbage, crackers, cheese and sauce.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon salt and pepper; end with crackers on top.

title: bean dip
directions: Saute meat; season and add sauce.
Drain.
Add beans.
Put meat in shallow pan, then put sour cream on top.
Add grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: quick cheesecake
directions: Soften	cream
cheese;	add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Pour
into	crust.	Refrigerate
at least 1 hour before serving. Serve plain or with your favorite fruit topping.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in the shortening.
Add the milk. Pare and core the apples; cut in eighths.
Roll dough until about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut in 5-inch squares.
Put 4 pieces apple in each square.
Cover with sugar; generously sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Dot with butter.
Place in greased baking pan.
After pinching corners together, pour over syrup.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix ingredients all together. Pour in Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked barbecue chicken
directions: In bowl, mix sauce, seasoned salt, onion flakes, sugar and water.
Arrange chicken in baking pan.
Salt and pepper pieces. Pour mixture over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 2 hours.

title: scrumptious punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Makes 3 gallons of punch.

title: cranberry orange muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray 12 muffin cups with cooking spray. In large bowl, combine next 4 ingredients.
In small bowl, blend egg, orange peel, juice and oil; stir into flour mixture until moistened.
Stir in cranberries (or blueberries) and nuts.
Spoon into muffin cups.
Sprinkle with 2 teaspoons sugar.
Bake 18 to 22 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 5 minutes; remove from pan. Makes 12 servings.

title: waikiki chicken and rice
directions: Coat chicken pieces with flour.
Brown in shortening.
Pour on gravy and pineapple chunks.
Stir in ginger, cover and simmer at 220° on top of the stove for 25 minutes.
Add oranges.
Simmer 5 minutes more.
Serve with hot cooked rice.

title: salt pickles
directions: Place 6 green grapes in a quart jar, then pack small washed cucumbers to fill the jar.
Add 3 more green grapes, 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 tablespoon salt. Fill jar to 1-inch of top with a mixture of 1 part vinegar to 1 part water.
Boil seals. Adjust on jars.
Place jars in hot water bath until the water comes to a boil.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed of mixer for 30 seconds.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.

title: party chocolate pie
directions: Cream the butter (in mixer).
Add sugar gradually. Add chocolate, extract and vanilla.
Mix well. Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating 5 minutes after adding each.
Pour into crust. Chill several hours. Cut.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Rinse and cool. Remove seeds and chop tomato.
Mix together all ingredients.

title: overnight french toast
directions: Place bread in single layer in a container.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over bread, turning once.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Fry 4 minutes on each side at 300°. Sprinkle with 10x sugar and top with syrup.

title: rocky road fudge bars
directions: Melt together 1/2 cup butter and 1 square chocolate.
Add 1 cup sugar, 1 cup flour, baking powder, 1 teaspoon vanilla, 2 eggs and 1/2 to 1 cup nuts.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix together the cream cheese, 1 egg, 1/4 cup butter, 1/2 teaspoon vanilla, 2 tablespoons flour and 1/4 cup chopped nuts.
Spread over chocolate mixture; sprinkle with 6 ounces chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with 2 cups miniature marshmallows. Bake 2 minutes longer.
Spread with icing and swirl with marshmallows.

title: great grandmother's russian teacakes
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla thoroughly.
Measure flour by dipping method.
Stir flour & salt together; blend in and mix in nuts.
Chill dough over night.
Heat oven to 400 degrees.
Roll dough in 1 in. balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Cookies do not spread.
Bake 10-12 minutes or until set but not brown, while still warm roll cookie balls in powdered sugar then roll in sugar a second time.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix
kraut
and
sugar together and let stand 1/2 hour. Add remaining
ingredients
and let sit in refrigerator overnight.

title: no bake lemon nuggets
directions: Mix all ingredients well; let stand 5 minutes.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in coconut.
Store in covered container in refrigerator a few days before serving.

title: potato doughnuts
directions: For doughnuts combine 1 1/2 cups flour, yeast and baking powder.
Heat milk or water, margarine, sugar and salt until warm (120° to 130°).
Add flour to mixture along with egg and potatoes. Beat with electric mixer on low speed for 30 seconds, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat on high 3 minutes.
Stir in remaining flour, using a spoon, until dough is smooth.
Place in a greased bowl.
Cover and chill 2 hours or overnight.

title: granola
directions: Mix dry ingredients together (first 7).
Melt butter and sugar together; pour over dry ingredients and mix well.
Spread into large, flat pan and bake at medium heat until golden brown, stirring often.
Add raisins after baking.
Allow to cool before storing.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix dressing of mayo, sugar & vinegar.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain liquid from pineapple into saucepan and add butter, sugar and well beaten eggs.
Place over medium heat and stir constantly until very hot, then thicken with paste of flour and water.
Let cool and pour over large bowl of pineapple, marshmallows and walnuts.

title: encheez-lada
directions: Drain chiles.
Combine soup, cheese spread and cumin.
Mix well.
Add chicken and chiles.
Spread 1/2 cup chicken mixture over bottom of 3 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Layer 4 tortillas, dipped in taco sauce and 1/3 of remaining chicken mixture.
Repeat layers 2 more times.
Cover and bake at 350° for 39 minutes.
Top with lettuce and tomato.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine sugar, salad oil and eggs in large bowl; mix well. Combine dry ingredients; add to oil mixture, beating well.
Stir in pumpkin.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in greased and floured pans.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough into pizza pan and bake until lightly browned 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip and spread on cooled cookie.
Chill.
Then put a light layer of glaze on mixture, arrange fruit in decorative pattern, drizzle lightly with glaze and serve.

title: bachelor's dish
directions: Saute onions and pepper in oil, add meat and brown.
Add all other ingredients and pour into 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 more minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Peel apples and potatoes; slice.
Layer in casserole:
sausage, apples and potatoes.
Repeat to top of casserole, ending with potatoes.
Add 2 tablespoons of water. Cover lightly and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: forever amber
directions: Cube orange slices.
Mix all ingredients together with orange slices.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 275° for 30 minutes. Take out of oven and add one box white confectioners sugar.
Mix well and drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Let stand overnight on wax paper.

title: magnificent mandarin mold
directions: Dissolve orange gelatin in boiling water; add cold water. Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in fruit; pour into 9-inch round or square pan.
Chill until firm.
Unmold onto platter. Combine whipped cream, salad dressing and miniature marshmallows; spoon over gelatin.
Yields 12 servings.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: In a large bowl, beat sugar, oil and eggs.
Add vanilla and zucchini.
Mix dry ingredients and add alternately with milk to zucchini mixture.
Pour into small (3 1/2 x 6 x 2) loaf pans and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Allow to stand for 10 minutes and remove from pans and cool.
You could also bake this in a 9 x 13 pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: the best dessert
directions: Combine flour, butter and pecans; press into a 13 x 9-inch ungreased pan.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon, cloves, shortening, eggs and molasses; beat well.
Add flour and baking soda (if baking soda is mixed with first cup of flour, it blends better).
Add flour slowly. Let dough stand in refrigerator for 1/2 hour.
Spoon dough onto cookie sheet.
Grease the bottom of a glass, dip in sugar, press cookie and add raisin on top.
Bake for 15 minutes at 300°.
Check often.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream Crisco with sugar; add eggs (unbeaten). Dissolve soda in hot water; add to first mixture. Sift flour, salt and baking powder, then add nuts and chocolate chips.
Combine all ingredients. Drop on cookie sheet in small amounts. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook ground beef until done, stirring to break up into small pieces.
Drain well on paper towels.
Salt and pepper lightly. Allow to cool.
Combine beef, drained beans, onion, chilies, tomatoes and olives.
Put lettuce in large bowl and top with beef-bean mixture.
Sprinkle on cheese and taco chips.
Pour dressing over all.
Toss well.
Serve at once.
(Hold cheese, taco chips and dressing until time to serve if made in advance.)

title: pizza chicken
directions: Dip breasts in eggs.
Roll in crumbs.
Brown chicken in oil; drain.
Place chicken in 13 x 9-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Pour spaghetti sauce over chicken.
Top with mushrooms and Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° until done (about 1 hour).

title: gazpacho
directions: In food processor, blend the garlic, half the green peppers, half the celery and half the onion with the tomatoes.
Pour into a large bowl.
Blend in chicken broth, seasonings, diced cucumber, lemon juice and oil.
Add the remaining green peppers, celery and onion.
Chill 25 hours.
Pour into chilled soup cups.
Garnish with cucumber slices.

title: fast tomato sauce
directions: Blend tomatoes in blender.
Saute onion and garlic in olive oil until soft.
Add salt, pepper and/or pepper flakes.
Add tomatoes.
Mix.
Bring to a boil.
Stir frequently.
Add basil. Simmer 25 to 35 minutes.

title: cocoa cream pie
directions: In a medium saucepan, stir together cocoa, sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Gradually add milk to dry ingredients, stirring until smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in margarine and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Carefully press plastic wrap directly onto pie filling.
Cool; refrigerate 6 to 8 hours.
Top with whipped cream.
Refrigerate leftover pie.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: pineapple cream cheese pie
directions: Blend together the cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and the vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip; pour into pie crust.
In a saucepan, cook the pineapple, 1/2 cup sugar and cornstarch until shiny or glazy.
Let cool, then pour over pie.
Refrigerate to set.

title: chive-roasted corn
directions: In a small bowl, combine margarine or butter, chives or green onions, garlic powder and pepper.
Using a knife, spread ears of corn with the butter mixture.
Wrap each ear in a piece of heavy foil.
Grill corn on an uncovered grill directly over hot coals for 15 to 18 minutes or until tender, turning frequently.

title: fluffy pudding frosting
directions: Pour milk into medium bowl.
Add pudding mix and sugar.
Beat with wire whisk 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Spread on cake at once.

title: deep-dish peach pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except butter or margarine.
Let stand while making pie crust (one crust) or shortcake dough.
(Use Bisquick, to which sugar and cream are added to taste.)
Put fruit mixture into deep pie plate.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Place pastry or shortcake over peaches.
Bake in hot 425° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm.
Use whipped topping or whipped cream as garnish, if desired.

title: strawberry salad squares
directions: Dissolve jello	in
water.
Add strawberries, pineapple and banana.
Pour half	of
mixture
in 8 x 8-inch pan and let set. Spread a layer
of	sour
cream, then pour rest of jello mixture and set.
Serve
on
green lettuce leaves and top with sour cream.

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Melt butter and remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 2 unbaked 9-inch pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl beat the eggs well and add oil, honey, yogurt and sugar; mix well.
Blend in flour, then add remaining ingredients and mix well. Spray an 8-inch square pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Pour batter into pan and bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
For a nice touch sprinkle on some confectioners sugar after cake has cooled.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: cranberry-raspberry mold
directions: Pour boiling water on gelatin in bowl; stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Refrigerate until thick, but not set.
Beat in sour cream and cranberry sauce with hand beater.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Makes 16 to 20 servings.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and
sugar.
Add
eggs,
one at a time and beat well.
Sift flour with salt, soda and baking powder.
Add flour mixture and
sour
cream
alternately to butter mixture. Add flavorings.
Bake
in greased and floured tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hash brown potato bake
directions: Thaw hash browns in a large bowl.
In a medium frying pan, saute onion in margarine until tender. Mix first 6 ingredients together and put in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Spread crushed chips on top. Bake at 350° until bubbly, 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Great with steak or roast.

title: turkey noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Cook egg noodles until tender. Melt butter and add flour. Cook approximately 30 seconds. Add milk and stir constantly. Bring to slow boil. Continue to stir until thick. Remove from heat. Add Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper. Add turkey and noodles to white sauce. Place in 2-quart casserole. Top with bread crumbs. Bake in 375° oven until top browns and heated through.

title: pizza sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut shortening into flour until mixture resembles bread crumbs.
Add milk; mix with fork.
Turn out on cloth, roll out and cut into 1/2-inch wide strips, about 3 inches long.
Dip in melted butter; roll in mixture of Parmesan cheese, oregano and garlic salt.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet; bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Great with basic sauce or cheese sauce.

title: tex mex(corn bread)
directions: Lightly beat egg and add all ingredients, except cheese and jalapenos. Stir until blended. Pour half of mixture into a greased 8-inch pan; sprinkle with cheese and jalapenos. Add rest of mixture and sprinkle with remaining cheese and jalapenos. Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apple wassail
directions: Heat on medium until it boils, then simmer for 10 minutes. Strain.
Serves 20.

title: laurie's whole wheat bread
directions: Combine water, molasses and yeast in large bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
Add oil and 4 cups whole wheat flour and beat about 110 strokes.
Add enough white flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Let rise until doubled.
Punch down, cover and let rise again.
Form into 3 loaves; place in well-greased bread pans.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Sift together dry ingredients and add to first mixture. Chill in refrigerator, then roll into 1-inch balls and place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes about 12 dozen.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Beat in large bowl, butter, sugar, egg and vanilla until smooth and blended.
At low speed, beat in flour mixture until smooth.
Stir in milk.
With spoon, stir in oats until well blended. Refrigerate, covered, about 3 hours.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook shells, drain and let cool.
Mix chopped ingredients with shells.
Let set to cool and add grated cheese.
Mix lightly and chill.

title: cheesy fish soup
directions: In large saucepan, cook onion in oleo until tender.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Blend well.
Add milk, stirring constantly until thick.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
In medium saucepan, dissolve bouillon in water.
Bring to a boil.
Add fish and simmer until fish flakes easily.
Add to cheese mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Reheat to serve.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Saute almonds in a small amount of butter.
Add to shredded cabbage.
Add green onions.

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: Blend sugar, corn syrup, hot water and butter in 2-qt. bowl. Microwave 12-14 minutes, stirring once or twice during last half of cooking to 250°.
Add peanuts and microwave 3-1/2 - 4 minutes until 300°.
Add vanilla and soda; blend well.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet or buttered foil.
Working quickly, partially cool by lifting edges with spatula and pulling mixture thin.
Cool and break into pieces.
Makes 2 lbs.

title: creme d' asperges soup("the best")
directions: Saute leeks and onion in butter.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes. Cut tips from asparagus and same.
Break off root end.
Cut rest in strips and add to leek/onion mix.
Cook 10 minutes more.
Stir in flour/curry mixture; brown slightly.
Add stock, half and half, salt, sugar and pepper.
Cook and stir until slightly thickened. Remove from heat; blend in blender until smooth.
Return to saucepan and reheat.
Pour into bowls; top with cooked asparagus tips.
One batch won't be enough of this excellent soup!

title: stuffed green peppers(six medium size)
directions: Mixture is spooned into peppers.
Tops are dabbed with catsup. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Dab with more catsup last 5 minutes.

title: easy chili
directions: Cook ground chuck and onion until brown.
Drain.
Add beans, tomato soup, water, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: cherry tart
directions: Mix all together until it becomes thick. Press into 9 x 13 inch pan. Put oven on 350°. Bake until crust is golden brown.
Let crust cool.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix eggs thoroughly.
Add sugar and mix until sugar is dissolved.

Add whipping cream and mix well with a dash of salt. Add vanilla and some milk, then pour into container and add enough milk to come to the marker, then mix some in container before freezing in an ice cream mixer.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt; cut in shortening.
In separate bowl combine egg, water and vinegar.
Add to flour all at once.
Blend with spoon until flour is all moistened.
Will keep refrigerated for several days.
For single pie shell, roll out and form in pie plate.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken; debone and cut up.
Place in pan.
Mix together soup, milk, flour, margarine and 1 can of broth from chicken. Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef; sprinkle soup mix over meat.
Stir in water; simmer 10 minutes uncovered.
Mix all ingredients and enjoy.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken with salt and pepper to taste.
Debone chicken; cut into small pieces.
Cook stuffing according to package directions.
Mix soups together.
Add 1/2 cup of reserved broth to soups.
In a casserole dish, do a layer of chicken, soup and stuffing, ending with stuffing on top.
Pour other 1/2 cup of reserved broth on top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: coleslaw parfait salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water; blend in mayonnaise, cold water, vinegar and salt.
Chill until partially set.
Beat until fluffy; add vegetables.
Pour into a 1-quart mold; chill until set.
Unmold on curly lettuce and garnish with radish slices and olive slices.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water and let cool.
Mix all ingredients together well.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a greased casserole at 325° for 45 minutes.
A few minutes before you are ready to serve, sprinkle grated cheese over the top and allow to melt.

title: pumpkin spice bread
directions: Alternate adding mixtures from bowls #2 and #3 to the first bowl.
Bake at 350 degrees in greased and floured pans (about 35 minutes for 6 small pans or 55 minutes for 2 large pans).
Do toothpick test to see if done.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Test with toothpick.
Wrap in foil.
Yield:
1 (9 x 5-inch) loaf.

title: rose punch
directions: In
large punch bowl, combine wine, grenadine syrup and lemon juice.
Stir in ginger ale.
Serves 22.

title: dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well; serve with crackers.

title: slaw dressing
directions: Mix sugar, mustard
and salt together well.
Add mayonnaise and stir well.
Add vinegar and mix well.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Boil spaghetti until done.
While spaghetti is cooking, cook meat until done with onions and mushrooms.
Drain. Put sauces in with meat, onion and mushrooms; let simmer for 20 minutes.
Drain noodles.
Put noodles into a rectangle deep dish pan, then put the butter and Parmesan cheese in with noodles and mix until pasty.
Flatten noodles out and up on the sides.
Put the meat mixture on top of the noodles and spread out.
Top with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Put in oven for 20 minutes and then serve.

title: barbecue muffins
directions: Measure flour by spooning into measuring cup and leveling. Stir together the flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and pepper. Combine egg, milk, barbecue sauce, mustard, green onions and oil. Add to dry ingredients all at once.
Stir only until flour is moistened.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: pirogie
directions: Mix all ingredients with enough water to make a medium soft dough.
Knead well.
Roll out until thin.
Cut into squares to make 50 pirogie.
Place on each square, 1 teaspoon filling.
Fold in half to make triangles.
Pinch edges well to keep filling from escaping.
Drop in salted water and cook until all pirogie rise to the top of the water.
Cook for 5 minutes longer.
When done, pour a small amount of cold water on them and strain.
Place in serving dish and pour over butter that has been melted and slightly browned.
Eat while hot, and if desired, add salt and pepper. Pirogie may be spread carefully on a breadboard after draining to allow them to dry a bit, then place on a serving dish.
This will make them less soggy.

title: lupe's brownies
directions: Purchase 1 roll of your favorite cookie dough (any flavor). Spread into a pizza pan and bake according to directions. Decorate and cut as you please; serve.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine 1 tablespoon flour and salt, dredge meat in mixture. Heat skillet.
Add 2 tablespoons butter.
When melted, add meat and brown quickly.
Flipping meat to turn all sides, add mushrooms, onions and garlic.
Cook 3 or 4 minutes or until onions are tender.

title: old-fashioned boiled chocolate cake
directions: In
mixing
bowl,
sift
together
sugar and flour.
In saucepan,
put
butter, Crisco, cocoa and water.
Mix together and bring
to a rapid boil and pour over flour-sugar mixture. Add remaining
ingredients;
beat well and bake 25 minutes at 400° in an oblong pan.
Frost with Chocolate Frosting.

title: vickie's chili
directions: Heat oil in heavy 10-quart pot over medium heat.
Add onions, bell peppers, celery and garlic.
Cook, stirring until onions are translucent.
Add the meat to the pot a little at a time, stirring occasionally.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until the meat is evenly browned.
Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then lower heat and simmer, uncovered, for 2 1/2 to 3 hours. Stir often.
Taste and adjust seasonings.
Serves 6.

title: teriyaki meat loaf
directions: Mix meat
and
onion.
Combine egg and milk.
Add bread crumbs, then
combine with meat.
Mix soy sauce, sugar, garlic and mayonnaise in bowl.
Stir 1/2 sauce into meat loaf.
Shape meat loaf.
Halfway through cooking, pour remaining sauce over loaf. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve with rice!

title: apple cake
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in large bowl and beat until smooth.
Slice and peel about 10 apples.
Mix in another bowl with 1 tablespoon cinnamon and 2/3 cup sugar.
Layer batter and apples (about 3 layers) in greased, large tube pan with apples on top. Bake at 350° for 1 3/4 to 2 hours.

title: malibu chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken in a shallow baking dish. Place 1 to 2 slices of ham on each piece of chicken, then place 1 slice of cheese on top of the ham. Bake for 45 minutes.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Melt margarine in 3-quart saucepan. Remove from heat. Stir in remaining ingredients except chocolate chips. Spread batter in pan and sprinkle with chocolate chips. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: ole nacho platter
directions: Melt cheese and milk until thin.
Cover platter with chips. Sprinkle with layer of lettuce and tomato.
Pour cheese over all. Serve at once.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add to mixture of remaining ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in loaf pan.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: lemon "icebox" sandwich
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Cook in double boiler until thick. Cool.
Add lemon juice when mixture is cool.
Beat egg whites, adding 1/2 cup sugar.
Whip 1 cup cream.
Fold together (beaten egg whites and whipped cream).
Line dish (approximate size of an ice tray or a little larger size) with crumbs.
Pour in mixture.
Place more crumbs on top.
Drained cherries may be added for decoration, if desired.

title: jane brown's ham fruit sauce
directions: Drain juice into heavy skillet and reserve fruit.
Add lemon juice and brown sugar to juice.
Simmer until reduced to one-third (about 2
hours).
Cool awhile and then add rum. Arrange fruit in baking dish, and then pour sauce over it.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serve hot with sliced baked ham and sour cream.

title: six layer dinner
directions: Place all ingredients in casserole dish in layers in order given.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: candied carrots with apples
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Put carrots in saucepan.
Cover with boiling salted water.
Cover and cook just until tender.
Drain. Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Alternate layers of carrots and apples in greased casserole.
Sprinkle sugar mixture over each layer.
Dot top with butter or margarine.
Bake 45 minutes or until apples are tender.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: fried tomatoes
directions: Slice red tomatoes a little thick.
Dip in flour and beaten egg.
Dip in corn flake
crumbs; fry in a little oil until golden brown.

title: breakfast brunch
directions: Brown sausage and drain. Beat together eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with bread cubes. Top with sausage.
Pour egg mixture over top of sausage.
Top with cheese. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake the next morning at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Serve with fruit slices and/or coffee cake.

title: squash casserole
directions: Drain squash and mix with other vegetables, soup and sour cream.
Prepare stuffing with margarine.
Reserve some for topping and line bottom of casserole dish with remaining mixture.
Add vegetables and top with stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot cottage salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Melt margarine in milk and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: praline yams
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place drained yams in
ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients; blend well.
Sprinkle over yams.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Stir carefully halfway through and avoid mashing yams as they will be soft.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients together and blend over medium heat until smooth.
Use a double boiler.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Let set.
Mix other ingredients except flour.
When cooled, add yeast and flour, mix well.	Let rise until double, roll.
Spread with butter, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll and slice.	Let rise until double.	Bake at 400 degrees for 10-12 minutes.	Yield 2-3 dozen rolls.

title: "sinful" coconut cake
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13 pan. While hot, punch holes in cake top and pour Eagle Brand over. Let cool 2 hours. Mix cream of coconut and Cool Whip. Spread on top and sprinkle with coconut. Serves 8 to 12.

title: garden linguine
directions: In large skillet, heat oil and butter.
Stir in vegetables and simmer until tender.
Stir in broth, cream, basil, parsley, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 3 to 4 minutes.
In heated serving dish, toss linguine with vegetable mixture and Parmesan.
Serve immediately.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute chicken breasts 1st in butter with salt & pepper.
Put in bottom of greased baking dish.
Cover with soup, sour cream, salt and pepper, chip beef and then Swiss cheese.

title: chicken enchilada pie
directions: Cook and bone chicken; reserve 1 cup of broth.
Combine soup, broth, peppers. spices and Tabasco sauce.
Mix well.
Cover 2 1/2 or 4-quart casserole.
Start with corn chips in bottom, then chicken, soup mixture and a layer of cheese.
Continue, ending with a layer of cheese on top.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake 25 or 30 minutes.

title: favorite casserole
directions: To ground beef, add tomatoes/green chiles, oregano, tomato sauce, salt, pepper and sugar. Simmer for 20 minutes. Mix cream cheese and sour cream until smooth, then add 2/3 of the Cheddar cheese. Add this mixture to the beef mixture along with the noodles. Pour into 9 x 13 baking dish. Add remaining Cheddar cheese on top. Bake at 350° until bubbly (about 30 minutes).

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix with mixer all ingredients and pour into 4-quart jars. Very Good!

title: easy carrot cake
directions: Combine cake and pudding mixes, cinnamon, eggs, salt, water and oil in large mixing bowl; beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Stir in carrots and pecans.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done. Cool in pans for 10 minutes before removing.
When cool, frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Mix all the first ingredients and leave the ginger ale to be pour in just as you serve it.

title: date pudding cake
directions: Pour boiling water with soda over dates.
Let stand awhile. Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg; beat well, then add salt, date mixture, dry ingredients and nuts.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: magic lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine lemon juice and grated lemon rind or lemon extract; gradually stir into milk.
Add egg yolks and stir until well blended.
Pour into chilled crumb crust or cooled pastry shell. Add cream of tartar to egg whites; beat until almost stiff enough to hold a peak.
Add sugar gradually, beating until stiff but not dry.
Pile lightly on pie filling.
Bake in slow oven (325°) until lightly browned, about 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: country side chicken bake
directions: Place rice in greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cover with combined vegetables and pepper.
Combine soup and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Gradually add water to soup mixture.
Mix well.
Pour 1/2 the soup mixture over vegetables and rice.
Top with chicken pieces and remaining soup mixture.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1 hour or until chicken is tender and rice is cooked.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.

title: banana surprise
directions: Mash banana in a bowl until soft.
Add dash of nutmeg; stir. Add sprinkles, red and green sugar.
Stir.
Put in a drop of vanilla and drop of banana flavoring.
Stir with a toothpick.
Add food coloring; stir.
Serves one person.
